obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (48396)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48396&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the New Delhi Municipal`
  line `Council Act, 1994.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to New Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 25th day of May, 1994.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (48397)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48397&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) "Administrator" means the Administrator of the National Capital Territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(2) "Appellate Tribunal" means an Appellate Tribunal constituted under section 253;`
  line
  line `(3) "budget-grant" means the total sum entered on the expenditure side of a budget estimate under`
  line `a major head and adopted by the Council and includes any sum by which such budget-grant may be`
  line `increased or reduced by transfer from or to other heads in accordance with the provisions of this Act`
  line `and the regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(4) "building" means a house, out-house, stable, latrine, urinal, shed, hut, wall (other than a`
  line `boundary wall) or any other structure, whether of masonry, bricks, wood, mud, metal or other`
  line `material but does not include any portable shelter;`
  line
  line `(5) "bye-law" means a bye-law made under this Act, by notification in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(6) "casual vacancy" means a vacancy occurring otherwise than by efflux of time in the office of`
  line `a member of the Council;`
  line
  line `(7) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Council;`
  line
  line `(8) "Corporation" means the Municipal Corporation of Delhi established under the Delhi`
  line `Municipal Corporation Act, 1957 (66 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(9) "Council" means the New Delhi Municipal Council established under this Act;`
  line
  line `(10) "dangerous disease" means--`
  line
  line `(a) cholera, plague, chicken-pox, small-pox, tuberculosis, leprosy, enteric fever,`
  line `cerebrospinal meningitis and diptheria; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other epidemic, endemic or infectious disease which the Chairperson may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a dangerous disease for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(11) "Delhi" means the entire area of the National Capital Territory of Delhi except New Delhi`
  line `and Delhi Cantonment as defined in clause (11) of section 2 of the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act,`
  line `1957 (66 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(12) "drain" includes a sewer, a house drain, a drain of any other description, a tunnel, a culvert, a`
  line `ditch, a channel and any other device for carrying off sewage, offensive matter, polluted water, waste`
  line `water, rain water or sub-soil water;`
  line
  line `(13) "entertainment" includes any exhibition, performance, amusement, game or sport to which`
  line `persons are ordinarily admitted on payment;`
  line
  line `(14) "factory" means a factory as defined in the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(15) "filth" includes offensive matter and sewage;`
  line
  line `(16) goods includes animals;`
  line
  line `(17) "Government" means the Government of the National Capital Territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(18) "house-gully" means a passage or strip of land constructed, set apart or utilised for the`
  line `purpose of serving as or carrying a drain or affording access to a latrine, urinal, cesspool or other`
  line `receptacle for filth or other polluted matter, by municipal employee or other person employed in the`
  line `cleansing thereof or in the removal of such matter therefrom;`
  line
  line `(19) "hut" means any building which is constructed principally of wood, bamboo, mud, leaves,`
  line `grass, cloth or thatch and includes any structure of whatever material made which the Council may`
  line `declare to be a hut for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(20) "inhabitant", in relation to the municipal area of New Delhi includes any person ordinarily`
  line `residing or carrying on business or owning or occupying immovable property therein and in case of a`
  line `dispute, means any person or persons declared by the Chairperson to be an inhabitant;`
  line
  line `(21) "land" includes benefits to arise out of land, things attached to the earth or permanently`
  line `fastened to anything attached to the earth and rights created by law over any street;`
  line
  line `(22) "licensed engineer" and "licensed plumber" mean respectively a person licensed under the`
  line `provisions of this Act as an engineer and a plumber;`
  line
  line `(23) "market" includes any place where persons assemble for the sale of, or for the purpose of`
  line `exposing for sale, meat, fish, fruits, vegetables, animals intended for human consumption or any other`
  line `articles of human food whatsoever, with or without the consent of the owner of such place`
  line `notwithstanding that there may be no common regulation for the concourse of buyers and sellers and`
  line `whether or not any control is exercised over the business of, or the person frequenting, the market by`
  line `the owner of the place or by any other person;`
  line
  line `(24) "member", in relation to the Council, means a member of the Council and includes the`
  line Chairperson;
  line
  line `(25) "municipal market" means a market vested in or managed by the Council;`
  line
  line `(26) "municipal water works" means water works vested in the Council;`
  line
  line `(27) "New Delhi" means the area within the boundaries described in the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(28) "nuisance" includes any act, omission, place, animal or thing which causes or is likely to`
  line `cause injury, danger, annoyance or offence to the sense of sight, smell or hearing or disturbance to`
  line `rest or sleep, or which is or may be dangerous to life or injurious to health or property;`
  line
  line `(29) "occupier" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) any person who for the time being is paying or is liable to pay to the owner the rent or any`
  line `portion of the rent of the land or building in respect of which such rent is paid or is payable;`
  line
  line `(b) an owner in occupation of or otherwise using his land or building;`
  line
  line `(c) a rent-free tenant of any land or building;`
  line
  line `(d) a licensee in occupation of any land or building; and`
  line
  line `(e) any person who is liable to pay to the owner damages for the use and occupation of any`
  line `land or building;`
  line
  line `(30) "offensive matter" includes animal carcasses, kitchen or stable refuse, dung, dirt and putrid`
  line `or putrefying substances other than sewage;`
  line
  line `(31) "Official Gazette" means the Official Gazette of the National Capital Territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(32) "owner" includes a person who for the time being is receiving or is entitled to receive, the`
  line `rent of any land or building whether on his own account or on account of himself and others or as an`
  line `agent, trustee, guardian or receiver for any other person or who should so receive the rent or be`
  line `entitled to receive it if the land or building or part thereof were let to a tenant and also includes--`
  line
  line `(a) the custodian of evacuee property in respect of evacuee property vested in him under the`
  line `Administration of Evacuee Property Act, 1950 (31 of 1950); and`
  line
  line `(b) the estate officer to the Government of India, the Secretary of the Delhi Development`
  line `Authority, constituted under the Delhi Development Act, 1957 (61 of 1957), the General Manager`
  line `of a railway and the head of a Government department, in respect of properties under their`
  line `respective control;`
  line
  line `(33) "premises" means any land or building or part of a building and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) the garden, ground and out-houses, if any, appertaining to a building or part of a building;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) any fittings affixed to a building or part of a building for the more beneficial enjoyment`
  line thereof;
  line
  line `(34) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(35) "private market" means a market which is not a municipal market;`
  line
  line `(36) "private street" means any street, which is not a public street and includes any passage`
  line `securing access to two or more places belonging to the same or different owners;`
  line
  line `(37) "public place" means any place which is open to the use and enjoyment of the public,`
  line `whether it is actually used or enjoyed by the public or not;`
  line
  line `(38) "public securities" means any securities of the Central Government or a State Government or`
  line `any securities guaranteed by the Central Government or a State Government or any securities issued`
  line `under this Act or any debentures issued by the Bombay, Calcutta, Delhi or Madras Municipal`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(39) "public street" means any street which vests in the Council as a public street or the soil`
  line `below the surface of which vests in the Council or which under the provisions of this Act becomes, or`
  line `is declared to be, a public street;`
  line
  line `(40) "railway administration" has the meaning assigned to it in the Railways Act, 1989`
  line `(24 of 1989);`
  line
  line `(41) "rate payer" means a person liable to pay any rate, tax, cess or licence fee under this Act;`
  line
  line `(42) "rateable value" means the value of any land or building fixed in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the bye-laws made thereunder for the purpose of assessment to property`
  line taxes;
  line
  line `(43) "regulation" means a regulation made by the Council under this Act by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(44) "reside",--`
  line
  line `(a) a person shall be deemed to "reside" in any dwelling-house which or some portion of`
  line `which he sometimes, although not uninterruptedly, uses as a sleeping apartment, and`
  line
  line `(b) a person shall not be deemed to cease to "reside" in any such dwelling-house merely`
  line `because he is absent from it or has elsewhere another dwelling-house in which he resides, if there`
  line `is the liberty of returning to it at any time and no abandonment of the intention of returning to it;`
  line
  line `(45) "rubbish" includes ashes, broken bricks, broken glass, dust, malba, mortar and refuse of any`
  line `kind which is not filth;`
  line
  line `(46) "rule" means a rule made by the Central Government under this Act by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(47) "Scheduled Castes" means such castes, races or tribes or parts of or groups within such`
  line `castes, races or tribes as are deemed to be Scheduled Castes under article 341 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(48) "service passage" or "lane" or "bye-lane" means a passage or strip of land constructed, set`
  line `apart or utilised for the purpose of serving as or carrying a drain or electricity cable (underground or`
  line `over-head) and any electrical and other allied installations or any other civic services by municipal`
  line `employees or other person employed in the service thereof;`
  line
  line `(49) "sewage" means night-soil and other contents of latrines, urinals, cesspools or drains, and`
  line `polluted water from sinks, bath-rooms, stables, cattle sheds and other like places and includes trade`
  line `effluents and discharges from factories of all kinds;`
  line
  line `(50) "shed" means a slight or temporary structure for shade or shelter;`
  line
  line `(51) "street" includes any way, road, lane, square, court, alley, gully, passage, whether a`
  line `thoroughfare or not and whether built upon or not, over which the public have a right of way and also`
  line `the roadway or footway over any bridge or causeway;`
  line
  line `(52) "trade effluent" means any liquid either with or without particles of matter in suspension`
  line `therein, which is wholly or in part produced in the course of any trade or industry carried on at trade`
  line `premises, and in relation to any trade premises means any such liquid as aforesaid which is so`
  line `produced in the course of any trade or industry carried on at those premises, but does not include`
  line `domestic sewage;`
  line
  line `(53) "trade premises" means any premises used or intended to be used for carrying on any trade`
  line `or industry;`
  line
  line `(54) "trade refuse" means the refuse of any trade or industry;`
  line
  line `(55) "vehicle" includes a carriage, cart, van, dray, truck, hand-cart, bicycle, tricycle,`
  line `cycle-rickshaw, auto-rickshaw, motor vehicle and every wheeled conveyance which is used or is`
  line `capable of being used on a street;`
  line
  line `(56) "water course" includes any river, stream or channel whether natural or artificial;`
  line
  line `(57) "water works" includes all lakes, tanks, streams, any river, cisterns, springs, pumps, wells,`
  line `reservoirs, aqueducts, water trucks, sluices, mains, pipes, culverts, hydrants, stand-pipes and conduits`
  line `and all lands, buildings, machinery bridges and things, used for, or intended for the purpose of,`
  line `supplying water;`
  line
  line `(58) "workshop" means any premises (including the precincts thereof) other than a factory,`
  line `wherein any industrial process is carried on;`
  line
  line `(59) "year" means a year commencing on the 1st day of April.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (48398)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48398&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be a Council charged with the municipal`
  line `government of New Delhi, to be known as the New Delhi Municipal Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property`
  line `and may by the said name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (48399)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48399&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, from amongst the officers, of the Central Government or the Government, of`
  line `or above the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India to be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Chief Minister of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b)`
  line `^1[two members] of Legislative Assembly of Delhi representing constituencies which comprise`
  line `wholly or partly the New Delhi area;`
  line
  line `(c) five members from amongst the officers of the Central Government or the Government or`
  line `their undertakings, to be nominated by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d)`
  line `^2[four members] to be nominated by the Central Government in consultation with the Chief`
  line `Minister of Delhi to represent from amongst lawyers, doctors, chartered accountants, engineers,`
  line `business and financial consultants, intellectuals, traders, labourers, social workers including social`
  line `scientists, artists, media persons, sports persons and any other class of persons as may be specified by`
  line `the Central Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `^3[(e) the Member of Parliament, representing constituency which comprises wholly or partly the`
  line `New Delhi area.]`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `^5[(3) Out of the thirteen members referred to in sub-section (1), there shall be, at least,--`
  line
  line `(a) three members who are women;`
  line
  line `(b) two members belonging to the Scheduled Castes, out of which one member shall be from`
  line `the members nominated under clause (d) of sub-section (1).]`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall nominate, in consultation with the Chief Minister of Delhi, a`
  line `Vice-Chairperson from amongst the members specified in clauses (b) and (d) of sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2012, s. 2, for "three members" (w.e.f. 1-3-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 5 of 2012, s. 2, for "two members" (w.e.f. 1-3-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-3-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-3-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-3-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (48400)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Duration of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48400&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council, unless sooner dissolved under section 398 or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, shall continue for five years from the date appointed for its first`
  line `meeting and no longer.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council,--`
  line
  line `(a) where it is dissolved before the expiry of its duration under sub-section (1), shall be`
  line `reconstituted within a period of six months of such dissolution; and`
  line
  line `(b) where it is dissolved after the expiry of its duration, shall be reconstituted before such expiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (48401)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Disqualification for membership of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48401&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person, other than a member of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the National Capital Territory of Delhi, shall be disqualified for being nominated`
  line `as a member of the Council on the ground that he holds an office of profit for purposes of election to the`
  line `legislature of the National Capital Territory of Delhi under any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person sits or votes as a member of the Council when he knows that he is not qualified or that`
  line `he is disqualified for such membership, he shall be liable in respect of each day on which he so sits or`
  line `votes to a penalty of three hundred rupees to be recovered as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (48402)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Oath or affirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48402&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every member before taking his seat shall make and subscribe at a`
  line `meeting of the Council an oath or affirmation according to the following form, namely:--`
  line
  line `"I, A. B., having been nominated as a member of Council do swear in the name of God/solemnly`
  line `affirm that I will bear true faith and allegiance to the Constitution of India as by law established, that I`
  line `will faithfully discharge the duty upon which I am about to enter."`
  line
  line `(2) If a person sits or votes as a member before he has complied with the requirements of`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall be liable in respect of each day on which he sits or votes as the case may be, to a`
  line `penalty of three hundred rupees to be recovered as arrears of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (48403)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Vacation of seat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48403&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a member resigns his seat by writing under his hand addressed to the`
  line `Chairperson and delivered to him, his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(2) If during three successive months, a member is without permission of the Council, absent from all`
  line `the meetings thereof, the Council may recommend to the Central Government that the seat of such`
  line `member may be declared vacant.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (48404)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Setting-up of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48404&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may constitute as many committees as it thinks fit for`
  line `the exercise of any power or discharge of any function which the Council may by resolution delegate to`
  line `them or for inquiring into, reporting or advising upon any matter which the Council may refer to them.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such committee shall consist of members of the Council only:`
  line
  line `Provided that a committee may, with the sanction of the Council, co-opt not more than two persons`
  line `who are not members of the Council, but who in the opinion of the Council possesses special`
  line `qualifications for serving on such committee.`
  line
  line `(3) Each committee constituted under this section shall be presided by the Chairperson of the Council.`
  line
  line `(4) Any matter relating to a committee constituted under this section, not expressly provided in this`
  line `Act may be provided by regulations made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (48405)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `General powers of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48405&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules,`
  line `regulations and bye-laws made thereunder the municipal government of New Delhi shall vest in the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), it shall be the duty of the`
  line `Council to consider all periodical statements of the receipts and disbursements and all progress reports`
  line `and pass such resolutions thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council may at any time require the Chairperson--`
  line
  line `(a) to produce any record, correspondence, plan or other document which is in his possession or`
  line `under his control as Chairperson or which is recorded or filed in his office or in the office of any`
  line `municipal officer or other municipal employee subordinate to him;`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish any return, plan, estimate, statement, account or statistics concerning or connected`
  line `with any matter pertaining to the administration of this Act or the municipal government of New`
  line Delhi;
  line
  line `(c) to furnish a report by himself or to obtain from the head of any department subordinate to him`
  line `and furnish with his own remarks thereon, a report, upon any subject concerning or connected with`
  line `the administration of this Act or the municipal government of New Delhi.`
  line
  line `(4) Every such requisition shall be complied with by the Chairperson without any unreasonable delay;`
  line
  line `and it shall be incumbent on every municipal officer and other municipal employee to obey any order`
  line `made by the Chairperson in pursuance of any such requisition:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson shall not be bound to comply with any such requisition if with the`
  line `previous approval of the Administrator he makes a statement that such compliance would be prejudicial`
  line `to public interest or to the interests of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (48406)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Obligatory functions of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48406&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, it shall be incumbent on the Council to make adequate provisions by any`
  line `means or measures which it may lawfully use or take, for each of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the construction, maintenance and cleansing of drains and drainage works and of public`
  line `latrines, urinals and similar conveniences;`
  line
  line `(b) the construction and maintenance of works and means for providing supply of water for`
  line `public and private purposes;`
  line
  line `(c) the scavenging, removal and disposal of filth, rubbish and other obnoxious or polluted`
  line matters;
  line
  line `(d) the construction or purchase, maintenance, extension, management for--`
  line
  line `(i) supply and distribution of electricity to the public;`
  line
  line `(ii) providing a sufficient supply of pure and wholesome water;`
  line
  line `(e) the reclamation of unhealthy localities, the removal of noxious vegetation and generally the`
  line `abatement of all nuisances;`
  line
  line `(f) the regulation of places for the disposal of the dead and the provision and maintenance of`
  line `places for the said purpose;`
  line
  line `(g) the registration of births and deaths;`
  line
  line `(h) public vaccination and inoculation;`
  line
  line `(i) measures for preventing and checking the spread of dangerous diseases;`
  line
  line `(j) the establishment and maintenance of hospitals, dispensaries and maternity and child welfare`
  line `centres and the carrying out of other measures necessary for public medical relief;`
  line
  line `(k) the construction and maintenance of municipal markets and regulation of all markets;`
  line
  line `(l) the regulation and abatement of offensive or dangerous trade or practices;`
  line
  line `(m) the securing or removal of dangerous buildings and places;`
  line
  line `(n) the construction, maintenance, alteration and improvements of public streets, bridges,`
  line `culverts, causeways and the like;`
  line
  line `(o) the lighting, watering and cleansing of public streets and other public places;`
  line
  line `(p) the removal of obstructions and projections in or upon streets, bridges and other public places;`
  line
  line `(q) the naming and numbering of streets and premises;`
  line
  line `(r) the establishment, maintenance of, and aid to, schools for primary educations subject to such`
  line `grants as may be determined by the Central Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(s) the maintenance of municipal offices;`
  line
  line `(t) the laying out or the maintenance of public parks, gardens or recreation grounds;`
  line
  line `(u) the maintenance of monuments and memorials vested in any local authority in New Delhi`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act or which may be vested in the Council after such`
  line commencement;
  line
  line `(v) the maintenance and development of the value of all properties vested in or entrusted to the`
  line `management of the Council;`
  line
  line `(w) the preparation of plans for economic development and social justice;`
  line
  line `(x) the maintenance including the expansion and upgradation of facilities of the hospitals existing`
  line `on the date of the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(y) sanction or refuse erection or re-erection of buildings; and`
  line
  line `(z) the fulfilment of any other obligation imposed by or under this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (48407)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Discretionary functions of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48407&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any general or special order of the`
  line `Government, or the Central Government from time to time, the Council may provide either wholly or in`
  line `part for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the furtherance of education including cultural and physical education, by measures other than`
  line `the establishment and maintenance of, and aid to, schools for primary education;`
  line
  line `(b) the establishment and maintenance of, and aid to, libraries, museums, art galleries, botanical`
  line `or zoological collections;`
  line
  line `(c) the establishment and maintenance of, and aid to, stadia, gymnasia, akharas and places for`
  line `sports and games;`
  line
  line `(d) the planting and care of trees on roadsides and elsewhere;`
  line
  line `(e) the surveys of buildings and lands;`
  line
  line `(f) the registration of marriages;`
  line
  line `(g) the taking of a census of population;`
  line
  line `(h) the provision of housing accommodation for the inhabitants of any area or for any class of`
  line inhabitants;
  line
  line `(i) the providing of music or other entertainments in public places or places of public resort and`
  line `the establishment of theatres and cinemas;`
  line
  line `(j) the organisation and management of fairs and exhibitions;`
  line
  line `(k) the acquisition of movable or immovable property for any of the purpose before mentioned,`
  line `including payment of the cost of investigations, surveys or examinations in relation thereto for the`
  line `construction or adaptation of building necessary for such purposes;`
  line
  line `(l) the construction and maintenance of--`
  line
  line `(i) rest-houses,`
  line
  line `(ii) poor-houses,`
  line
  line `(iii) infirmaries,`
  line
  line `(iv) children's homes,`
  line
  line `(v) houses for the deaf and dumb and for disabled and handicapped children,`
  line
  line `(vi) shelters for destitute and disabled persons,`
  line
  line `(vii) asylums for persons of unsound mind;`
  line
  line `(m) the construction and maintenance of cattle pounds;`
  line
  line `(n) the building or purchase and maintenance of dwelling-houses for municipal officers and other`
  line `municipal employees;`
  line
  line `(o) any measures for the welfare of the municipal officers and other municipal employees or any`
  line `class of them including the sanctioning of loans to such officers and employees or any class of them`
  line `for construction of houses and purchase of vehicles;`
  line
  line `(p) the organisation or management of chemical or bacteriological laboratories for the`
  line `examination or analysis of water, food and drugs for the detection of diseases or research connected`
  line `with the public health or medical relief;`
  line
  line `(q) the provision for relief to destitute and disabled persons;`
  line
  line `(r) the establishment and maintenance of veterinary hospitals;`
  line
  line `(s) the organisation, construction, maintenance and management of swimming pools, public wash`
  line `houses, bathing places and other institutions designed for the improvement of public health;`
  line
  line `(t) the organisation and management of farms and dairies within or without New Delhi for the`
  line `supply, distribution and processing of milk and milk products for the benefit of the residents of New`
  line Delhi;
  line
  line `(u) the organisation and management of cottage industries, handicraft centres and sales emporia;`
  line
  line `(v) the construction and maintenance of warehouses and godowns;`
  line
  line `(w) the construction and maintenance of garrages, sheds and stands for vehicles and cattle biers;`
  line
  line `(x) the provision for unfiltered water supply;`
  line
  line `(y) the improvement of New Delhi in accordance with improvement schemes approved by the`
  line Council;
  line
  line `(z) any measure not hereinbefore specifically mentioned, likely to promote public safety, health,`
  line `convenience or general welfare.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (48408)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Appointment, etc., of the Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48408&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, appoint a suitable person as the Chairperson of the Council in accordance with`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 4.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson so appointed shall hold office for a term of five years in the first instance:`
  line
  line `Provided that his appointment may be renewed from time to time for a term not exceeding one year at`
  line `a time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Chairperson holds a lien on any service under the Central`
  line `Government or the Government, the Central Government may at any time after reasonable notice to the`
  line `Council replace his services at the disposal of the concerned Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may remove the Chairperson from office at any time if it appears to that`
  line `Government that he is incapable of performing the duties of his office or has been guilty of neglect or`
  line `misconduct in the discharge of such duties, which renders his removal expedient.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson shall not undertake any work unconnected with his office without the sanction of`
  line `the Central Government and of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (48409)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Leave of absence of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48409&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Leave may be granted to the Chairperson by the`
  line Administrator.
  line
  line `(2) Whenever such leave is granted to the Chairperson, the Central Government shall appoint another`
  line `person to officiate as Chairperson in his place.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (48410)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Appointment of officiating Chairperson in case of death, resignation or removal of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48410&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If any vacancy occurs in the office of Chairperson on account of death, resignation or`
  line `removal, the Central Government shall appoint another person to officiate as Chairperson in his place for`
  line `a term not exceeding two months, pending the appointment of a Chairperson under section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (48411)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Salary and allowances of the Chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48411&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall be paid`
  line `out of the New Delhi Municipal Fund constituted under section 44 such monthly salary and such monthly`
  line `allowances, if any, as may from time to time be fixed by the Central Government and may be given such`
  line `facilities, if any, in relation to residential accommodation, conveyance and the like as may from time to`
  line `time be fixed by that Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the salary of the Chairperson shall not be varied to his disadvantage after his`
  line appointment.
  line
  line `(2) The members shall be entitled to receive allowances for attendance at meeting of Council and of`
  line `any of its committees at such rates as may be determined by rules made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (48412)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Service regulations of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48412&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `If a member is an officer in the service of the Government or`
  line `the Central Government, the Council shall make such contribution towards his leave allowances, pension`
  line `and provident fund as may be required by the conditions of his service under the Government or the`
  line `Central Government to be paid by him or for him, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (48413)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Functions of the Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48413&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act the entire executive`
  line `power for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Act and of any other Act, for the time being in`
  line `force which confers, any power or imposes any duty on the Council, shall vest in the Chairperson who`
  line `shall also--`
  line
  line `(a) exercise all the powers and perform all the duties specifically conferred or imposed upon him`
  line `by this Act or by any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the duties of and exercise supervision and control over the acts and proceedings of,`
  line `all municipal officers and other municipal employees and subject to any regulation that may be made`
  line `in this behalf, dispose of all questions relating to the service of the said officers and other employees`
  line `and their pay, privileges, allowances and other conditions of service;`
  line
  line `(c) on the occurrence or threatened occurrence of any sudden accident or any unforeseen event or`
  line `natural calamity involving or likely to involve extensive damage to any property of the Council, or`
  line `danger to human life, take such immediate action as he considers necessary and make a report`
  line `forthwith to the Council and the Administrator of the action he has taken and the reasons for the same`
  line `as also of the amount of cost, if any, incurred or likely to be incurred in consequence of such action,`
  line `which is not covered by a budget-grant; and`
  line
  line `(d) subject to any regulation that may be made in this behalf, be the disciplinary authority in`
  line `relation to all municipal officers and other municipal employees.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (48414)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Chairperson not to be interested in any contract, etc., with the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48414&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall`
  line `be disqualified for being appointed as the Chairperson who has directly or indirectly, by himself or by a`
  line `partner or any other person, any share or interest in any contract made with, or any work being done for,`
  line `the Council other than as such Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Chairperson acquires directly or indirectly, by himself or by his partner, or any other person,`
  line `any share or interest in any such contract or work as is referred to in sub-section (1), he shall, unless the`
  line `Central Government in any particular case otherwise decides, be liable to be removed from his office by`
  line `the order of the authority competent to remove him under the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that before an order of removal is made the Chairperson shall be given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause against the action proposed to be taken in regard to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (48415)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Exercise of powers to be subject to sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48415&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the`
  line `exercise of any power or the performance of any duty conferred or imposed upon the Council by or under`
  line `this Act which will involve expenditure, shall be subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that such expenditure, in so far as it is to be incurred in the year in which such power is`
  line `exercised or duty performed, shall be provided for under a current budget-grant; and`
  line
  line `(b) that if the exercise of such powers or the performance of such duty involves or is likely to`
  line `involve expenditure for any period or at any time after the close of the said year, such expenditure`
  line `shall not be incurred without the sanction of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (48416)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48416&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall ordinarily hold at least one meeting in every month for the`
  line `transaction of business.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and in his absence the Vice-Chairperson may, whenever he thinks fit, and shall,`
  line `upon a requisition in writing by not less than one-fourth of the total number of members, convene a`
  line `special meeting of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) Any meeting may be adjourned until the next or any subsequent date, and an adjourned meeting`
  line `may be further adjourned in like manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (48417)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `First meeting of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48417&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The first meeting of the Council shall be held as early as possible`
  line `and shall be convened by the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (48418)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Notice of meetings and business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48418&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `A list of the business to be transacted at every meeting`
  line `except at an adjourned meeting shall be sent to the address of each member at least seventy-two hours`
  line `before the time fixed for such meeting; and no business shall, except where the Chairperson otherwise`
  line `directs, be brought before, or transacted at, in any meeting other than the business of which a notice has`
  line `been so given:`
  line
  line `Provided that any member may send of deliver to the Secretary notice of any resolution going beyond`
  line `the matters mentioned in the notice given of such meeting so as to reach him at least forty-eight hours`
  line `before the date fixed for the meeting and the Secretary shall, with all possible despatch, take steps to`
  line `circulate such resolution to every member in such manner as he may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (48419)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Quorum.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48419&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The quorum necessary for the transaction of business at a meeting of the Council`
  line `shall be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) If at any time during a meeting of the Council, there is no quorum, it shall be the duty of the`
  line `Chairperson or the person presiding over such meeting either to adjourn the meeting or to suspend the`
  line `meeting until there is a quorum.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a meeting has been adjourned under sub-section (2), the business which would have been`
  line `brought before the original meeting if there had been a quorum present there at, shall be brought before,`
  line `and may be transacted at an adjourned meeting, whether there is a quorum present or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (48420)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Presiding Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2012, s. 3, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-3-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48420&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The meetings of the Council shall be presided over, in the following`
  line `order, by,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Minister of Delhi, if he is a member of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Delhi representing the constituency which comprises wholly or partly the New Delhi area, and`
  line `attends the meeting being a member of the Council under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 4; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Union Minister, if he is a Member of Parliament representing the constituency`
  line `which comprises wholly or partly the New Delhi area, and attends the meeting being a member of`
  line `the Council under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 4; or`
  line
  line `(c) the Minister in the Government of National Capital Territory of Delhi, if he is a Member`
  line `of the Legislative Assembly of Delhi representing the constituency which comprises wholly or partly`
  line `the New Delhi area, and attends the meeting being a member of the Council under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4; or`
  line
  line `(d) the Member of Parliament not being a Minister for the Union representing the`
  line `constituency which comprises wholly or partly the New Delhi area, and attends the meeting being a`
  line `member of the Council under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 4; or`
  line
  line `(e) the Chairperson of the Council.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or the person presiding over a meeting shall have and exercise a second or a`
  line `casting vote in all cases of equality of votes.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (48421)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Method of deciding questions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48421&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all matters required`
  line `to be decided by the Council shall be decided by the majority of the votes of the members present and`
  line voting.
  line
  line `(2) The voting shall be by show of hands, but the Council may, subject to such regulations as may be`
  line `made by it, resolve that any question or class of question shall be decided by ballot.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (48422)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Members not to vote on matter in which they are interested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48422&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No member shall vote at a`
  line `meeting of the Council or of any Committee thereof on any question relating to his own conduct or vote`
  line `or take part in any discussion on any matter (other than a matter affecting generally the residents of New`
  line `Delhi) which affect his pecuniary interest or any property in respect of which he is directly or indirectly`
  line `interested, or any property of or for which he is a manager or agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (48829)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Right to attend meetings of Council and its committees, etc., and right of members to ask questions in relation to the municipal government of New Delhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48829&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any municipal officer`
  line `authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf may attend, speak in, or otherwise take part in the`
  line `proceedings of, any meeting of the Council or any of its Committees, but none of the persons specified`
  line `herein shall by virtue of this sub-section be entitled to vote in any such meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) A member may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), ask the Chairperson questions on any`
  line `matter relating to the municipal government of New Delhi or the administration of this Act in any`
  line `meeting of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The right to ask a question shall be governed by the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) not less than seven clear days notice in writing specifying the question shall be given to the`
  line Secretary;
  line
  line `(b) no question shall--`
  line
  line `(i) bring in any name or statement not strictly necessary to make the question intelligible,`
  line
  line `(ii) contain argument, ironical expressions, imputations, epithets or defamatory statements,`
  line
  line `(iii) ask for an expression of opinion or the solution of a hypothetical proposition,`
  line
  line `(iv) ask as to the character or conduct of any person except in his official or public capacity,`
  line
  line `(v) relate to a matter which is not primarily the concern of the Council,`
  line
  line `(vi) make or imply a charge of a personal character,`
  line
  line `(vii) raise questions of policy too large to be dealt with within the limits of an answer to a`
  line question,
  line
  line `(viii) repeat in substance questions already answered or to which an answer has been refused,`
  line
  line `(ix) ask for information on trivial matters,`
  line
  line `(x) ordinarily ask for information on matters of past history,`
  line
  line `(xi) ask for information set forth in accessible documents or in ordinary works of reference,`
  line
  line `(xii) raise matters under the control of bodies or persons not primarily responsible to the`
  line Council,
  line
  line `(xiii) ask for any information on matter which is under adjudication by a court of law.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson shall not be bound to answer a question if it asks for information which has been`
  line `communicated to him in confidence or if in the opinion of the Chairperson it cannot be answered without`
  line `prejudice to public interest or the interest of the Council.`
  line
  line `(5) The Council may make regulations for the transaction of business at its meetings:`
  line
  line `Provided that the time, place and procedure for the first meeting after the constitution of the Council`
  line `under section 4 shall be determined by the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (48424)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Keeping of minutes and proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48424&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Minutes in which shall be recorded the names of the`
  line `members present at, and the proceedings of each meeting of the Council, and every other committee`
  line `constituted under sub-section (1) of section 9 shall be drawn up and recorded in a book to be kept for that`
  line `purpose, and shall be laid before the next ensuring meeting of the Council, or of such committee, as the`
  line `case may be, and signed at such meeting by the presiding officer thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (48425)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Circulation of minutes and inspection of minutes and reports of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48425&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Minutes`
  line `of the proceedings of each meeting of the Council shall be circulated to all the members and shall at`
  line `reasonable times be available at the municipal office for inspection by any other person on payment of a`
  line `fee of two rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Full reports, if any, of such proceedings shall similarly be available for inspection, by any member`
  line `without charge and by any other person on payment of a fee of two rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (48426)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Forwarding minutes and reports of proceedings to the Administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48426&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Secretary`
  line `shall forward to the Administrator a copy of the minutes of the proceedings of each meeting of the`
  line `Council, within ten days from the date on which the minutes of the proceedings of such meeting were`
  line `signed under section 29.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator may also in any case ask for a copy of any paper or all the papers which were`
  line `laid before the Council or any committee thereof and the Secretary shall forward to the Administrator a`
  line `copy of such paper or papers.`
  line
  line `(3) The Secretary shall also forward to the Administrator as soon as may be after the date referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) a full report of the proceedings of each meeting of the Council, if any such report be`
  line prepared.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (48427)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Validation of proceedings, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48427&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act done or proceedings taken under this Act shall be`
  line `questioned on the ground merely of--`
  line
  line `(a) the seat of any member remaining unfilled from any cause whatsoever;`
  line
  line `(b) the existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Council or in any`
  line `committee thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) any member having voted or taken part in any proceedings in contravention of section 27;`
  line
  line `(d) any defect or irregularity not affecting the merits of the case.`
  line
  line `(2) Every meeting of the Council or of any committee thereof, the minutes of the proceeding of which`
  line `have been duly drawn up and signed shall be deemed to have been duly convened and to be free from all`
  line `defects and irregularities.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (48428)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Appointment of certain officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48428&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall appoint suitable persons to be the`
  line `Secretary and Chief Auditor of the Council, and such other officer or officers as the Council may deem fit`
  line `on such monthly salaries and such allowances, if any, as may be fixed by the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Auditor shall not be eligible for any other office under the Council after he`
  line `has ceased to hold this office.`
  line
  line `(2) The appointment of the Secretary and the Chief Auditor shall be made with the previous approval`
  line `of the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (48429)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Schedule of permanent posts and creation of temporary posts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48429&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall`
  line `from time to time prepare and lay before the Council a Schedule of category 'A' and category 'B' posts`
  line `other than the posts of Secretary and Chief Auditor specified in section 33, setting forth the designations`
  line `and grades of municipal officers and other municipal employees who should be maintained permanently`
  line `in the service of the Council indicating therein the salaries, fees and allowances which are proposed to be`
  line `paid to such officers and other employees.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall approve and sanction the Schedule either without modifications or with such`
  line `modifications as it thinks fit or may amend it either on its own motion or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson may create any category 'B', or category 'C', or Category 'D' post and for a`
  line `period not exceeding six months any category 'A' post:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such category 'A' post shall be beyond the said period without the previous approval`
  line `of the Council.`
  line
  line `(4) In this section and in section 36--`
  line
  line `(i) "category 'A' post" means any post, which having regard to its scale of pay or emoluments,`
  line
  line `would, if such post had been in the Central Government, be classified as a Group 'A' post under the`
  line `Central Government in accordance with the orders issued by that Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(ii) "category 'B' post" means any post which having regard to its scale of pay or emoluments,`
  line
  line `would, if such post had been in the Central Government, be classified as a Group 'B' post under the`
  line `Central Government in accordance with the orders issued by that Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(iii) "category 'C' posts" means any post, which having regard to its scale of pay or emoluments`
  line `would, if such post had been in the Central Government, be classified as a Group 'C' post under the`
  line `Central Government, in accordance with the orders issued by that Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(iv) "category 'D' posts" means any post, other than a category 'A' or category 'B' or category`
  line `'C' post.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (48430)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Restriction on employment of permanent officers and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48430&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No permanent`
  line `officer or other employee shall be entertained in any department of the municipal administration unless he has been appointed under sub-section (1) of section 33 or his office and emoluments are included in the`
  line `Schedule for the time being in force prepared and sanctioned under section 34 or is appointed against a`
  line `permanent post under section 36.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (48431)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to make appointments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48431&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 33, the power of`
  line `appointing municipal officers and other municipal employees, whether temporary or permanent,--`
  line
  line `(a) to category 'A', category 'B' and category 'C' posts, shall vest in the Chairperson; and`
  line
  line `(b) to category 'D' posts shall vest in the Secretary.`
  line
  line `(2) The claims of the members of the Scheduled Castes shall be taken into consideration, consistently`
  line `with the maintenance of efficiency of administration, in the making of appointments of municipal officers`
  line `and other municipal employees.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (48432)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Officers and other employees not to undertake any extraneous work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48432&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `No municipal officer`
  line `or other municipal employee shall undertake any work unconnected with his duties under this Act except`
  line `with the permission of the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (48433)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Officers and other employees not to be interested in any contract, etc., with the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48433&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified for being appointed as a municipal officer or employee if he`
  line `has, directly or indirectly, by himself or by a partner or any other person any share or interest in any`
  line `contract made with, or any work being done for, the Council other than as such officer or employee.`
  line
  line `(2) If any such officer or other employee acquires, directly or indirectly, by himself or by a partner or`
  line `any other person, any share or interest in any such contract or work as is referred to in sub-section (1), he`
  line `shall unless the authority appointing him in any particular case otherwise decides, be liable to be removed`
  line `from his office by an order of such authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that before an order of removal is made, such officer or other employee shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the action proposed to be taken in regard to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (48434)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Punishment for municipal officers and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48434&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every municipal officer or other`
  line `municipal employee shall be liable to have his increments or promotion withheld or to be censured,`
  line `reduced in rank, compulsorily retired, removed or dismissed for any breach of any departmental`
  line `regulations or of discipline or for carelessness, unfitness, neglect of duty or other misconduct by such`
  line `authority as may be prescribed by regulation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such officer or other employee as aforesaid shall be reduced in rank, compulsorily`
  line `retired, removed or dismissed by an authority subordinate to that by which he was appointed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Council may by regulations provide that municipal employees belonging to`
  line `such classes or categories as may be specified in the regulations shall be liable also to be fined by such`
  line `authority as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `(2) No such officer or other employee shall be punished under sub-section (1) unless he has been`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the action proposed to be taken in regard to him:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply--`
  line
  line `(a) where an officer or other employee is removed or dismissed on the ground of conduct which`
  line `had led to his conviction on a criminal charge; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the authority empowered to remove or dismiss such officer or other employee is`
  line `satisfied that for some reason, to be recorded by that authority, it is not reasonably practicable to give`
  line `that person an opportunity of showing cause.`
  line
  line `(3) If any question arises whether it is not reasonably practicable to give any officer or other`
  line `employee an opportunity of showing cause under sub-section (2), the decision thereon of the authority`
  line `empowered to remove or dismiss such officer or other employee shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) An officer or other employee upon whom a punishment has been inflicted under this section may`
  line `appeal to such officer or authority as may be prescribed by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an officer or other employee appointed by the Chairperson, an appeal`
  line `shall lie to the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (48435)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Consultation with the Union Public Service Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48435&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No appointment to any category A`
  line `post within the meaning of clause (i) of sub-section (4) of section 34 shall be made except after`
  line `consultation with the Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such consultation with the Commission shall be necessary in regard to the selection`
  line `for appointment--`
  line
  line `(a) to any acting or temporary post for a period not exceeding one year; or`
  line
  line `(b) to such ministerial posts as may from time to time be specified by the Council in consultation`
  line `with the Commission when such posts are to be filled by promotion; or`
  line
  line `(c) to a post when at the time of such appointment the person to be appointed thereto is in the`
  line `service of the Central Government or a State Government in a Group A post;`
  line
  line `(d) to a permanent or temporary post, if the officer or other employee to be appointed is not likely`
  line `to hold that post for more than one year; or if such officer or other employee is likely to hold the post`
  line `for more than one year but not more than three years and the Commission advises that the`
  line `appointment may be made without consulting the Commission; or`
  line
  line `(e) to such other posts, as may, from time to time, be specified by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (48819)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of Commission to make regulations and reference to the Central Government in case of difference between the Commission and the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48819&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission may make regulations`
  line `for the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed by the Commission in advertising posts, inviting applications,`
  line `scrutinising the same and selecting candidates for interview;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by the Commission for selecting candidates for appointment and`
  line `by the Council for consultation with the Commission;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is incidental to, or necessary for, the purpose of consultation with the`
  line Commission.
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any difference of opinion between the Commission and the Council on any matter,`
  line `the Council shall refer the matter to the Central Government and the decision of that Government thereon`
  line `shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (48437)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Recruitment to category B and category C posts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48437&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The direct recruitment to category B and`
  line `category C posts may be made by the Government through such agencies as may be prescribed for it.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (48438)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power of Council to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48438&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may make regulations to provide for`
  line `any one or more of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the tenure of office, salaries and allowances, provident funds, pensions, gratuities, leave of`
  line `absence and other conditions of service of officers and other employees appointed under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers, duties and functions of Secretary;`
  line
  line `(c) the qualifications of candidates for appointment to posts specified in section 33 and to posts`
  line `dealt with in the Schedule of posts referred to in sub-section (1) of section 34 and the manner of`
  line `selection for appointments to such posts;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure to be followed in imposing any penalty under sub-section (1) of section 39,`
  line `suspension pending departmental inquiries before the imposition of such penalty and the authority by`
  line `whom such suspension may be ordered; the officer or authority to whom an appeal shall lie under`
  line `sub-section (4) of that section;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is incidental to or necessary for, the purpose of regulating the`
  line `appointment and conditions of service of persons appointed to services and posts under the Council`
  line `and any other matter for which in the opinion of the Council provisions should be made by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(2) No regulation under clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be made except after consultation with the`
  line Commission.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (48439)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Constitution of the New Delhi Municipal Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48439&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) all funds which immediately before the establishment of the Council vested in the New Delhi`
  line `Municipal Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) all moneys received by or on behalf of the Council under the provisions of this Act or of any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, or under any contract;`
  line
  line `(c) all proceeds of the disposal of property by, or on behalf of, the Council;`
  line
  line `(d) all rents accruing from any property of the Council;`
  line
  line `(e) all moneys raised by any tax, rate or cess levied for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) all fees collected and all fines levied under this Act or under any rule, regulation or bye-law`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(g) all moneys received by or on behalf of the Council from the Government or Central`
  line `Government or any individual or association of individuals by way of grant or gift or deposit;`
  line
  line `(h) all interests and profits arising from any investment of, or from any transaction in connection`
  line `with, any money belonging to the Council, including loans advanced under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(i) all moneys received by or on behalf of the Council from any other source whatsoever,`
  line
  line `shall form one Fund to be entitled "the Municipal Fund of New Delhi" (hereafter in this Act referred to as`
  line `"the New Delhi Municipal Fund").`
  line
  line `(2) The New Delhi Municipal Fund shall be held by the Council in trust for the purposes of this Act`
  line `subject to the provisions herein contained and a General Account relating to all moneys received by or on`
  line `behalf of the Council shall be maintained.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (48440)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `New Delhi Municipal Fund to be kept in the State Bank of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48440&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `All moneys payable to the`
  line `credit of the New Delhi Municipal Fund in the General Account shall be received by the Chairperson and`
  line `shall be forthwith paid into the State Bank of India to the credit of the said Account which shall be`
  line `entitled “The General Account of the New Delhi Municipal Fund”.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (48441)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Operation of the Accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48441&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act no payment shall be`
  line `made by the State Bank of India out of the New Delhi Municipal Fund except on a cheque signed by`
  line both--
  line
  line `(a) the Financial Adviser or an officer subordinate to him authorised by the Chairperson in this`
  line `behalf; and`
  line
  line `(b) the Chairperson or the Secretary or an officer subordinate to the Chairperson authorised by`
  line `him in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Payment of any sum due by the Council in excess of five hundred rupees shall be made by means`
  line `of a cheque signed in accordance with sub-section (1) and not in any other way.`
  line
  line `(3) Payments not covered by sub-section (2) may be made in cash.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (48442)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Payments not to be made unless covered by a budget-grant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48442&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `No payment of any sum out of`
  line `the New Delhi Municipal Fund shall be made unless the expenditure of the same is covered by a current`
  line `budget-grant and a sufficient balance of such budget-grant is still available notwithstanding any reduction`
  line `or transfer thereof which may have been made under the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that this section shall not apply to payments made in the following classes of cases,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) refund of taxes and other moneys which are authorised under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) repayment of moneys belonging to contractors or other persons and held in deposit and of`
  line `moneys collected or credited to the New Delhi Municipal Fund by mistake;`
  line
  line `(c) sums payable in any of the following circumstances--`
  line
  line `(i) under orders of the Central Government on failure of the Council to take any action as`
  line `required by that Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) under any other enactment for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(iii) under the decree or order of a civil or criminal court passed against the Council; or`
  line
  line `(iv) under a compromise of any claim, suit or other legal proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(v) on account of cost incurred in taking immediate action by the Chairperson under`
  line `clause (c) of section 18 to avert a sudden threat of danger to the property of the Council or to`
  line `human life;`
  line
  line `(d) temporary payments for works urgently required by the Central Government in the public`
  line interest;
  line
  line `(e) sums payable as compensation under this Act or under any rules, regulations or bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(f) expenses incurred under section 287 by the Chairperson on special measures taken on the`
  line `outbreak of dangerous diseases.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (48443)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Duty of persons signing cheques.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48443&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Before any person signs a cheque in accordance with`
  line `section 46, he shall satisfy himself that the sum for which the cheque is drawn is either--`
  line
  line `(a) required for a purpose or work specifically sanctioned by the proper authority and covered by`
  line `a current budget-grant, or`
  line
  line `(b) required for any payment referred to or specified in section 47.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (48444)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Procedure when money not covered by a budget-grant is expended.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48444&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any sum is`
  line `expended under clauses (c), (e) or (f) of the proviso to section 47, the Chairperson shall forthwith`
  line `communicate the circumstances to the Council, which may take such action under the provisions of this`
  line `Act as shall, in the circumstances appear possible and expedient for covering the amount of the additional`
  line expenditure.
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (48445)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Application of New Delhi Municipal Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48445&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The moneys from time to time credited to the`
  line `New Delhi Municipal Fund shall be applied in payment of all sums, charges and costs necessary for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act, and of the rules, regulations and bye-laws made thereunder, or of`
  line `which payment is duly directed, sanctioned or required by or under any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Such moneys shall likewise be applied in payment of all sums payable out of the New Delhi`
  line `Municipal Fund under any other enactment for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (48817)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Temporary payments from the New Delhi Municipal Fund for works urgently required for the public service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48817&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the written requisition of a Secretary to the Central Government, the`
  line `Chairperson may at any time undertake the execution of any work certified by such Secretary to be`
  line `urgently required in public interest, and for this purpose may temporarily make payments from the New`
  line `Delhi Municipal Fund so far as the same can be met without unduly interfering with the regular work of`
  line `the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The cost of work so executed and of the establishment engaged in executing the same shall be`
  line `paid by the Central Government and credited to the New Delhi Municipal Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) On the receipt of any requisition under sub-section (1) the Chairperson shall forthwith forward a`
  line `copy thereof to the Council together with a report of the steps taken by him in pursuance of the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (48447)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Investment of surplus moneys.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48447&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Surplus money standing at the credit of General Account of`
  line `the New Delhi Municipal Fund which cannot immediately be applied for the purposes specified in`
  line `section 50 shall be deposited in the State Bank of India or in such scheduled bank or banks as the Council`
  line `may select or be invested in public securities`
  line
  line `(2) The loss, if any, arising from such deposit or investment shall be debited to the General Account`
  line `of the New Delhi Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (48448)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Constitution of Finance Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48448&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the commencement of this Act the Finance`
  line `Commission referred to in sub-section (1) of section 107A of the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957`
  line `(66 of 1957), shall review the financial position of the Council and make recommendations to the`
  line `Administrator as to,--`
  line
  line `(a) the principles which should govern,--`
  line
  line `(i) the distribution between the National Capital Territory of Delhi and the Council of the net`
  line `proceeds of the taxes, duties, tolls and fees leviable by the National Capital Territory of Delhi`
  line `which may be divided between them;`
  line
  line `(ii) the determination of the taxes, duties, tolls and fees which may be assigned to or`
  line `appropriated by, the Council;`
  line
  line `(iii) the grants-in-aid to the Council from the Consolidated Fund of the National Capital`
  line `Territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b) the measures needed to improve the financial position of the Council,`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter referred to the Finance Commission by the Administrator in the interest of`
  line `sound finance of the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator shall cause every recommendation made by the Commission under this section`
  line `together within an explanatory memorandum as to the action taken thereon to be laid before the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the National Capital Territory of Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (48449)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Constitution of special funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48449&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall constitute such special fund or funds as`
  line `may be prescribed by regulations and such other funds necessary for the purposes of this Act as may be so`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The constitution and disposal of such funds shall be effected in the manner laid down by`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (48450)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Adoption of budget estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48450&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall, on or before the 31st day of March of`
  line `every year, adopt for the ensuing year the budget estimate which shall be an estimate of the income and`
  line `expenditure of the Council to be received and incurred on account of the municipal government of New`
  line Delhi.
  line
  line `(2) On or before the 15th day of February of each year the Council shall determine the rates at which`
  line `various municipal taxes, rates and cesses shall be levied in the next following year and save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act the rates so fixed shall not be subsequently altered for the year for which they have`
  line `been fixed.`
  line
  line `(3) Budget estimates shall be prepared in such form as may be approved by the Council and presented`
  line `and adopted in such manner and shall provide for all such matters as are prescribed by regulations made`
  line `in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (48451)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power of Council to alter budget estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48451&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the recommendation of the Chairperson in`
  line `respect of the budget estimate, the Council may from time to time, during the year,`
  line
  line `(i) increase the amount of budget-grant under any head;`
  line
  line `(ii) make additional budget-grant for the purpose of meeting any special or unforeseen`
  line `requirement arising during the said year;`
  line
  line `(iii) transfer the amount or portion of the amount of the budget-grant under any head to any other`
  line `head; or`
  line
  line `(iv) reduce the amount of the budget-grant under any head:`
  line
  line `Provided that due regard shall be had to all the requirements of this Act and in making any increase or`
  line `any additional budget-grant, the estimated cash balance at the close of the year shall not be reduced below`
  line `the sum of one lakh rupees or such higher sum as the Council may determine in respect of the budget`
  line estimate.
  line
  line `(2) Every increase in a budget-grant and every additional budget-grant made in any year under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be included in the budget estimates finally adopted for that year.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council may from time to time during the year--`
  line
  line `(a) reduce the amount of a budget-grant; or`
  line
  line `(b) sanction the transfer of any amount within a budget-grant.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson may from time to time during the year sanction the transfer of any amount not`
  line `exceeding ten thousand rupees within a minor head if such transfer does not involve a recurring liability:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such transfer if it exceeds ten thousand rupees shall be reported forthwith by the`
  line `Chairperson to the Council and the Chairperson shall give effect to any order that may be passed by the`
  line `Council in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (48452)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power of Council to re-adjust income and expenditure during the year.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48452&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time`
  line `during the year it appears to the Council that, notwithstanding any reduction of budget-grant that has been`
  line `made under section 56 the income of the New Delhi Municipal Fund during the same year will not suffice`
  line `to meet the expenditure sanctioned in the budget estimates of that year and to leave at the close of the year`
  line `the cash balance specified in or determined under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 56, then, it`
  line `shall be incumbent on the Council to sanction forthwith any measures which it may consider necessary`
  line `for adjusting the years income to the expenditure.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Council may either diminish the sanctioned expenditure of`
  line `the year so far as it may be possible so to do with regard to all the requirements of this Act, or have`
  line `recourse to supplementary taxation under section 97 or to an increase of the rates of cesses, fees, fares and`
  line `other charges leviable under this Act, or to adopt all or any of these methods.`
  line
  line `(3) If the whole or any part of any budget-grant included in the budget estimates for a year remains`
  line `unexpended at the close of that year, and the amount thereof has not been taken into account in the`
  line `opening balance entered in the budget estimates of any of the next two following years, the Chairperson`
  line `may sanction the expenditure of such budget-grant or the unexpended portion thereof during the next two`
  line `following years for the completion of the purpose or object for which the budget-grant was originally`
  line `made and not for any other purpose or object.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (48453)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Accounts to be kept.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48453&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `These shall be kept in such manner and in such form as may be prescribed`
  line `by regulations the General Account of all receipts and expenditures of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (48454)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48454&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Auditor shall conduct a monthly examination and audit of the accounts of`
  line `the Council and shall report thereon to the Chairperson, who shall publish monthly an abstract of the`
  line `receipts and expenditure of the month last proceeding signed by him and by the Chief Auditor.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may also, from time to time and for such period, as he may think fit, conduct`
  line `independently any examination and audit of the accounts of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of examination and audit of the accounts of the Council, the Chief Auditor shall`
  line `have access to all the accounts of the Council and to all records and correspondence relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Auditor shall audit the accounts of the Council with the assistance of the officers and`
  line `other employees subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(5) In the discharge of his functions under this section the Chief Auditor shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) audit the accounts of expenditure from the revenue of the Council, expenditure on account of`
  line `loan works and expenditure incurred out of special funds and shall ascertain whether moneys shown`
  line `therein as have been disbursed were legally available for, and applicable to, the service or purpose to`
  line `which they have been applied or charged, and whether the expenditure conforms to the authority`
  line `which governs it;`
  line
  line `(b) audit the accounts of debts, deposits, sinking funds, advances, suspense and remittance`
  line `transactions of the Council and report upon those accounts and upon the results of verification of the`
  line `balance relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chief Auditor shall examine and audit the statement of accounts relating to the commercial`
  line `services conducted in any department of the Council including the trading, manufacturing and profit and`
  line `loss accounts, and the balance-sheets where such accounts are maintained under the orders of the Council`
  line `and shall certify and report upon these accounts.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chief Auditor shall in consultation with the Chairperson and subject to any directions given`
  line `by the Council determine the form and manner in which his reports on the accounts of the Council shall`
  line `be prepared and shall have authority to call upon any officer of the Council to provide any information`
  line `necessary for the preparation of these reports.`
  line
  line `(8) The Chief Auditor may make such queries and observations in relation to any of the accounts of`
  line `the Council which he is required to audit and call for such vouchers, statements, returns and explanation`
  line `in relation to such accounts as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(9) Every such query or observation as aforesaid shall be promptly taken into consideration by the`
  line `officer or authority to whom it may be addressed and returned without delay with the necessary vouchers,`
  line `documents or explanations to the Chief Auditor.`
  line
  line `(10) The power of the Chief Auditor with regard to the disapproval of, and the procedure with regard`
  line `to the settlement of objections to expenditure from the revenues of the Council shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Chairperson in Consultation with Chief Auditor, and with the approval of the Council.`
  line
  line `(11) If the Chief Auditor considers it desirable that the whole or any part of the audit applied to any`
  line `accounts which he is required to audit shall be conducted in the offices in which those accounts originate`
  line `he may require that those accounts, together with all books and documents having relation thereto, shall at`
  line `all convenient times be made available in the said offices for inspection.`
  line
  line `(12) The Chief Auditor shall have the power to require that any books or other documents relating to`
  line `the accounts he is required to audit shall be sent for inspection by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the documents are confidential, he shall be responsible for preventing disclosure of`
  line `their contents.`
  line
  line `(13) The Chief Auditor shall have authority to frame standing orders and to give directions on all`
  line `matters relating to audit, and particularly, in respect of the method and the extent of audit to be applied`
  line `and the raising and pursuing the objections.`
  line
  line `(14) Expenditure sanctioned by the Chief Auditor shall be audited by an officer to be nominated by`
  line `the Council.`
  line
  line `(15) The Chief Auditor shall report to the Chairperson any material impropriety or irregularity which`
  line `he may at any time observe in the expenditure or in the recovery of moneys due to the Council or in the`
  line `accounts of the Council.`
  line
  line `(16) The Chairperson shall cause to be laid before the Council every report made by the Chief`
  line `Auditor to the Chairperson and every statement of the views of the Chief Auditor on any matter affecting`
  line `the exercise and performance of the powers and duties assigned to him under this Act and the Council`
  line `may take such action in regard to any of the matters as aforesaid as the Council may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(17) As soon as may be after the commencement of each year, the Chief Auditor shall deliver to the`
  line `Council a report of the entire accounts of the Council for the previous year.`
  line
  line `(18) The Chairperson shall cause the said report to be printed and shall forward as soon as may be`
  line `printed copy thereof to each member of the Council.`
  line
  line `(19) The Chairperson shall also forward without delay to the Government so many copies of the said`
  line `report, as may be required by the Government with a brief statement of the action taken or proposed to be`
  line `taken if any:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may at any time appoint auditor for the purpose of making a special`
  line `audit of the General Account of the New Delhi Municipal Fund and reporting thereon to the Government`
  line `and the costs of such audit, as determined by the Government, shall be chargeable to the New Delhi`
  line `Municipal Fund. The auditor so appointed may exercise any power which the Chief Auditor may`
  line exercise.
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (48455)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Taxes to be imposed by the Council under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48455&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, levy the following taxes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) property tax;`
  line
  line `(b) a tax on vehicles and animals;`
  line
  line `(c) a theatre-tax;`
  line
  line `(d) a tax on advertisements other than advertisements published in the newspapers;`
  line
  line `(e) a duty on the transfer of property; and`
  line
  line `(f) a tax on buildings payable along with the application for sanction of the building plan.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the taxes specified in sub-section (1) the Council may, for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `levy any of the following taxes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) an education cess;`
  line
  line `(b) a tax on professions, trades, callings and employments;`
  line
  line `(c) a tax on the consumption, sale or supply of electricity;`
  line
  line `(d) a betterment tax on the increase in urban land values caused by the execution of any`
  line `development or improvement work;`
  line
  line `(e) tolls.`
  line
  line `(3) The taxes specified in sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) shall be levied, assessed and collected in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act and the bye-laws made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (48456)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Rates of property tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48456&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the property tax shall be`
  line `levied on lands and buildings in New Delhi and shall consist of not less than ten and not more than thirty`
  line `per cent. of the rateable value of lands and buildings:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council may, when fixing the rate at which the property tax shall be levied during`
  line `any year, determine that the rate leviable in respect of lands and buildings or portions of lands and`
  line `buildings in which any particular class of trade or business is carried on shall be higher than the rate`
  line `determined in respect of other lands and buildings or portions of other lands and buildings by an amount`
  line `not exceeding one-half of the rate so fixed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the tax may be levied on graduated scale, if the Council so determines.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where any portion of a land or building is liable to a higher rate of the tax such`
  line `portion shall be deemed to be a separate property for the purpose of municipal taxation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may exempt from the tax lands and buildings of which the rateable value does not`
  line `exceed one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (48457)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Premises in respect of which property tax is to be levied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48457&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `this Act, the property tax shall be levied in respect of all lands and buildings in New Delhi except--`
  line
  line `(a) lands and buildings or portions of lands and buildings exclusively occupied and used for`
  line `public worship or by a society or body for a charitable purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that such society or body is supported wholly or in part by voluntary contributions,`
  line `applies its profits, if any, or other income in promoting its objects and does not pay any dividend or`
  line `bonus to its members.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- "Charitable purpose" includes relief of the poor, education and medical relief but`
  line `does not include a purpose which relates exclusively to religious teaching;`
  line
  line `(b) lands and buildings vested in the Council, in respect of which the said tax, if levied, would`
  line `under the provisions of this Act be leviable primarily on the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) agricultural lands and buildings (other than dwelling houses).`
  line
  line `(2) Lands and buildings or portions thereof shall not be deemed to be exclusively occupied and used`
  line `for public worship or for a charitable purpose within the meaning of clause (a) of sub-section (1) if any`
  line `trade or business is carried on in such lands and buildings or portions thereof or if in respect of such lands`
  line `and buildings or portions thereof, any rent is derived.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any portion of any land or building is exempt from the property tax by reason of its being`
  line `exclusively occupied and used for public worship or for a charitable purpose such portion shall be deemed`
  line `to be a separate property for the purpose of municipal taxation.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (48458)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Determination of rateable value of lands and buildings assessable to property tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48458&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `rateable value of any lands or building assessable to any property taxes shall be the annual rent at which`
  line `such land or building might reasonably be expected to let from year to year less a sum equal to`
  line `ten per cent. of the said annual rent which shall be in lieu of all allowances for cost of repairs and`
  line `insurance, and other expenses, if any, necessary to maintain the land or building in a state to command`
  line `that rent:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of any land or building the standard rent of which has been fixed under the`
  line `Delhi Rent Control Act, 1958 (59 of 1958) the rateable value thereof shall not exceed the annual amount`
  line `of the standard rent so fixed.`
  line
  line `(2) The rateable value of any land which is not built upon but is capable of being built upon and of`
  line `any land on which a building is in process of erection shall be fixed at five per cent. of estimated capital`
  line `value of such land.`
  line
  line `(3) All plant and machinery contained or situate in or upon any land or building and belonging to any`
  line `of the classes specified from time to time by public notice by the Chairperson with the approval of the`
  line `Council, shall be deemed to form part of such land or building for the purpose of determining the rateable`
  line `value thereof under sub-section (1) but save as aforesaid no account shall be taken of the value of any`
  line `plant or machinery contained or situated in or upon any such land or building.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (48459)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Charge for supply of water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48459&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) A charge shall be levied for the water supplied to any land or`
  line `building by measurement at such rate as shall from time to time be prescribed by the Council in this`
  line behalf.
  line
  line `(2) The Council may prescribe such conditions as it may think fit regarding the use of the water and`
  line `regarding the charges to be paid for water consumed whilst a meter is out of order or under repair:`
  line
  line `Provided that no condition prescribed under this sub-section shall be inconsistent with this Act or`
  line `with any bye-law made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) Any sum payable by a person, who is charged for water supplied, and not paid when it becomes`
  line `due shall be recoverable as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) In prescribing charges for water supplied by measurement under sub-section (1), it shall be lawful`
  line `for the Council to prescribe different rates in respect of different classes of lands and buildings.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (48460)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Taxation of Union properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48460&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, lands and buildings being properties of the Union shall be exempt from the`
  line `property tax specified in section 61:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall prevent the Council from levying property tax on such`
  line `lands and buildings to which immediately before the 26th January, 1950, they were liable or treated as`
  line `liable, so long as that tax continues to be levied by the Council on other lands and buildings.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the possession of any land or building, being property of the Union, has been delivered in`
  line `pursuance of section 20 of the Displaced Persons (Compensation and Rehabilitation) Act, 1954`
  line `(44 of 1954) to a displaced person, or any association of displaced persons, whether incorporated or not,`
  line `or to any other person [hereafter in this sub-section and the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 66`
  line `referred to as the transferee], the property tax specified in section 61 shall be leviable and shall be deemed`
  line `to have been leviable in respect of such land or building with effect from the 7th day of April, 1958 or the`
  line `date on which possession thereof has been delivered to the transferee, whichever is later, and such`
  line `property tax shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, be recoverable`
  line `with effect from that day or date, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (48461)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Incidence of property tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48461&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) The property tax shall be primarily leviable as follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the land or building is let, upon the lessor;`
  line
  line `(b) if the land or building is sub-let, upon the superior lessor;`
  line
  line `(c) if the land or building is unlet, upon the person in whom the right to let the same vests:`
  line
  line `Provided that the property tax in respect of land and building, being property of the Union, possession`
  line `of which has been delivered in pursuance of section 20 of the Displaced Persons (Compensation and`
  line `Rehabilitation) Act, 1954 (44 of 1954) shall be primarily leviable upon the transferee.`
  line
  line `(2) If any land has been let for a term exceeding one year to a tenant and such tenant has built upon`
  line `the land, the property tax assessed in respect of that land and the building erected thereon shall be`
  line `primarily leviable upon the said tenant, whether the land and building are in the occupation of such tenant`
  line `or a sub-tenant of such tenant.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The term "tenant" includes any person deriving title to the land or the building erected`
  line `upon such land from the tenant whether by operation of law or by transfer inter vivos.`
  line
  line `(3) The liability of the several owners of any buildings which is, or purports to be, severally owned in`
  line `parts or flats or rooms, for payment of property tax or any instalment thereof payable during the period of`
  line `such ownership shall be joint and several.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (48462)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Apportionment of liability for property tax when the premises are let or sub-let.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48462&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any`
  line `land or building assessed to property tax is let, and its rateable value exceeds the amount of rent payable`
  line `in respect thereof to the person upon whom under the provision of section 66 the said tax is leviable, that`
  line `person shall be entitled to receive from his tenant the difference between the amount of the property tax`
  line `levied upon him and the amount which would be leviable upon him if the said tax was calculated on the`
  line `amount of rent payable to him.`
  line
  line `(2) If the land or building is sub-let and its rateable value exceeds the amount of rent payable in`
  line `respect thereof to the tenant by his sub-tenant, or the amount of rent payable in respect thereof to a`
  line `sub-tenant by the person holding under the sub-tenant, the tenant shall be entitled to receive from his`
  line `sub-tenant or the sub-tenant shall be entitled to receive from the person holding under him, as the case`
  line `may be, the difference between any sum recovered under this section from such tenant or sub-tenant and`
  line `the amount of property tax which would be liable in respect of the said land or building if the rateable`
  line `value thereof were equal to the difference between the amount of rent which such tenant or sub-tenant`
  line `receives and the amount of rent which he pays.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person entitled to receive any sum under this section shall have, for the recovery thereof, the`
  line `same rights and remedies as if such sum were rent payable to him by the person from whom he is entitled`
  line `to receive the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (48463)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Recovery of property tax from occupiers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48463&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the failure to recover any sum due on`
  line `account of property tax in respect of any land or building from the person primarily liable therefor under section 66, the Chairperson shall recover from every occupier of such land or building by attachment, in`
  line `accordance with section 108 of the rent payable by such occupier, a portion of the total sum due which`
  line `bears, as nearly as may be, the same proportion to that sum as the rent annually payable by such occupier`
  line `bears to the total amount of rent annually payable in respect of the whole of the land or building.`
  line
  line `(2) An occupier from whom any sum is recovered under sub-section (1) shall be entitled to be`
  line `reimbursed by the person primarily liable for the payment, and may in addition to having recourse to`
  line `other remedies that may be open to him, deduct the amount so recovered from the amount of any rent`
  line `from time to time becoming due from him to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (48464)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Property tax a first charge on premises on which it is assessed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48464&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Property tax due under this`
  line `Act in respect of any land or building shall, subject to the prior payment of the land revenue, if any, due to`
  line `the Council or Government or Central Government thereon, be a first charge--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any land or building held immediately from the Council or Government or`
  line `Central Government, upon the interest in such land or building of the person liable for such tax and`
  line `upon the goods and other movable properties, if any, found within or upon such land or building and`
  line `belonging to such person; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other land or building, upon such land or building and upon the goods and`
  line `other movable properties, if any, found within or upon such land or building and belonging to the`
  line `person liable for such tax.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The term "property tax" in this section shall be deemed to include the costs on`
  line `recovery of property tax and the penalty, if any, payable as specified in the bye-laws.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (48465)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48465&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the Council shall cause an`
  line `assessment list of all lands and buildings in New Delhi to be prepared in such form and manner and`
  line `containing such particulars with respect to each land and building as may be prescribed by bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(2) When the assessment list has been prepared the Chairperson shall give public notice thereof and`
  line `of the place where the list or a copy thereof may be inspected, and every person claiming to be the owner,`
  line `lessee or occupier of any land or building included in the list and any authorised agent of such person,`
  line `shall be at liberty to inspect the list and to take extracts therefrom free of charge.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall, at the same time, give public notice of a date, not less than one month`
  line `thereafter, when he will proceed to consider the rateable values of lands and buildings entered in the`
  line `assessment list; and in all cases in which any land or building is for the first time assessed, or the rateable`
  line `value of any land or building is increased, he shall also give written notice thereof to the owner or to any`
  line `lessee or occupier of the land or building.`
  line
  line `(4) Any objection to a rateable value or any other matter as entered in the assessment list shall be`
  line `made in writing to the Chairperson before the date fixed in the notice and shall state in what respect the`
  line `rateable value, or other matter is disputed, and all objections so made shall be recorded in a register to be`
  line `kept for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(5) The objections shall be inquired into and investigated, and the persons making them shall be`
  line `allowed an opportunity of being heard either in person or by authorised agent, by the Chairperson or by`
  line `any officer of the Council authorised in this behalf by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(6) When all objections have been disposed of, and the revision of the rateable value has been`
  line `completed, the assessment list shall be authenticated by signature of the Chairperson or, as the case may`
  line `be, the officer authorised by him in this behalf, who shall certify that except in the case, if any in which`
  line `amendments have been made as shown therein, no valid objection has been made to the rateable value or`
  line `any other matter entered in said list.`
  line
  line `(7) The assessment list so authenticated shall be deposited in the office of the Council and shall be`
  line `open, free of charge during office hours to all owners, lessees and occupiers of lands and buildings`
  line `comprised therein or the authorised agents of such persons, and a public notice that it is so open shall`
  line `forthwith be published.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (48466)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Evidential value of assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48466&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such alterations as may thereafter be made in`
  line `the assessment list under section 72 and to the result of any appeal made under the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the entries in the assessment list authenticated and deposited as provided in section 70 shall be accepted`
  line `as conclusive evidence for the purpose of assessing any tax levied under this Act, of the rateable value of`
  line `all lands and buildings to which such entries respectively relate.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (48467)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Amendment of assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48467&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may, at any time, amend the assessment`
  line list--
  line
  line `(a) by inserting therein the name of any person whose name ought to be inserted; or`
  line
  line `(b) by inserting therein any land or building previously omitted; or`
  line
  line `(c) by striking out the name of any person not liable for the payment of property tax; or`
  line
  line `(d) by increasing or reducing for adequate reasons the amount of any rateable value and of the`
  line `assessment thereupon; or`
  line
  line `(e) by making or cancelling any entry exempting any land or building from liability to property`
  line `tax; or`
  line
  line `(f) by altering the assessment on the land or building which has been erroneously valued or`
  line `assessed through fraud, mistake or accident; or`
  line
  line `(g) by inserting or altering an entry in respect of any building erected, re-erected, altered or added`
  line `to, after the preparation of the assessment list:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall by reason of any such amendment become liable to pay any tax or`
  line `increase of tax in respect of any period prior to the commencement of the year in which the notice under`
  line `sub-section (2) is given.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making any amendment under sub-section (1) the Chairperson shall give to any person`
  line `affected by the amendment, notice of not less than one month that he proposes to make the amendment`
  line `and consider any objection which may be made by such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (48468)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Preparation of new assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48468&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `It shall be in the discretion of the Chairperson to prepare`
  line `for the whole or any part of New Delhi, a new assessment list every year or to adopt the rateable value`
  line `contained in the list for any year, with such alterations as may in particular cases be deemed necessary, as`
  line `the rateable value for the year following, giving the same public notice as well as individual notices, to`
  line `persons affected by such alterations, of the rateable value as if a new assessment list had been prepared.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (48469)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Notice of transfers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48469&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the title of any person primarily liable for the payment of`
  line `property tax on any land or building is transferred, the person whose title is transferred and the person to`
  line `whom the same is transferred shall within three months after the execution of the instrument of transfer or`
  line `after registration, if it is registered, or after the transfer is effected, if no instrument is executed, give`
  line `notice of such transfer in writing to the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of the death of any person primarily liable as aforesaid, the person on whom the title`
  line `of the deceased devolves, shall give notice of such devolution to the Chairperson within six months from`
  line `the date of the death of the deceased.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice to be given under this section shall be in such form as may be determined by bye-laws`
  line `made under this Act, and the transferee or the other person on whom the title devolves shall, if so`
  line `required, be bound to produce before the Chairperson any document evidencing the transfer or`
  line devolution.
  line
  line `(4) Every person who makes a transfer as aforesaid without giving such notice to the Chairperson`
  line `shall, in addition to any penalty to which he may be subjected under the provisions of this Act, continue`
  line `to be liable for the payment of property tax from time to time payable in respect of the land or building`
  line `transferred until he gives such notice or until the transfer has been recorded in the Chairperson's book, but`
  line `nothing in this section shall be held to affect the liability of the transferee for the payment of the said tax.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson shall record every transfer or devolution of title notified to him under this section`
  line `in his books and in the assessment list.`
  line
  line `(6) On a written request by the Chairperson, the registrar or sub-registrar of New Delhi appointed`
  line `under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), shall furnish such particulars regarding the registration of instruments of transfer of immovable properties in New Delhi, as the Chairperson may from time to time`
  line require.
  line
  line `(7) Such information shall be furnished as soon as may be after the registration of an instrument of`
  line `transfer is effected or, if the Chairperson so requests, by periodical returns at such intervals as the`
  line `Chairperson may fix.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (48470)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Notice of erection of building, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48470&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `When any new building is erected or when any building is`
  line `rebuilt or enlarged or when any building which has been vacant is reoccupied, the person primarily liable`
  line `for the property tax assessed on the building shall give notice thereof in writing to the Chairperson within`
  line `fifteen days from the date of its completion or occupation whichever first occurs, or as the case may be,`
  line `from the date of its enlargement or reoccupation; and property tax shall be assessable on the building`
  line `from the said date.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (48471)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Notice of demolition or removal of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48471&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any building or any portion of a`
  line `building, which is liable to the payment of property tax is demolished or removed, otherwise than by`
  line `order of the Chairperson, the person primarily liable for the payment of the said tax shall give notice`
  line `thereof in writing to the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) Until such notice is given, the person aforesaid shall continue to be liable to the payment of such`
  line `property tax as he would have been liable to pay in respect of such building if the same or any portion`
  line `thereof had not been demolished or removed.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (48472)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Power of Chairperson to call for information and returns and to enter and inspect premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48472&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) To enable him to determine the rateable value of any land or building and the person`
  line `primarily liable for the payment of property tax leviable in respect thereof, the Chairperson may require`
  line `the owner or occupier of such land or building, or of any portion thereof to furnish him within such`
  line `reasonable period as the Chairperson fixes in this behalf, with information or with a written return signed`
  line `by such owner or occupier--`
  line
  line `(a) as to the name and place of residence of the owner or occupier, or of both the owner and`
  line `occupier of such land or buildings;`
  line
  line `(b) as to the measurements or dimensions of such land or building or of any portion thereof and`
  line `the rent, if any, obtained for such land or building or any portion thereof; and`
  line
  line `(c) as to the actual cost or other specified details connected with the determination of the value of`
  line `such land or building.`
  line
  line `(2) Every owner or occupier on whom any such requisition is made shall be bound to comply with the`
  line `same and to give true information or to make a true return to the best of his knowledge or belief.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever omits to comply with any such requisition or fails to give true information or to make a`
  line `true return to the best of his knowledge or belief, shall, in addition to any penalty to which he may be`
  line `liable, be precluded from objecting to any assessment made by the Chairperson in respect of such land or`
  line `building of which he is the owner or occupier.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (48820)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Premises owned by, or let to two or more persons in severalty to be ordinarily assessed as one property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48820&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that any land or building is owned by, or let to, two or more persons in`
  line `severalty, the Chairperson shall for the purpose of assessing such land or building to property tax treat the`
  line `whole of it as one property:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson may, in respect of any land or building which was originally treated as`
  line `one property but which subsequently passes on by transfer, succession or in any other manner to two or`
  line `more persons who divide the same into several parts and occupy them in severalty, treat, subject to any`
  line `bye-law made in this behalf, each such several part, or two or more of such several parts together, as a`
  line `separate property and assess such part or parts to property tax accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (48474)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Assessment in case of amalgamation of premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48474&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `If any land or building, bearing two or`
  line `more municipal numbers, or portions thereof, be amalgamated into one or more new premises, the`
  line `Chairperson shall on such amalgamation assign to them one or more number and assess them to property`
  line `tax accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total assessment on amalgamation shall not be greater than the sum of the previous`
  line `assessments of the several premises except when there is any re-valuation of any of the said premises.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (48475)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Power of Chairperson to assess separately outhouses and portions of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48475&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Chairperson may in his discretion assess any outhouse appurtenant to a building, or any portion of a land`
  line `or building separately from such building or as the case may be, from the rest of such land or building.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (48476)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Power of Chairperson to employ valuers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48476&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may, if he thinks fit, employ`
  line `one or more competent persons to give advice or assistance in connection with the valuation of any land`
  line `or building, and any person so employed shall have power, at all reasonable times and after giving due`
  line `notice, and on production, if so required, of authorisation in writing in that behalf from the Chairperson,`
  line `to enter on, survey and value any land or building which the Chairperson may direct him to survey and`
  line value.
  line
  line `(2) No person shall willfully delay or obstruct any such person in the exercise of any of his powers`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (48477)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Tax on certain vehicles and animals and rates thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48477&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this`
  line `Act, a tax at the rates not exceeding those specified in the Second Schedule shall be levied on vehicles`
  line `and animals of the descriptions specified in that Schedule which are kept within New Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (48478)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `The tax on whom leviable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48478&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `The tax on vehicles or animals shall be leviable upon the owner of,`
  line `or the person having possession or control of, such vehicles or animals in respect of which the tax is`
  line `leviable:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an animal generally used or employed in drawing any vehicle, the tax in`
  line `respect of such animal shall be leviable upon the owner of, or the person having possession or control of,`
  line `such vehicle, whether or not such animal is owned by such owner or person:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the tax under this section shall not be levied in respect of--`
  line
  line `(a) vehicles and animals belonging to the Central Government or to the Government or to the`
  line `Council used or intended to be used solely for public purposes;`
  line
  line `(b) vehicles intended exclusively for the conveyance free of charge, of the injured, the sick or the`
  line dead;
  line
  line `(c) children's perambulators or tricycles;`
  line
  line `(d) a cow or a she-buffalo kept for milking for domestic use if the cow or the she-buffalo is the`
  line `only cow or she-buffalo kept by the owner or the person having possession or control thereof for such`
  line `milking and is registered in accordance with bye-laws made in this behalf, so, however, that--`
  line
  line `(i) where more cows or, as the case may be, more she-buffaloes than one are kept by several`
  line `such owners or persons constituting a family, the tax under this section shall be levied in respect`
  line `of all such cows or all such she-buffaloes;`
  line
  line `(ii) where a cow and also a she-buffalo are kept by the owner or the person having the`
  line `possession or control thereof or by several such owners or persons constituting a family, the tax`
  line `under this section shall be levied in respect of the cow and the she-buffalo.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (48479)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Tax when payable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48479&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `The tax on vehicles or animals shall be payable in advance in such number`
  line `of instalments and in such manner as may be determined by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (48480)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power of Chairperson to compound with livery stable keeper, etc., for tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48480&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson`
  line `may with the approval of the Council, compound for any period not exceeding one year at a time, with`
  line `any livery stable keeper or other person keeping vehicles for hire or animals for sale or hire, for a lump`
  line `sum to be paid in respect of the vehicles or animals so kept in lieu of the taxes leviable under section 82`
  line `which such livery stable keeper or other person would otherwise be liable to pay.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (48481)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title Theatre-tax.
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48481&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, there shall be levied a tax (referred to in`
  line `this Act as theatre-tax) in respect of every cinema, theatre, circus, carnival and other place of`
  line `entertainment to which persons are ordinarily admitted on payment for performances or shows held or`
  line `conducted thereat, at such rates not exceeding those specified in the Third Schedule as the Council may`
  line `determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the theatre-tax shall not be levied in respect of any performance or show if the`
  line `Chairperson is satisfied--`
  line
  line `(a) that the entire receipts from such performance or show will be devoted to philanthropic,`
  line `religious or charitable purposes; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the performance or show is of a wholly educational character; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the performance or show is provided for partly educational or partly scientific purposes`
  line `by a society not conducted or established for profit.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (48482)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Liability to pay theatre-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48482&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `Every proprietor, manager, or person-in-charge of a theatre,`
  line `cinema, circus, carnival or other place of entertainment shall be liable to pay the theatre-tax and shall pay`
  line `the same in advance before the commencement of the performances or shows:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson may, with the approval of the Council, compound for any series of`
  line `performances or shows or for any period not exceeding one month, with such proprietor, manager or`
  line `person for a lump sum to be paid for such series of performances or shows or for the performances or`
  line `shows held or conducted during such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (48483)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Tax on advertisements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48483&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person, who erects, exhibits, fixes or retains upon or over`
  line `any land, building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or structure or upon or in any vehicle any advertisement or,`
  line `who displays any advertisement to public view in any manner whatsoever, visible from a public street or`
  line `public place (including any advertisement exhibited by means of cinematographs), shall pay for every`
  line `advertisement which is so erected, exhibited, fixed or retained or so displayed to public view, a tax`
  line `calculated at such rates not exceeding those specified in the Fourth Schedule as the Council may`
  line `determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that no tax shall be levied under this section on any advertisement which--`
  line
  line `(a) relates to a public meeting, or to an election to Parliament or the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Delhi; or`
  line
  line `(b) is exhibited within the window of any building if the advertisement relates to the trade,`
  line `profession or business carried on in that building; or`
  line
  line `(c) relates to the trade, profession or business carried on within the land or building upon or over`
  line `which such advertisement is exhibited or to any sale or letting of such land or building or any effects`
  line `therein or to any sale, entertainment or meeting to be held on or upon or in the same; or`
  line
  line `(d) relates to the name of the land or building upon or over which the advertisement is exhibited,`
  line `or to the name of the owner or occupier of such land or building; or`
  line
  line `(e) relates to the business of a railway administration and is exhibited within any railway station`
  line `or upon any wall or other property of a railway administration; or`
  line
  line `(f) relates to any activity of the Central Government or the Government or the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The tax on any advertisement leviable under this section shall be payable in advance in such`
  line `number of instalments and in such manner as may be determined by bye-law made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--The word "structure" in this section includes any movable board on wheels used as`
  line `an advertisement or an advertisement medium.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--The word "advertisement" in relation to a tax on advertisement under this Act means`
  line `any word, letter, model, sign, placard, notice, device or representation, whether illuminated or not, in the`
  line `nature of and employed wholly or in part for the purposes of advertisement, announcement or direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (48484)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Prohibition of advertisements without written permission of the Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48484&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `advertisement shall be erected, exhibited, fixed or retained upon or over any land, building, wall,`
  line `hoarding, frame, post or structure or upon or in any vehicle or shall be displayed in any manner`
  line `whatsoever in any place within New Delhi without the written permission of the Chairperson granted in`
  line `accordance with bye-laws made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall not grant such permission if--`
  line
  line `(a) the advertisement contravenes any bye-law made under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) the tax, if any, due in respect of the advertisement has not been paid.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), in the case of an advertisement liable to the`
  line `advertisement tax, the Chairperson shall grant permission for the period to which the payment of the tax`
  line `relates and no fee shall be charged in respect of such permission.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (48485)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Permission of the Chairperson to become void in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48485&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `The permission granted`
  line `under section 89 shall become void in the following cases, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the advertisement contravenes any bye-law made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) if any material change is made in the advertisement or any part thereof without the previous`
  line `permission of the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) if the advertisement or any part thereof falls otherwise than through accident;`
  line
  line `(d) if any addition or alteration is made to, or in the building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or`
  line `structure upon or over which the advertisement is erected, exhibited, fixed or retained if such addition`
  line `or alteration involves the disturbance of the advertisement or any part thereof; and`
  line
  line `(e) if the building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or structure over which the advertisement is`
  line `erected, exhibited, fixed or retained is demolished or destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (48486)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Presumption in case of contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48486&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `any advertisement has been erected, exhibited,`
  line `fixed or retained upon or over any land, building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or structure or upon or in`
  line `any vehicle or displayed to public view from a public street or public place in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any bye-laws made thereunder, it shall be presumed, unless and until contrary is`
  line `proved, that the contravention has been committed by the person or the persons on whose behalf the`
  line `advertisement purports to be or the agents of such person or persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (48487)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Power of Chairperson in case of contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48487&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `If any advertisement is erected, exhibited,`
  line `fixed or retained in contravention of the provisions of section 89, the Chairperson may require the owner`
  line `or occupier of the land, building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or structure or vehicle upon, or over or in`
  line `which the same is erected, exhibited, fixed or retained, to take down or remove such advertisement or`
  line `may enter any land, building, property or vehicle and have the advertisement dismantled, taken down or`
  line `removed or spoiled, defaced or screened.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (48488)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Duty on transfer of property and method of assessment thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48488&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act, the Council shall levy a duty on transfer of immovable property situated within the`
  line `limits of New Delhi in accordance with the provisions hereafter in this section contained.`
  line
  line `(2) The said duty shall be levied--`
  line
  line `(a) in the form of a surcharge on the duty imposed by the Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899), as in`
  line `force for the time being in the National Capital Territory of Delhi, on every instrument of the`
  line `description specified below, and`
  line
  line `(b) at such rate as may be determined by the Council not exceeding five per cent. on the amount`
  line `specified below against such instruments:`
  line
  line `Description of instrument Amount on which duty should be levied`
  line
  line `(i) Sale of immovable property. The amount of value of the consideration for`
  line `the sale, as set forth in the instrument.`
  line
  line `Description of instrument Amount on which duty should be levied`
  line
  line `(ii) Exchange of immovable property. The value of the property of the greater value,`
  line `as set forth in the instrument.`
  line
  line `(iii) Gift of immovable property. The value of the property as set forth in the`
  line instrument.
  line
  line `(iv) Mortgage with possession of immovable`
  line property.
  line
  line `The amount secured by the mortgage as set`
  line `forth in the instrument.`
  line
  line `(v) Lease in perpetuity of immovable property. The amount equal to one sixth of the whole`
  line `amount or value of the rent which would be`
  line `paid or delivered in respect of the first fifty`
  line `years of the lease as set forth in the instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (48489)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Provisions applicable on the introduction of transfer duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48489&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `On the introduction of the duty`
  line `on transfers of property--`
  line
  line `(a) section 27 of the Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899), as in force in the National Capital Territory of`
  line `Delhi shall be read as if it specifically required the particulars to be set forth separately in respect of`
  line `property situated within and without New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b) section 64 of the said Act shall be read as if it referred to the Council as well as the`
  line `Government of National Capital Territory of Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (48490)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Tax on building applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48490&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act the Council shall levy`
  line `a tax on buildings at such rates not exceeding those specified in the Fifth Schedule as the Council shall`
  line determine.
  line
  line `(2) The tax shall be leviable on every person who makes an application to the Chairperson for the`
  line `sanction of building plan and shall be payable along with the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (48491)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Imposition of other taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48491&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, at a meeting, pass a resolution for the levy of`
  line `any of the taxes specified in sub-section (2) of section 60, defining the maximum rate of the tax to be`
  line `levied, the class or classes of persons or the description or descriptions of articles and properties to be`
  line `taxed, the system of assessment to be adopted and the exemptions, if any, to be granted.`
  line
  line `(2) Any resolution passed under sub-section (1) shall be submitted to the Central Government for its`
  line `sanction, and if sanctioned by that Government, shall come into force on and from such date as may be`
  line `specified in the order of sanction.`
  line
  line `(3) After a resolution has come into force under sub-section (2), the Council may, subject to the`
  line `maximum rate, pass a second resolution determining the actual rates at which the tax shall be leviable and`
  line `the tax shall come into force on the first day of the quarter of the year next following the date on which`
  line `such second resolution is passed.`
  line
  line `(4) After a tax has been levied in accordance with foregoing provisions of this section, the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (2) of section 55, shall apply in relation to such tax as they apply in relation to any tax`
  line `imposed under sub-section (1) of section 60.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (48492)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Supplementary taxation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48492&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Council decides to have recourse to supplementary`
  line `taxation under sub-section (2) of section 57 in any year, it shall do so by increasing from such date as the`
  line `Council may determine, the rates at which any tax leviable under this Act is being levied, but every such increase shall be made subject to the maximum rate and any other limitation specified in respect of such`
  line tax.
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (48493)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Time and manner of payment of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48493&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, any tax levied`
  line `under this Act shall be payable on such dates, in such number of instalments and in such manner as may`
  line `be determined by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (48494)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Presentation of bill.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48494&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any tax has become due, the Chairperson shall cause to be`
  line `presented to the person liable for the payment thereof, a bill for the amount due:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such bill shall be necessary in the case of--`
  line
  line `(a) a tax on vehicles and animals;`
  line
  line `(b) a theatre-tax; and`
  line
  line `(c) a tax on advertisements.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such bill shall specify the particulars of the tax and the period for which the charge is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (48495)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Notice of demand and notice fee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48495&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the amount of the tax for which a bill has been`
  line `presented under section 99 is not paid within fifteen days from the presentation thereof, or if the tax on`
  line `vehicles and animals or the theatre-tax or the tax on advertisements is not paid after it has become due,`
  line `the Chairperson may cause to be served upon the person liable for the payment of the same a notice of`
  line `demand in the form set forth in the Sixth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) For every notice of demand which the Chairperson causes to be served on any person under this`
  line `section, a fee of such amount not exceeding five rupees as may be determined by bye-laws made in this`
  line `behalf, shall be payable by the said person and shall be included in the cost of recovery.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (48496)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Penalty in case of default of payment of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48496&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person liable for the payment of any`
  line `tax does not, within thirty days of the service of the notice of demand under section 100 pay the sum due`
  line `and if no appeal is preferred against such tax, he shall be deemed to be in default.`
  line
  line `(2) When the person liable for the payment of any tax is deemed to be in default under`
  line `sub-section (1), such sum not exceeding twenty per cent. of the amount of the tax as may be determined`
  line `by the Chairperson, may be recovered from him by way of penalty, in addition to the amount of the tax`
  line `and the notice fee, payable under sub-section (2) of section 100.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount due as penalty under sub-section (2) shall be recoverable as an arrear of tax under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (48497)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Recovery of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48497&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person liable for the payment of the tax does not, within thirty days`
  line `from the service of the notice of demand, pay the amount due, such sum together with all costs and the`
  line `penalty provided for in section 101 may be recovered under a warrant, issued in the form set forth in the`
  line `Seventh Schedule, by distress and sale of the movable property or the attachment and sale of the`
  line `immovable property, of the defaulter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson shall not recover any sum the liability for which has been remitted on`
  line `appeal under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every warrant issued under this section shall be signed by the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (48498)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title Distress.
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48498&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for any officer or other employees of the Council to whom a`
  line `warrant issued under section 102 is addressed to distrain, wherever it may be found in any place in New`
  line `Delhi; any movable property, or any standing timber, growing crops or grass belonging to the person`
  line `therein named as defaulter, subject to the following conditions, exceptions and exemptions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the following property shall not be distrained:--`
  line
  line `(i) the necessary wearing apparel and bedding of the defaulter, his wife and children and their`
  line `cooking and eating utensils;`
  line
  line `(ii) tools of artisans;`
  line
  line `(iii) books of account; or`
  line
  line `(iv) when the defaulter is an agriculturist his implements of husbandry, seed, grain and such`
  line `cattle as may be necessary to enable the defaulter to earn his livelihood;`
  line
  line `(b) the distress shall not be excessive, that is to say, the property distrained shall be as nearly as`
  line `possible equal in value to the amount recoverable under the warrant, and if any property has been`
  line `distrained which, in the opinion of the Chairperson, should not have been distrained, it shall forthwith`
  line `be released.`
  line
  line `(2) The person charged with the execution of a warrant of distress shall forthwith make an inventory`
  line `of the property which he seizes under such warrant, and shall, at the same time, give a written notice in`
  line `the form set forth in the Eighth Schedule, to the person in possession thereof at the time of seizure that the`
  line `said property will be sold as therein mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (48499)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Disposal of distrained property and attachment and sale of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48499&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the property seized is subject to speedy and natural decay or when the expense of keeping it in`
  line `custody is, when added to the amount to be recovered, likely to exceed its value, the Chairperson shall`
  line `give notice to the person in whose possession the property was at the time of seizure that it will be sold at`
  line `once, and shall sell it accordingly by public auction unless the amount mentioned in the warrant is`
  line `forthwith paid.`
  line
  line `(2) If the warrant is not in the meantime suspended by the Chairperson, or discharged, the property`
  line `seized shall, after the expiry of the period named in the notice served under sub-section (2) of section 103`
  line `be sold by public auction by order of the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3) When a warrant is issued for the attachment and sale of immovable property, the attachment shall`
  line `be made by an order prohibiting the defaulter from transferring or charging the property in any way, and`
  line `all persons from taking any benefit from such transfer or charge, and declaring that such property would`
  line `be sold unless the amount of tax due with all costs of recovery is paid into the municipal office within`
  line `fifteen days from the date of the attachment.`
  line
  line `(4) Such order shall be proclaimed at some place on or adjacent to such property by beat of drum or`
  line `other customary mode and a copy of the order shall be affixed on a conspicuous part of the property and`
  line `upon a conspicuous part of the municipal office and also, when the property is land paying revenue to the`
  line `Government, in the office of the collector.`
  line
  line `(5) Any transfer of or charge on the property attached or any interest therein made without written`
  line `permission of the Chairperson shall be void as against all claims of the Council enforceable under the`
  line attachment.
  line
  line `(6) The surplus of the sale-proceeds, if any, shall, immediately after the sale of the property, be`
  line `credited to the New Delhi Municipal Fund, and notice of such credit shall be given at the same time to the`
  line `person whose property has been sold or his legal representative and if the same is claimed by written`
  line `application to the Chairperson, within one year from the date of the notice, a refund thereof shall be made`
  line `to such person or representative.`
  line
  line `(7) Any surplus not claimed within one year as aforesaid shall be the property of the Council.`
  line
  line `(8) For every distraint and attachment made in accordance with the foregoing provisions, a fee of`
  line `such amount not exceeding two and a half per cent. of the amount of the tax due as shall in each case be`
  line `fixed by the Chairperson, shall be charged, and the said fee shall be included in the costs of recovery.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (48500)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Recovery from a person about to leave New Delhi or Delhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48500&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Chairperson has`
  line `reason to believe that any person from whom any sum is due or is about to become due on account of any`
  line `tax is about to move from New Delhi or Delhi, he may direct the immediate payment by such person of`
  line `the sum so due or about to become due and cause a notice of demand for the same to be served on such`
  line person.
  line
  line `(2) If, on the service of such notice, such person does not forthwith pay the sum so due or about to`
  line `become due, the amount shall be leviable by distress or attachment and sale in the manner hereinbefore`
  line `provided, and the warrant of distress or attachment and sale may be issued and executed without any`
  line delay.
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (48501)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Power to institute suit for recovery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48501&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `Instead of proceeding against a defaulter by distress and`
  line `sale as hereinbefore provided, or after a defaulter has been so proceeded against unsuccessfully or with`
  line `partial success, any sum due or the balance of any sum due, as the case may be, from such defaulter on`
  line `account of a tax may be recovered from him by a suit in any court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (48502)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Power of seizure of vehicles and animals in case of non-payment of tax thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48502&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `tax on any vehicle or animal is not paid, then, instead of proceeding against the defaulter by distress and`
  line `sale of his other movable property as hereinbefore provided, the Chairperson may, at any time after the`
  line `tax has become due, seize and detain the vehicle or animal or both and, if the owner or other person`
  line `entitled thereto does not within seven days in respect of a vehicle and two days in respect of an animal`
  line `from the date of such seizure and detention, claim the same and pay the tax due together with the charges`
  line `incurred in connection with the seizure and detention, the Chairperson may cause the same to be sold and`
  line `apply the proceeds of the sale or such part thereof as is required in discharge of the sum due and the`
  line `charges incurred as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) The surplus, if any, remaining after the application of the sale-proceeds under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be disposed of in the manner laid down in sub-sections (6) and (7) of section 104.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (48503)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Occupiers may be required to pay rent towards satisfaction of property tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48503&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the`
  line `purposes of recovering the amount of any property tax from any occupier under section 68, the`
  line `Chairperson shall cause to be served on such occupier a notice requiring him to pay to the Council, any`
  line `rent due or falling due from him in respect of the land or building to the extent necessary to satisfy the`
  line `portion of the sum due for which he is liable under the said section.`
  line
  line `(2) Such notice shall operate as an attachment of the said rent unless the portion of the sum due shall`
  line `have been paid and satisfied and the occupier shall be entitled to credit in account with the person to`
  line `whom such rent is due for any sum paid by him to the Council in pursuance of such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the person to whom such rent is due is not the person primarily liable for payment of`
  line `the property tax, he shall be entitled to recover from the person primarily liable for the payment of such`
  line `tax any amount for which credit is claimed as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) If any occupier fails to pay to the Council any rent due or falling due which he has been required`
  line `to pay in pursuance of a notice served upon him as aforesaid, the amount of such rent may be recovered`
  line `from him by the Council as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (48504)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Demolition, etc., of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48504&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `If any building is wholly or partly demolished or destroyed or`
  line `otherwise deprived of value, the Chairperson may, on the application in writing of the owner or occupier,`
  line `remit or refund such portion of any tax assessed on the rateable value thereof as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (48505)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Remission or refund of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48505&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any building together with land appurtenant thereto has`
  line `remained vacant and unproductive of rent for sixty or more consecutive days, the Chairperson shall remit`
  line `or refund, as the case may be, two-thirds of such portion of the property tax assessed on the rateable value`
  line `thereof, as may be proportionate to the number of days during which the said building together with the`
  line `land appurtenant thereto has remained vacant and unproductive of rent.`
  line
  line `(2) If any land, not being land appurtenant to a building, has remained vacant and unproductive of`
  line `rent for sixty or more consecutive days, the Chairperson shall remit or refund, as the case may be, one`
  line `half of such portion of the property tax assessed on the rateable value thereof, as may be, proportionate to`
  line `the number of days during which the said land has remained vacant and unproductive of rent.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (48506)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Power to require entry in assessment list of details of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48506&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of`
  line `obtaining a partial remission or refund of tax, the owner of a building composed of separate tenements`
  line `may request the Chairperson, at the time of the assessment of the building, to enter in the assessment list,`
  line `in addition to the rateable value of the whole building, a note regarding any detail of the rateable value of`
  line `each separate tenement.`
  line
  line `(2) When any tenement, the rateable value of which has been thus separately recorded has remained`
  line `vacant and unproductive of rent for sixty or more consecutive days, such portion of any tax assessed on the rateable value of the whole building shall be remitted or refunded as would have been remitted or`
  line `refunded if the tenement had been separately assessed.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (48507)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Notice to be given of the circumstances in which remission or refund is claimed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48507&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line No
  line `remission or refund under section 110 or section 111 shall be made unless notice in writing of the fact that`
  line `land, building or tenement has become vacant and unproductive of rent has been given to the Chairperson,`
  line `and no remission or refund shall take effect in respect of any period commencing more than fifteen days`
  line `before delivery of such notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (48508)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `What buildings are to be deemed vacant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48508&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of sections 110 and 111 no`
  line `land, building or tenement shall be deemed vacant if maintained as a pleasure resort or town or country`
  line `house or be deemed unproductive of rent if let to a tenant who has a continuing right of occupation`
  line `thereof, whether he is in actual occupation or not.`
  line
  line `(2) The burden of proving the facts entitling any person to claim relief under sections 109, 110 or`
  line `section 111, shall be upon him.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (48509)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Notice to be given of every occupation of vacant land or building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48509&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `The owner of any land,`
  line `building or tenement in respect of which a remission or refund of tax has been given under section 110 or`
  line `section 111, shall give notice of the re-occupation of such land, building or tenement within fifteen days`
  line `of such re-occupation.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (48510)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Appeal against assessment, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48510&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal against the levy or assessment of any tax under`
  line `this Act shall lie to the court of the district judges of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(2) If, before or on the hearing of an appeal under this section, any question of law or usage having`
  line `the force of law or construction of a document arises, the Court of district judge on his own motion may,`
  line `or on the application of any party to the appeal, shall, draw up a statement of the facts of the case, and the`
  line `question so arising, and refer the statement with his opinion on the question for the decision of the High`
  line Court.
  line
  line `(3) On a reference being made under sub-section (2), the subsequent proceedings in the case shall be,`
  line `as nearly as may be in conformity with the rules relating to references to the High Court contained in`
  line `Order XLVI of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(4) In every appeal, the costs shall be in the discretion of the Court.`
  line
  line `(5) Costs awarded under this section to the Council shall be recoverable by the Council as an arrear of`
  line `tax due from the appellant.`
  line
  line `(6) If the Council fails to pay any costs awarded to an appellant within ten days after the date of the`
  line `order for payment thereof, the Court may order the Chairperson to pay the amount to the appellant.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (48511)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Conditions of right to appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48511&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `No appeal shall be heard or determined under section 115`
  line unless--
  line
  line `(a) the appeal is, in the case of a property tax, brought within thirty days next after the date of`
  line `authentication of the assessment list under section 70 (exclusive of the time requisite for obtaining a`
  line `copy of the relevant entries therein) or, as the case may be, within thirty days of the date on which an`
  line `amendment is finally made under section 72 and, in the case of any other tax, within thirty days next`
  line `after the date of the receipt of the notice of assessment or of alteration of assessment or, if no notice`
  line `has been given, within thirty days after the date of the presentation of the first bill or, as the case may`
  line `be, the first notice of demand in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount, if any, in dispute in the appeal has been deposited by the appellant in the office of`
  line `the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (48512)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Condonation of delay in preferring the appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48512&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `clause (a) of section 116, an appeal may be admitted after the expiration of the period prescribed therefor`
  line `by that section if the appellant satisfies the court that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal`
  line `within the period.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (48513)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Finality of appellate orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48513&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `The order of the Court confirming, setting aside or modifying an`
  line `order in respect of any rateable value or assessment or liability to assessment or taxation shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be lawful for the Court upon application or on its own motion, to review any`
  line `order passed by it in appeal within three months from the date of the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (48514)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Power to inspect for purposes of determining rateable value or tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48514&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson`
  line `may, without giving any previous notice, enter upon and make an inspection of--`
  line
  line `(a) any land or building for the purpose of determining the rateable value of such land or`
  line building;
  line
  line `(b) any stable, garage, or coach house or any place wherein he may have reason to believe that`
  line `there is any vehicle or animal liable to a tax under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any place or premises which he has reason to believe are being used or are about to be used`
  line `for any performance or show in respect of which the theatre-tax is payable or would be payable;`
  line
  line `(d) any land, building or vehicle in or upon which any advertisement liable to tax under this Act`
  line `is exhibited or displayed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may, by written summons, require the attendance before him of any person`
  line `whom he has reason to believe to be liable to the payment of a tax in respect of a vehicle or animal, or of`
  line `any servant of any such person and may examine such person or servant as to the number and description`
  line `of vehicles and animals owned by or in the possession or under the control of such person; and every`
  line `person or servant of such person so summoned shall be bound to attend before the Chairperson and to`
  line `give information to the best of his knowledge and belief as to the said matters.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (48515)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title Composition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48515&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may with the previous sanction of Council allow any`
  line `person to compound for any tax.`
  line
  line `(2) Every sum due by reason of the composition of a tax under sub-section (1) shall be recovered as`
  line `an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (48516)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Irrecoverable debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48516&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may write off any sum due on account of any tax or`
  line `of the costs of recovering any tax if such sum is, in his opinion irrecoverable:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the sum written off in favour of any person exceeds one thousand rupees, the`
  line `previous sanction of the Council shall be first obtained.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall report to the Council every case in which any sum has been written off`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (48517)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Obligation to disclose liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48517&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may, by written notice, call upon any`
  line `inhabitant of New Delhi to furnish such information as may be necessary for the purpose of`
  line ascertaining--
  line
  line `(a) whether such inhabitant is liable to pay any tax imposed by the Council under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) at what amount he should be assessed; or`
  line
  line `(c) the rateable value of the land or building which he occupies and the name and address of the`
  line `owner or lessee thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person when called upon under sub-section (1) to furnish information neglects to furnish it`
  line `within the period specified in this behalf by the Chairperson or furnishes information which is not true to`
  line `the best of his knowledge or belief, he shall be liable, in addition to any penalty which may be imposed`
  line `under this Act, to be assessed at such amount on account of tax as the Chairperson may deem proper, and`
  line `the assessment so made shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (48518)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Immaterial error not to affect liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48518&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `No assessment and no charge or demand on account`
  line `of any tax shall be impeached or affected by reason only of any mistake in the name, residence, place of`
  line `business or occupation of any person liable to pay the tax or in the description of any property or thing, or`
  line `of any mistake in the amount of the assessment, charge or demand, or by reason only of clerical error or other defect of form, if the directions contained in this Act and the bye-laws made thereunder have in`
  line `substance and effect been complied with and it shall be enough in the case of any such tax on property or`
  line `any assessment of value for the purpose of any such tax, if the property taxed or assessed is so described`
  line `as to be generally known; and it shall not be necessary to name the owner or occupier thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (48519)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `General power of exemption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48519&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `The Council may, by resolution passed in this behalf, exempt`
  line `either wholly or in part from the payment of any tax levied under this Act, any class of persons or any`
  line `class of property or goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (48520)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Payment of proceeds of entertainment and betting taxes to Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48520&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `The proceeds of the`
  line `entertainment and betting taxes collected in New Delhi under the provisions of the U. P. Entertainment`
  line `and Betting Tax Act, 1937 (U.P. Act 18 of 1937), as extended to the National Capital Territory of Delhi`
  line `(which shall form part of the Consolidated Fund of the National Capital Territory of Delhi) reduced by`
  line `the cost of collection as determined by the Government shall, if the Legislative Assembly of the National`
  line `Capital Territory of Delhi by appropriation made by law in this behalf so provides, be paid to the Council`
  line `for the performance of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (48521)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Power of Council to borrow.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48521&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, in pursuance of any resolution passed by`
  line `it, borrow by way of debenture or otherwise on the security of all or any of the taxes, rates, cesses, fees`
  line `and charges authorised by or under this Act, any sums of money which may be required--`
  line
  line `(a) for acquiring any land which it has power to acquire;`
  line
  line `(b) for erecting any building which it has power to erect;`
  line
  line `(c) for the execution of any permanent work, the provision of any plant, or the doing of any other`
  line `thing which it has power to execute, provide or do, if the cost of carrying out the purpose in question`
  line `ought to be spread over a term of years;`
  line
  line `(d) to pay off any debt due to the Central Government or the Government;`
  line
  line `(e) to repay a loan previously raised under this Act or any other Act previously in force; or`
  line
  line `(f) for any other purpose for which the Council is, by virtue of this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, authorised to borrow:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) no loan shall be raised without the previous sanction of the Central Government or without`
  line `previous publication of the application for sanction under the Local Authorities Loans Act, 1914`
  line `(9 of 1914), and the rules made thereunder; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the amount of loan, the rate of interest and the terms including the date of floatation, the time`
  line `and method of the repayment and the like shall be subject to the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) When any sum of money has been borrowed under sub-section (1), no portion of any sum of`
  line `money borrowed for any of the purposes referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be applied to the`
  line `payment of salaries and allowances to any officers or other employees other than those exclusively`
  line `employed in connection with the carrying out of that purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (48522)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Time for repayment of money borrowed under section 126.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48522&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `The time for the repayment of`
  line `any money borrowed under section 126 shall in no case exceed sixty years and the time for repayment of`
  line `any money borrowed for the purpose of discharging any previous loan shall not, except with the express`
  line `sanction of Central Government, extend beyond the unexpired portion of the period for which such`
  line `previous loan was sanctioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (48523)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Form and effect of debenture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48523&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `All debentures issued under this Chapter shall be in such form`
  line `as the Council may, with the previous sanction of the Central Government, determine and shall be transferable in such manner as shall be therein expressed; and the right to sue in respect of the moneys`
  line `secured by any of such debentures shall vest in the holders thereof for the time being without any`
  line `preference by reason of some such debentures being prior in date to others.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (48524)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Payment to survivors of joint payees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48524&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `When any debenture or security issued under this Act`
  line `is payable to two or more persons jointly, and either or any of them dies, then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `in section 45 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), the debenture or security shall be payable to`
  line `the survivor or survivors of such person:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall affect any claim by legal representative of a deceased`
  line `person against such survivor or survivors.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (48525)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Receipt by joint holders for interest or dividend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48525&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `When two or more persons are joint`
  line `holders of any debenture or security issued under this Act, any one of such persons may give an effectual`
  line `receipt for any interest or dividend payable in respect of such debenture or security, unless notice to the`
  line `contrary has been given to the Council by the other of such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (48526)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Maintenance and investment of sinking funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48526&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall maintain sinking funds`
  line `for the repayment of money borrowed on debentures issued and shall pay every year into such sinking`
  line `funds such sum as will be sufficient for the repayment within the period fixed for the loan of all moneys`
  line `borrowed on the debentures issued.`
  line
  line `(2) All money paid into the sinking funds shall, as soon as possible, be invested by the Chairperson in`
  line `public securities and every such investment shall be reported by the Chairperson to the Council within`
  line `fifteen days.`
  line
  line `(3) All dividends and other sums received in respect of any such investment shall, as soon as possible`
  line `after receipt, be paid into the sinking funds and invested in the manner laid down in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) When any part of a sinking fund is invested in New Delhi municipal debentures, or is applied in`
  line `paying off any part of a loan before the period fixed for repayment, the interest which would otherwise`
  line `have been payable on such debentures or on such part of the loan shall be paid into the sinking fund and`
  line `invested in the manner laid down in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) Any investment made under this section may, subject to the provision of sub-section (2), be varied`
  line `or transposed.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (48527)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Application of sinking funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48527&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `A sinking fund or any part thereof shall be applied in or`
  line `towards the discharge of the loan or a part of the loan for which such fund was created, and until such`
  line `loan or part is wholly discharged shall not be applied for any other purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that when any loan or part thereof has been consolidated under section 134, the Chairperson`
  line `shall transfer to the sinking fund of the consolidated loan such part of the sinking funds of the original`
  line `loans as may be proportionate to the amount of the original loans incorporated in the consolidated loan.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (48528)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Annual statement by Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48528&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall, at the end of every year,`
  line `submit to the Council a statement showing--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount which has been invested during the year under section 131;`
  line
  line `(b) the date of the last investment made previous to the submission of the statement;`
  line
  line `(c) the aggregate amount of the securities then in his hand; and`
  line
  line `(d) the aggregate amount which has up to the date of the statement been applied under section`
  line `132, in or towards discharging loans.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such statement shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (48529)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Power of Council to consolidate loans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48529&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in this Chapter, the Council may consolidate all or any of its loans and for that purpose may`
  line `invite tenders for a new loan (to be called "the New Delhi Municipal Council Consolidated Loan, 19--")`
  line `and invite holders of the municipal debentures to exchange their debentures for scrips of such loan.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms of any such consolidated loan and the form of its scrip and the rates at which exchange`
  line `into such consolidated loan shall be permitted shall be subject to the prior approval of the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The period for the exchanging of any such consolidated loan shall not, without the sanction of the`
  line `Central Government, extend beyond the farthest date within which any of the loans to be consolidated`
  line `would otherwise be repayable.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall provide for the repayment of any such consolidated loan by a sinking fund in`
  line `the manner laid down in section 131 having regard to the amount transferred to such sinking fund under`
  line `section 132.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (48530)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Priority of payment for interest and repayment of loans over other payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48530&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) All`
  line `payments due from the Council for interest on and repayment of loans shall be made in priority to all`
  line `other payments due from the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) If any money borrowed or deemed to have been borrowed by the Council from Central`
  line `Government or the Government or any interest or costs due in respect thereof be not repaid according to`
  line `the conditions of the loan, the Central Government or the Government may attach the New Delhi`
  line `Municipal Fund or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) After such attachment no person except an officer appointed in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government shall in any way deal with the attached fund; but such officer may do all acts in respect`
  line `thereof which any municipal authority, officer or other employee might have done if such attachment has`
  line `not taken place, and may apply the proceeds in satisfaction of the arrears and of all interests and cost due`
  line `in respect thereof and of all expenses caused by the attachment and subsequent proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such attachment shall defeat or prejudice any debt for which the fund was previously`
  line `charged in accordance with law; and all such prior charges shall be paid out of the proceeds of the fund`
  line `before any part of the proceeds is applied to satisfaction of the debt due to the Central Government or the`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (48531)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48531&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `The Council may make regulations to carry out the purposes of`
  line `this Chapter including, in particular, the issue of duplicates in case of loss of debentures by theft,`
  line `destruction or otherwise, and renewal of debentures on payment of fees prescribed in this behalf by such`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (48532)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Acquisition of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48532&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall, for the purpose of this Act, have power to acquire`
  line `and hold movable and immovable property, or any interest therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (48533)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Acquisition of immovable property by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48533&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Council decides to acquire`
  line `any immovable property for the purpose of this Act, the Chairperson shall acquire such property on behalf`
  line `of the Council by agreement on such terms and at such price as may be approved by the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (48534)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Procedure when immovable property cannot be acquired by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48534&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the`
  line `Chairperson is unable to acquire any immovable property under section 138 by agreement, the Central`
  line `Government may at the request of the Chairperson procure the acquisition thereof under the provisions of`
  line `the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), and on payment by the Council of the compensation awarded`
  line `under that Act and of the charges incurred by that Government in connection with the proceedings, the`
  line `land shall vest in the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (48535)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Disposal of movable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48535&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) With respect to the disposal of movable property`
  line `belonging to Council the Chairperson may, in his discretion, dispose of by sale or otherwise, any movable`
  line `property belonging to the Council not exceeding in value in each instance one thousand rupees, or such`
  line `higher amount as the Council may prescribe, or let out on hire any movable property or grant a lease of any immovable property belonging to the Council including any right of gathering and taking fruits and`
  line `the like, for a period not exceeding one year at a time.`
  line
  line `(2) In cases not covered by sub-section (1), the Chairperson may, with the sanction of the Council,`
  line `lease, sell, let out on hire or otherwise transfer any movable property belonging to the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (48536)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Disposal of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48536&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may, with the sanction of the Council,`
  line `lease, sell, let out on hire or otherwise transfer any immovable property belonging to the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The consideration for which any immovable property may be sold, leased or otherwise transferred`
  line `shall not be less than the value at which such immovable property could be sold, leased or otherwise`
  line `transferred in normal and fair competition.`
  line
  line `(3) The sanction of Council under section 140 or this section may be given either generally for any`
  line `class of cases or specially for any particular case.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to any conditions or limitation that may be specified in any other provisions of this Act`
  line `the foregoing provisions of section 140 and this section shall apply to every disposal of property`
  line `belonging to the Council made under, or for any purpose of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Every case of disposal of property under sub-section (1) of section 140 shall be reported by the`
  line `Chairperson without delay to the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (48537)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Contracts by the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48537&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of sections 143 and 144 the Council shall`
  line `be competent to enter into and perform any contract necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (48538)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Procedure for making contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48538&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `With respect to the making of contracts, the following`
  line `provisions shall have effect, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) every such contract shall be made on behalf of the Council by the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) no such contract, for any purpose which in accordance with any provision of this Act the`
  line `Chairperson may not carry out without the approval or sanction of the Council shall be made by him`
  line `until and unless such approval or sanction has been duly obtained;`
  line
  line `(c) no contract which will involve an expenditure exceeding ten lakh rupees or such higher`
  line `amount as the Central Government may from time to time, fix, shall be made by the Chairperson`
  line `unless the same is previously approved by the Council; and`
  line
  line `(d) every contract made by the Chairperson involving an expenditure exceeding one lakh rupees`
  line `but not exceeding ten lakh rupees or such higher amount as may be fixed under clause (c) shall be`
  line `reported by him, within one month after the same has been made to the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (48539)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Mode of executing contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48539&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) The mode of executing contracts under this Act shall be`
  line `prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) No contract which is not made in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder shall be binding on the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (48540)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48540&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, the following words and`
  line `expressions in relation to water supply shall have the respective meanings given below, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) "communication pipe" means,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the premises supplied with water abut on the part of the street in which the main is`
  line `laid, and the service pipe enters those premises otherwise than through the outer wall of a`
  line `building abutting on the street and has a stopcock placed in those premises and as near to the boundary of that street as is reasonably practicable, so much of the service pipe as lies between`
  line `the main and that stopcock;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, so much of the service pipe as lies between the main and the boundary`
  line `of the street in which the main is laid, and includes the ferrule at the junction of the service pipe`
  line `with the main, and also--`
  line
  line `(i) where the communication pipe ends at a stopcock, that stopcock; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any stopcock fitted on the communication pipe between the end thereof and the main;`
  line
  line `(2) "main" means a pipe laid by the Council for the purpose of giving a general supply of water`
  line `as distinct from a supply to individual consumers and includes any apparatus used in connection with`
  line `such a pipe;`
  line
  line `(3) "service pipe" means so much of any pipe for supplying water from a main to any premises as`
  line `is subject to water pressure from that main, or would be so subject but for the closing of some tap;`
  line
  line `(4) "supply pipe" means so much of any service pipe as is not a communication pipe;`
  line
  line `(5) "trunk main" means a main constructed for the purpose of conveying water from a source of`
  line `supply to a filter or reservoir or from one filter or reservoir to another filter or reservoir, or for the`
  line `purpose of conveying water in bulk from one part of the limits of supply to another part of those`
  line `limits, or for the purpose of giving or taking a supply of water in bulk;`
  line
  line `(6) "water fittings" includes pipes (other than mains), taps, cocks, valves, ferrules, meters,`
  line `cisterns, baths and other similar apparatus used in connection with the supply and use of water.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (48541)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Council may carry out surveys and formulate proposals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48541&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may--`
  line
  line `(a) carry out a survey of the existing consumption of and demand for water supplies in New Delhi`
  line `and of the water resources in or likely to be made available in New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b) prepare an estimate of the future water supply requirements of New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(c) carry out a survey of the existing quantity of sewage collection;`
  line
  line `(d) formulate proposals as to--`
  line
  line `(i) the existing or future water supply requirements of New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(ii) the existing or future sewage collection requirement in New Delhi including proposals for`
  line `the manner in which and the place or places at which sewage should be carried and collected.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Council is of the opinion that the works and other properties for the time being vested in the`
  line `Council, are inadequate for the purpose of sufficient supply of water or for the purpose of efficient`
  line `collection of sewage under this Act it may take step in accordance with the provisions of this Act for the`
  line `construction of additional works, whether within New Delhi or outside New Delhi with the approval of`
  line `the Administrator and for the acquisition of additional properties for such works.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (48542)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Functions in relation to water supplies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48542&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Council to take steps`
  line `from time to time--`
  line
  line `(a) for ascertaining the sufficiency and wholesomeness of water supplies within New Delhi and`
  line `receiving bulk supplies of water from the authority prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) for providing a supply of wholesome water in pipes to every part of New Delhi in which there`
  line `are houses, for the domestic purposes of the occupants thereof, and for taking the pipes affording that`
  line `supply to such point or points as will enable the houses to be connected thereto at a reasonable cost,`
  line `so, however, that this clause shall not require the Council to do anything which is not practicable at a`
  line `reasonable cost or to provide such a supply to any part of New Delhi where such a supply is already`
  line `available at such point or points aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(c) for providing as far as possible, a supply of wholesome water otherwise than in pipes to every`
  line `part of New Delhi in which there are houses, for the domestic purposes of the occupants thereof and to which it is not practicable to provide a supply in pipes at a reasonable cost, and in which danger to`
  line `health arises from the insufficiency or unwholesomeness of the existing supply and a public supply is`
  line `required and can be provided at a reasonable cost, and for securing that such supply is available`
  line `within a reasonable distance of every house in that part.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises under clause (b) of sub-section (1) as to whether anything is or is not`
  line `practicable at a reasonable cost or as to the point or points to which pipes must be taken in order to enable`
  line `houses to be connected to them at a reasonable cost, or under clause (c) thereof, as to whether a public`
  line `supply can be provided at a reasonable cost, the Council shall determine that question and thereupon it`
  line `shall give effect to that determination.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Chairperson shall, for the purpose of`
  line `securing, so far as is reasonably practicable, that every house has available a sufficient supply of`
  line `wholesome water for domestic purposes, exercise his powers under this Act of requiring the owners of`
  line `houses to provide a supply of water thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall secure that the water in any water works belonging to the Council from which`
  line `the water is supplied for domestic purpose is wholesome.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (48543)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Water supplied for domestic purposes not to be used for non-domestic purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48543&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line No
  line `person shall, without the written permission of the Chairperson, use or allow to be used for other than`
  line `domestic purposes water supplied for domestic purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (48544)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Supply of water for domestic purposes not to include any supply for certain specified purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48544&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `The supply of water for domestic purposes under this Act shall not be deemed to include any`
  line supply--
  line
  line `(a) for animals or for washing vehicles where such animals or vehicles are kept for sale or hire;`
  line
  line `(b) for any trade, manufacture or business;`
  line
  line `(c) for fountains, swimming baths or any ornamental or mechanical purpose;`
  line
  line `(d) for gardens or for purposes of irrigation;`
  line
  line `(e) for making or for watering streets; or`
  line
  line `(f) for building purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (48545)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Power to supply water for non-domestic purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48545&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may supply water`
  line `for any purpose other than a domestic purpose on such terms and conditions consistent with this Act and`
  line `the bye-laws made thereunder as may be laid down in this behalf by the Council on receiving a written`
  line `application specifying the purpose for which the supply is required and the quantity likely to be`
  line consumed.
  line
  line `(2) When a application under sub-section (1) is received, the Chairperson may subject to such charges`
  line `and rates as may be fixed by the Council, place or allow to be placed the necessary pipes and water`
  line `fittings of such dimensions and character as may be prescribed by bye-laws and may arrange for the`
  line `supply of water through such pipes and fittings.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (48546)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Use of water for extinguishing fire.`
  content `Water may be used for extinguishing fire.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48546&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (48547)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Power to require water supply to be taken.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48547&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the Chairperson that any`
  line `premises in New Delhi are without supply of wholesome water for domestic purposes or that the existing`
  line `supply of water for domestic purposes available for the persons usually occupying or employed in such`
  line `premises is inadequate or on any sanitary grounds objectionable, the Chairperson may by notice in writing`
  line `require the owner of the premises or the persons primarily liable for the payment of the property tax in`
  line `respect of the same--`
  line
  line `(a) to take a connection from the municipal water works adequate for the requirements of the`
  line `persons occupying or employed in the premises, or to take such additional or enlarged connection or`
  line `connections from the municipal water works; and`
  line
  line `(b) to provide, supply pipes and water fittings, install and work a pump and do all such works and`
  line `take all such measures as may, in the opinion of the Chairperson be necessary for the above purposes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may in the notice issued under sub-section (1) specify--`
  line
  line `(a) the size, material and quality of the pipes and water fittings to be provided;`
  line
  line `(b) the position of the pipes and water fittings to be provided;`
  line
  line `(c) the means of access for the inspection of the pipes and water fittings;`
  line
  line `(d) the type of pump that should be installed and the period or periods of the day for which it`
  line `should be kept working;`
  line
  line `(e) the period within which any or all the requisitions specified in the notice should be carried out.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (48548)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `New premises not to be occupied without arrangement for water supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48548&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `It shall not be`
  line `lawful for the owner of any premises which may be newly constructed or reconstructed within any portion`
  line `of New Delhi to occupy it or cause or permit it to be occupied until he has obtained a certificate from the`
  line `Chairperson that there is provided within, or within a reasonable distance of, the premises such supply of`
  line `wholesome water as appears to the Chairperson to be adequate for the persons who may occupy, or be`
  line `employed in, such premises for their domestic purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (48549)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Public gratuitous water supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48549&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson with the approval of the Council may`
  line `provide gratuitous supply of wholesome water to the public within New Delhi and may, for that purpose,`
  line `erect public hydrants or other conveniences.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may with like approval close a public hydrant or other convenience when it is no`
  line `longer required for the supply of wholesome water to the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (48550)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Power to lay mains.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48550&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may lay a main whether within or without the local`
  line `limits of the Council--`
  line
  line `(a) in any street; and`
  line
  line `(b) with the consent of every owner and occupier of any land not forming part of a street, in, over`
  line `or on that land,`
  line
  line `and may, from time to time, inspect, repair, alter or renew or may at any time remove any main so laid`
  line `whether by virtue of this section or otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a consent required for the purpose of this sub-section is withheld, the`
  line `Chairperson may, after giving the owner or occupier of the land a written notice of his intention so to do,`
  line `lay the main in, over or on that land even without such consent.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Chairperson, in exercise of the powers under this section, lays a main in, over or on any`
  line `land not forming part of a street, or inspects, repairs, alters, renews or removes a main so laid down in,`
  line `over or on any such land, he shall pay compensation to every person interested in that land for any`
  line `damage done to, or injurious affection of that land by reason of the inspection, laying, repair, alteration,`
  line `renewal or removal of the main.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (48551)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Power to lay service pipes, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48551&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may, in any street whether within or`
  line `without the local limits of the Council lay such service pipes with such stopcocks and other water fittings`
  line `as he may deem necessary for supplying water to premises and may, from time to time, inspect, repair,`
  line `alter or renew and may, at any time, remove any service pipe laid in a street whether by virtue of this`
  line `section or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a service pipe has been lawfully laid in, over, or on the land not forming part of a street,`
  line `the Chairperson may from time to time enter upon that land and inspect, repair, alter, renew or remove the`
  line `pipe or lay a new pipe in substitution thereof but shall pay compensation for any damage done in the`
  line `course of such action.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (48552)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Provision of fire hydrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48552&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall fix hydrants on water mains (other than`
  line `trunk mains) at such places as may be most convenient for affording a supply of water for extinguishing`
  line `any fire which may break out and shall keep in good order and from time to time renew every such`
  line hydrant.
  line
  line `(2) To denote the situation of every hydrant placed under this section, letters, marks or figures shall`
  line `be displayed prominently on some wall, building or other structure near such hydrant.`
  line
  line `(3) As soon as any such hydrant is completed, the Chairperson shall deposit a key thereof at each`
  line `place where a public fire engine is kept and in such other places as he deems necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson may, at the request and expense of the owner or occupier of any factory,`
  line `workshop, trade premises or place of business situated in or near a street in which a pipe is laid (and not`
  line `being a trunk main and being of sufficient dimensions to carry a hydrant), fix on the pipe and keep in`
  line `good order and from time to time renew one or more fire hydrants, to be used only for extinguishing fires`
  line `as near as conveniently may be to that factory, workshop, trade premises or place of business.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson shall allow all persons to take water for extinguishing fires from any pipe on`
  line `which a hydrant is fixed without any payment.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (48553)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Supply of water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48553&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may permit the owner, lessee or occupier of any`
  line `premises to connect the premises by means of supply pipes for conveying to the premises a supply of`
  line `water for his domestic purposes from the municipal water works subject to the requirements specified in`
  line `section 159 and the conditions, if any, laid down in the bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner of every premises connected with the municipal water works, shall, when so required`
  line `by the Chairperson, set up electric pumps or other contrivances whereby water may be caused to reach to`
  line `the top of the top-most story of such premises.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (48554)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Laying of supply pipes, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48554&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) An owner, lessor or occupier of any premises, who desires to`
  line `have a supply of water for his domestic purposes from the municipal water works, shall comply with the`
  line `following requirements, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) he shall give to the Chairperson fourteen days notice of his intention to lay the necessary`
  line `supply pipe; and`
  line
  line `(b) he shall lay the supply pipe at his own expense, having first obtained, as respects any land not`
  line `forming part of a street, the consent of the owners or occupiers thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any part of the supply pipe is to be laid in a street, he shall not himself break`
  line `open the street or lay that part of the pipe.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the receipt of such a notice as is referred to in sub-section (1), the Chairperson shall lay the`
  line `necessary communication pipe and any part of the supply pipe which is to be laid in street shall connect`
  line `the communication pipe with the supply pipe.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses, reasonably incurred by the Chairperson in executing the work which he is required`
  line `or authorised by this section to execute, shall be repaid to him by the person to whom the notice was`
  line `given and may be recovered from such person as an arrear of tax under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if under the provisions of this section, the Chairperson lays a main in lieu of a supply`
  line `pipe, the additional cost incurred in laying the main instead of a supply pipe shall be borne by him.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, the Chairperson`
  line `may, within a reasonable time after the service of the notice upon him, require the person giving the`
  line `notice either to pay to him, in advance the cost of the work, as estimated by the Chairperson or any officer`
  line `authorised by in this behalf or to give security for payment thereof to his satisfaction.`
  line
  line `(5) If any payment made to the Chairperson under sub-section (4) exceeds the expenses which the`
  line `Chairperson would be entitled to recover from the person giving the notice, the excess shall be repaid by`
  line `him and if and so far as those expenses are not covered by the payment, the Chairperson may recover the`
  line `balance from such person as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (48555)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Power to require separate service pipes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48555&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may require the provision of a`
  line `separate service pipe for each of the premises supplied or to be supplied by him with water.`
  line
  line `(2) If, in the case of any premises already supplied with water but not having a separate service pipe,`
  line `the Chairperson gives notice to the owner of the premises requiring the provision of such a pipe, the`
  line `owner shall, within three months, lay so much of the required pipe as will constitute a supply pipe and is`
  line `not required to be laid in a street, and the Chairperson, shall, within fourteen days after the owner has`
  line `done so, lay so much of the required pipe as will constitute a communication pipe or a supply pipe to be`
  line `laid in a street and make all necessary communications.`
  line
  line `(3) If an owner upon whom a notice has been served under sub-section (2) fails to comply therewith`
  line `the Chairperson may himself execute the work which the owner was required to execute and recover the`
  line `expenses reasonably incurred by him in executing the work as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (48556)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title Stopcocks.
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48556&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) On every service pipe laid after the commencement of this Act the Chairperson,`
  line `shall, and on every service pipe laid before such commencement, Chairperson may, fit a stopcock`
  line `enclosed in a cover box or a pit of such size as may be reasonably necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Every stopcocks fitted on a service pipe after the commencement of this Act shall be placed in`
  line `such position as the Chairperson deems most convenient:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) a stopcock in private premises shall be placed as near as is reasonably practicable to the street`
  line `from which the service pipe enters those premises; and`
  line
  line `(b) a stopcock in a street shall be placed as near to the boundary thereof as is reasonably`
  line practicable.
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (48557)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Power of Chairperson to provide meters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48557&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may provide a water-meter`
  line `and attach the same to the service pipe in premises connected with municipal water works.`
  line
  line `(2) The expense of providing and attaching a meter under sub-section (1) shall be paid out of the New`
  line `Delhi Municipal Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) The use, rent to be paid for such use, maintenance and testing of meters shall be regulated by`
  line `orders made by the Council in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (48558)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Presumption as to correctness of meters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48558&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `Whenever water is supplied under this Chapter`
  line `through a meter it shall be presumed that the quantity indicated by the meter has been consumed until the`
  line `contrary is proved.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (48559)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Prohibition of waste or misuse of water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48559&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall wilfully or negligently cause or`
  line `suffer any water fitting which he is liable to maintain,--`
  line
  line `(a) to be or remain so out of order or so in need of repair, or`
  line
  line `(b) to be or remain so constructed or adapted or to be so used,`
  line
  line `that the water supplied to him by the Council is or is likely to be wasted, misused or unduly consumed, or`
  line `contaminated before use, or that foul air or any impure matter is likely to return into any pipe belonging`
  line `to, or connected with, a pipe belonging to the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) If any water fittings which any person is liable to maintain is in such a condition, or so constructed`
  line `or adapted as aforesaid, the Chairperson, without prejudice to his right to proceed against the person`
  line `under any other provision of this Act may require that person to carry out any necessary repairs or`
  line `alterations and if he fails to do so within forty-eight hours, may himself carry out the work and recover`
  line `from him the expenses reasonably incurred by him in so doing, as an arrear of tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (48560)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Power to enter premises to detect waste or misuse of water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48560&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or any`
  line `municipal officer authorised by the Chairperson in writing may, between sunrise and sunset, enter any`
  line `premises supplied with water by the Council in order to examine if there be any waste or misuse of such`
  line `water and the Chairperson or such officer shall not be refused admittance to the premises nor shall be`
  line `obstructed by any person in making his examination.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (48561)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Power to test water fittings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48561&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may test any water fitting used in connection`
  line `with water supplied by the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (48562)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Power to close or restrict use of water from polluted source of supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48562&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `Chairperson is of opinion that the water in or obtained from any well, tank or other source of supply not`
  line `vested in the Council, being water which is or is likely to be used for domestic purposes, or for the`
  line `preparation of food or drink for human consumption, is or is likely to become so polluted as to be`
  line `prejudicial to health, the Chairperson may, after giving the owner or occupier of the premises in which the`
  line `source of supply is situated a reasonable opportunity of being heard, by order, direct that the source of`
  line `supply be permanently or temporarily closed or cut off or the water therefrom be used for certain`
  line `purposes only or make such order as appears to him necessary to prevent injury or danger to the health of`
  line `persons using the water or consuming food or drink prepared therewith or therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making any order under this section, the Chairperson may cause the water to be analysed`
  line `at the cost of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) If the person to whom an order is made under this section fails to comply therewith, the`
  line `Chairperson may do whatever may be necessary for giving effect to the order, and any expenses`
  line `reasonably incurred by him in so doing may be recovered by him from the person in default as an arrear`
  line `of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (48563)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `Water pipes, etc., not to be placed where water will be polluted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48563&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `(1) No water pipes shall be`
  line `laid in a drain or on the surface of an open channel or house gully or within six meters of a cesspool or in`
  line `any position where the pipe is likely to be injured or the water therein polluted; and no well or tank and`
  line `except with the consent of the Chairperson, no cistern shall be constructed within six meters of a latrine,`
  line `or cesspool.`
  line
  line `(2) No latrine, or cesspool shall be constructed or made within six meters of any well, tank, water`
  line `pipe or cistern or in any position where the pipe, well, tank or cistern is likely to be injured or the water`
  line `therein polluted.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (48564)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 169
  title `Power to cut off private water supply or to turn off water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48564&sectionno=169&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may,`
  line `subject to the conditions laid down in this behalf in the bye-laws, cut off or turn off water supply from`
  line `any municipal water work to any premises or part thereof to which a private water supply is furnished by`
  line `the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenses of cutting off or turning off water supply shall be paid by the owner or occupier of`
  line `premises and shall be recoverable from the owner or occupier as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (48565)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 170
  title `Joint and several liability of owners and occupiers for offence in relation to water supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48565&sectionno=170&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `If any offence relating to water supply is committed under this Act on any premises connected`
  line `with the municipal water works, the owner, the person primarily liable for the payment of property tax`
  line `and occupiers of the said premises shall be jointly and severally liable for such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (48566)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 171
  title `Public drains, etc., to vest in the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48566&sectionno=171&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `(1) All public drains, all drains in, alongside or`
  line `under any public street, and all sewage collection works, whether constructed out of the New Delhi`
  line `Municipal Fund or otherwise and all works, materials and things appertaining thereto, which are situated`
  line `in New Delhi shall vest in the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) All public and other drains which are vested in the Council are hereafter in this Act referred to as`
  line `municipal drains.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of enlarging, deepening or otherwise repairing or maintaining any such drain or`
  line `sewage collection work so much of the sub-soil appertaining thereto as may be necessary for the said`
  line `purpose shall be deemed all so to vest in the Council.`
  line
  line `(4) All drains and ventilation shafts, pipes and all appliances and fittings connected with the drainage`
  line `works constructed, erected or set up out of the New Delhi Municipal Fund in or upon premises not`
  line `belonging to the Council whether--`
  line
  line `(a) before or after the commencement of this Act, and`
  line
  line `(b) for the use of the owner or occupier of such premises or not,`
  line
  line `shall, unless the Council has otherwise determined, or does at any time otherwise determine, vest and be`
  line `deemed always to have vested in the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (48567)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 172
  title `Control of drains and sewage collection works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48567&sectionno=172&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `(1) All municipal drains, all sewage`
  line `collection and all works, materials and things appertaining thereto shall be under the control of the`
  line Chairperson.
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall maintain and keep in repair all municipal drains and sewage collection`
  line `works and when authorised by the council, shall construct as many new drains and sewage collection`
  line `works as may from time to time be necessary for effectual drainage and sewage collection.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (48568)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 173
  title `Certain matters not to be passed into municipal drains.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48568&sectionno=173&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall throw, empty,`
  line `or turn into any municipal drain or into any drain communicating with a municipal drain--`
  line
  line `(a) any matter likely to injure the drain or to interfere with the free flow of its contents, or to`
  line `affect prejudicially the treatment and disposal of its contents; or`
  line
  line `(b) any chemical, refuse or waste steam, or any liquid of a temperature higher than forty-five`
  line `degrees centigrade, being refuse or steam which, or a liquid which when so heated, is, either alone or`
  line `in combination with the contents of the drain, dangerous, or the cause of a nuisance, or prejudicial to`
  line `health; or`
  line
  line `(c) any dangerous petroleum.`
  line
  line `(2) In this section, the expression "dangerous petroleum" has the same meaning as in the Petroleum`
  line `Act, 1934 (30 of 1934).`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (48569)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 174
  title `Application by owners and occupiers to drain into municipal drains.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48569&sectionno=174&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf, the owner or occupier of any premises`
  line `having a private drain, or the owner of any private drain within New Delhi may apply to the Chairperson`
  line `to have his drain made to communicate with the municipal drains and thereby to discharge foul water and`
  line `surface water from those premises or that private drain:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall entitle any person--`
  line
  line `(a) to discharge directly or indirectly into any municipal drain--`
  line
  line `(i) any trade effluent from any trade premises except in accordance with bye-laws made in`
  line `this behalf; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any liquid or other matter the discharge of which into municipal drains is prohibited by or`
  line `under this Act or any other law; or`
  line
  line `(b) where separate municipal drains are provided for foul water and for surface water to discharge`
  line `directly or indirectly--`
  line
  line `(i) foul water into a drain provided for surface water; or`
  line
  line `(ii) except with the permission of the Chairperson, surface water into a drain provided for`
  line `foul water; or`
  line
  line `(c) to have his drains made to communicate directly with a strom-water overflow drain.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person desirous of availing himself of the provisions of sub-section (1) shall give to the`
  line `Chairperson notice of his proposals, and at any time within one month after receipt thereof, the`
  line `Chairperson may by notice to him refuse to permit the communication to be made, if it appears to him`
  line `that the mode of construction or condition of the drain is such that the making of the communication`
  line `would be prejudicial to the drainage system, and for the purpose of examining the mode of construction`
  line `and condition of the drain he may, if necessary, require it to be laid open for inspection.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson may, if he thinks fit, construct such parts of the work necessary for having a`
  line `private drain made to communicate with a municipal drain, as is in or under a public street and in such a`
  line `case, the expenses incurred by the Chairperson shall be paid by the owner or occupier of the premises, or`
  line `as the case may be, the owner of the private drain and shall be recoverable from the owner or occupier as`
  line `an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (48570)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 175
  title `Drainage of and drained premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48570&sectionno=175&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `drainage and a municipal drain or some place approved`
  line `by the Chairperson for the discharge of filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter is situated at a`
  line `distance of not exceeding thirty meters from any part of the said premises, he may, by written notice,`
  line `require the owner of the said premises--`
  line
  line `(a) to make a drain emptying into such municipal drain or place;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide and set up all such appliances and fittings as may appear to the Chairperson`
  line `necessary for the purposes of gathering and receiving the filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter from, and conveying the same off, the said premises and of effectually flushing such drain and`
  line `every fixture connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(c) to remove any existing drain or other appliance or thing used or intended to be used for`
  line `drainage which is injurious to health;`
  line
  line `(d) to provide a closed drain in substitution of an open drain or to provide such other appliance or`
  line `thing either newly or in substitution of any existing appliance or thing or to provide both a close drain`
  line `and such other appliance or thing in substitution of the existing open drain and other appliance or`
  line `thing, which is or is likely to be injurious to health;`
  line
  line `(e) to provide and set up all such appliances and fittings as may appear to the Chairperson to be`
  line `necessary for the purpose of gathering and receiving the waste water from floors and galleries of`
  line `buildings when they are washed, and conveying the same through spouts, by down-take pipes so as to`
  line `prevent such waste water from discharging directly on streets or inside any lower portion of the`
  line premises;
  line
  line `(f) to carry out any work to improve or re-model an existing drain which is inadequate,`
  line `insufficient or faulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in any case not provided for in sub-section (1) any premises are, in the opinion of the`
  line `Chairperson, without sufficient means of effectual drainage, he may, by written notice, require the owner`
  line `of the premises--`
  line
  line `(a) to construct a drain up to a point to be prescribed in such notice but not at a distance of more`
  line `than thirty meters from any part of the premises; or`
  line
  line `(b) to construct a closed cesspool or soakage pit and drain or drains emptying into such cesspool`
  line `or soakage pit.`
  line
  line `(3) Any requisition for the construction of any drain under sub-section (2) may contain any of the`
  line `details specified in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (48571)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 176
  title `New premises not to be erected without drains.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48571&sectionno=176&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall not be lawful to erect or to`
  line `re-erect any premises in New Delhi or to occupy any such premises unless--`
  line
  line `(a) a drain be constructed of such size, materials and description, at such level and with such fall`
  line `as shall appear to the Chairperson to be necessary for the effectual drainage of such premises;`
  line
  line `(b) there have been provided and set up on such premises such appliances and fittings as may`
  line `appear to the Chairperson to be necessary for the purposes of gathering or receiving the filth and other`
  line `polluted and obnoxious matter from, and conveying the same off, the said premises and of effectually`
  line `flushing the drain of the said premises and every fixture connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(2) The drain so constructed shall empty into a municipal drain situated at a distance of not exceeding`
  line `thirty meters from the premises; but if no municipal drain is situated within that distance then such drain`
  line `shall empty into a cesspool situated within that distance to be specified by the Chairperson for the`
  line purpose.
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (48572)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 177
  title `Power to drain group or block of premises by combined operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48572&sectionno=177&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the`
  line `Chairperson that any group or block of premises may be drained more economically or advantageously in`
  line `combination than separately, and a municipal drain of sufficient size already exists or is about to be`
  line `constructed within thirty meters of any part of that group or block of premises, the Chairperson may cause`
  line `that group or block of premises to be drained by a combined operation.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenses incurred in carrying out any work under sub-section (1) in respect of any group or`
  line `block of premises shall be paid by the owners of such premises in such proportions as the Chairperson`
  line `may determine and shall be recoverable from them as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Not less than fifteen days before any such work is commenced, the Chairperson shall give to each`
  line `such owner--`
  line
  line `(a) written notice of the nature of the proposed work, and`
  line
  line `(b) an estimate of the expenses to be incurred in respect thereof and of the proportion of such`
  line `expenses payable by him.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson may require the owners of such groups or block of premises to maintain the work`
  line `executed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (48573)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 178
  title `Power of Chairperson to close or limit the use of private drains in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48573&sectionno=178&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `Where a`
  line `drain connecting any premises with a municipal drain is sufficient for the effectual drainage of such`
  line `premises and is otherwise unobjectionable but is not in the opinion of the Chairperson, adapted to the`
  line `general system of drainage in New Delhi, he may, by written notice addressed to the owner of the`
  line `premises, direct--`
  line
  line `(a) that such drain be closed, discontinued or destroyed and that any work necessary for that`
  line `purpose be done; or`
  line
  line `(b) that such drain shall, from such date as may be specified in the notice in this behalf, be used`
  line `for filth and polluted water only or for rain water and unpolluted sub-soil water only:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) no drain may be closed, discontinued or destroyed by the Chairperson under clause (a) except`
  line `on condition of his providing another drain equally effectual for the drainage of the premises and`
  line `communicating with any municipal drain which he thinks fit; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the expenses of the construction of any drain so provided by the Council and of any work`
  line `done under clause (a) may be paid out of the New Delhi Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (48574)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 179
  title `Use of drain by a person other than the owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48574&sectionno=179&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Chairperson either on receipt`
  line `of an application from the owner of any premises or otherwise is of the opinion that the only, or the most`
  line `convenient means of effectual drainage of the premises into a municipal drain is through a drain`
  line `belonging to another person, the Chairperson may by notice in writing require the owner of such drain to`
  line `show cause within a period specified in the notice as to why an order under this section should not be`
  line made.
  line
  line `(2) Where no cause is shown within the specified period or the cause shown appears to the`
  line `Chairperson invalid or insufficient, the Chairperson may by order in writing either authorise the owner of`
  line `the premises to use the drain or declare him to be a joint owner thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) An order made under sub-section (2) may contain directions as to--`
  line
  line `(a) the payment of rent or compensation by the owner of the premises;`
  line
  line `(b) the construction of a drain for the premises for the purpose of connecting it with the aforesaid`
  line drain;
  line
  line `(c) the entry upon the land in which the aforesaid drain is situate with assistants and workmen at`
  line `all reasonable hours;`
  line
  line `(d) the respective responsibilities of the parties for maintaining, repairing, flushing, cleaning and`
  line `emptying the aforesaid drain.`
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (48575)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 180
  title `Sewage and rain water drains to be distinct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48575&sectionno=180&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it is provided in this Chapter that`
  line `steps shall or may be taken for the effectual drainage of any premises, it shall be competent to the`
  line `Chairperson to require that there shall be one drain for filth and polluted water and an entirely distinct`
  line `drain for rain water and unpolluted sub-soil water or both rain water and unpolluted sub-soil water, each`
  line `emptying into separate municipal drains or other suitable places.`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (48576)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 181
  title `Power of Chairperson to require owner to carry out certain works for satisfactory drainage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48576&sectionno=181&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of efficient drainage of any premises, the Chairperson may, by notice in`
  line writing--
  line
  line `(a) require any courtyard, alley or passage between two or more buildings to be paved by the`
  line `owner or owners of such buildings with such materials and in such manner as may be approved by the`
  line `Chairperson, and`
  line
  line `(b) require such paving to be kept in proper repair.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (48577)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 182
  title `Appointment of places for the emptying of drains and collection of sewage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48577&sectionno=182&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Chairperson may cause any or all of the municipal drains to empty into, and all sewage to be collected of`
  line `at, such place or places as he considers suitable:`
  line
  line `Provided that no place which has not been before the commencement of this Act used for any of the`
  line `purposes specified in this section shall, after such commencement be used therefor without the approval`
  line `of the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided further that on and after such date as may be appointed by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf no sewage shall be discharged into any water course until it has been so treated as not to affect`
  line `prejudicially the purity and quality of the water into which it is discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (48578)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 183
  title `Connection with water works and drains not to be made without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48578&sectionno=183&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `Without the`
  line `written permission of the Chairperson, no person shall, for any purpose whatsoever, at any time make or`
  line `cause to be made any connection or communication with any drain referred to in section 172 or any water`
  line `works, constructed or maintained by, or vested in, the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (48821)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 184
  title `Building, railways and private streets not to be erected or constructed over drains or water works without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48821&sectionno=184&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without the written permission of the Chairperson no railway or private`
  line `street shall be constructed and no building, wall, fence or other structure shall be erected on any`
  line `municipal drain or on any water works constructed or maintained by, or vested in, the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) If any railway or private street be constructed or any building, wall, fence or structure erected on`
  line `any drain or water works as aforesaid without the written permission of the Chairperson, the Chairperson`
  line `may remove or otherwise deal with the same as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses incurred by the Chairperson in so doing shall be paid by the owner of the private`
  line `street or of the building, fence, wall or other structure or, as the case may be, by the railway`
  line `administration or the person offending and shall be recoverable as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (48580)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 185
  title `Rights of user of property for aqueducts, lines, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48580&sectionno=185&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may place and`
  line `maintain aqueducts, conduits and lines of mains or pipes or drains over, under, along or across any`
  line `immovable property whether within or without the local limits of the Council without acquiring the same,`
  line `and may at any time for the purpose of examining, repairing, altering or removing any aqueducts,`
  line `conduits or lines of mains or pipes or drains, enter on any property over, under, along or across which the`
  line `aqueducts, conduits or lines of mains or pipes, or drains have been placed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council shall not acquire any right other than a right of user in the property over,`
  line `under, along or across which any aqueduct, conduit or line of mains or pipes, or drain is placed.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers conferred by sub-section (1) shall not be exercisable in respect of any property vested`
  line `in the Union or under the control or management of the Central Government or railway administration or`
  line `vested in any local authority save with the permission of the Central Government or railway`
  line `administration or the local authority, as the case may be, and in accordance with any bye-laws made in`
  line `this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson may, without such permission, repair, renew or amend any existing`
  line `works of which the character or position is not to be altered if such repair, renewal or amendment is`
  line `urgently necessary in order to maintain without interruption the supply of water, drainage or collection of`
  line `sewage or is such that delay would be dangerous to health, human life or property.`
  line
  line `(3) In exercise of the powers conferred upon him by this section, the Chairperson shall cause as little`
  line `damage and inconvenience as may be possible, and shall make full compensation for any damage or`
  line `inconvenience caused by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (48581)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 186
  title `Power of owner of premises to place pipes and drains through land belonging to other persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48581&sectionno=186&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the Chairperson that the only or most convenient means of water supply to,`
  line `and drainage of, any premises is by placing or carrying any pipe or drains over, under, along or across the immovable property of another person, the Chairperson may, by order in writing, authorise the owner of`
  line `the premises to place or carry such pipe or drain over, under, along or across such immovable property:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any such order the Chairperson shall give to the owner of the immovable`
  line `property a reasonable opportunity of showing cause within such time as may be prescribed by bye-laws`
  line `made in this behalf as to why the order should not be made:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the owner of the premises shall not acquire any right other than a right of user in`
  line `the property over, under, along or across which any such pipe or drain is placed or carried.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the making of an order, under sub-section (1), the owner of the premises may, after giving`
  line `reasonable notice of his intention so to do, enter upon the immovable property with assistants and`
  line `workmen at any time between sunrise and sunset for the purpose of placing a pipe or drain over, under,`
  line `along or across such immovable property or for the purpose of repairing the same.`
  line
  line `(3) In placing or carrying a pipe or drain under this section, as little damage as possible shall be done`
  line `to the immovable property and the owner of the premises shall--`
  line
  line `(a) cause the pipe or drain to be placed or carried with the least practicable delay;`
  line
  line `(b) fill in, re-instate and make good at his own cost and with the least practicable delay, any land`
  line `opened, broken up or removed for the purpose of placing or carrying such pipe or drain; and`
  line
  line `(c) pay compensation to the owner of the immovable property and to any other person who`
  line `sustains damage by reason of the placing or carrying of such pipe or drain.`
  line
  line `(4) If the owner of the immovable property, over, under, along or across which a pipe or drain has`
  line `been placed or carried under this section whilst such immovable property was not built upon, desires to`
  line `erect any building on such property, the Chairperson shall, by notice in writing, require the owner of the`
  line `premises to close, remove or divert the pipe or drain in such manner as shall be approved by him and to`
  line `fill in, re-instate and make good the immovable property as if the pipe or drain had not been placed or`
  line `carried over, under, along or across the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such requisition shall be made unless in the opinion of the Chairperson it is`
  line `necessary or expedient for the construction of the proposed building or the safe enjoyment thereof that the`
  line `pipe or drain should be closed, removed or diverted.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (48582)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 187
  title `Power to require railway level, etc., to be raised or lowered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48582&sectionno=187&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `If the Council places or carries`
  line `any pipe or drain or does any other work connected with the water supply or drainage across any railway`
  line `line, it may, with the sanction of the Central Government and at the cost of the New Delhi Municipal`
  line `Fund, require the railway administration to raise or lower the level thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (48583)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 188
  title `Power of Chairperson to execute work after giving notice to the person liable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48583&sectionno=188&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `(1) When`
  line `under the provisions of this Chapter any person may be required or is liable to execute any work, the`
  line `Chairperson may, in accordance with the provisions of this Act and of any bye-laws made in this behalf,`
  line `cause such work to be executed after giving such person an opportunity of executing the same within such`
  line `time as may be specified by him for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenses incurred or likely to be incurred by the Chairperson in the execution of any such`
  line `work shall be payable by the said person and the expenses incurred by the Chairperson in connection with`
  line `the maintenance of such work or the enjoyment of amenities and conveniences rendered possible by such`
  line `work shall be payable by the person or persons enjoying such amenities and conveniences.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses referred to in sub-section (2) shall be recoverable from the person or persons liable`
  line `therefor as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (48584)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 189
  title `Power of Chairperson to affix shafts, etc., for ventilation of drain or cesspool.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48584&sectionno=189&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `For the`
  line `purpose of ventilating any drain or cesspool, whether vested in Council or not, the Chairperson may, in`
  line `accordance with bye-laws made in this behalf, erect upon any premises or affix to the outside of any`
  line `building or to any tree any such shaft or pipe as may appear to him to be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (48585)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 190
  title `Power of Chairperson to examine and test drains, etc., believed to be defective.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48585&sectionno=190&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where`
  line `it appears to the Chairperson that there are reasonable grounds for believing that a private drain or`
  line `cesspool is in such condition as to be prejudicial to health or a nuisance or that a private drain communicating directly or indirectly with a municipal drain is so defective as to admit sub-soil water, he`
  line `may examine its condition, and for that purpose may apply any test, other than a test by water under`
  line `pressure, and if he deems it necessary, open the ground.`
  line
  line `(2) If on examination the drain or cesspool is found to be in proper condition, the Chairperson shall,`
  line `as soon as possible, re-instate any ground which has been opened by him and make good any damage`
  line `done by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (48586)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 191
  title `Bulk receipt of water and delivery of sewage by the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48586&sectionno=191&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall receive`
  line `bulk supply of water from, and deliver in bulk all the sewage to, the authority prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall be entitled to receive bulk supply of water from, and to deliver in bulk all the`
  line `sewage to, the authority prescribed under sub-section (1) subject to such charges for the supply of water`
  line `in bulk to the Council and the delivery of sewage of the area of New Delhi as may be determined by`
  line `means of an agreement entered into between that other authority and the Council. The agreement`
  line `mentioned in this sub-section shall provide also for a stipulation therein that in case of any dispute about`
  line `the payments to be made to that other authority by the Council, the matter shall be referred to the Central`
  line `Government whose decision thereon shall be final and binding on both parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (48587)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 192
  title `Employment of Government agencies for repairs, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48587&sectionno=192&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may for`
  line `reason to be recorded, direct that any specified work, repair, renewal or replacement which is to be`
  line `undertaken by or for the Council under this Chapter, shall be carried out on behalf of the Council by the`
  line `Central Government and the Council shall pay the charges therefor at the rates and subject to the terms for`
  line `the time being applicable in the case of works constructed by that Government on behalf of a local`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (48588)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 193
  title `Work to be done by licensed plumber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48588&sectionno=193&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person other than a licensed plumber shall`
  line `execute any work described in this Chapter and no person shall permit any such work to be executed`
  line `except by a licensed plumber:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, in the opinion of the Chairperson, the work is of a trivial nature, he may grant`
  line `permission in writing for the execution of such work by a person other than a licensed plumber.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who employs a licensed plumber to execute any work shall, when so required,`
  line `furnish to the Chairperson the name of such plumber.`
  line
  line `(3) When any work is executed except in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1), such`
  line `work shall be liable to be dismantled at the discretion of the Chairperson without prejudice to the right of`
  line `the Council to prosecute under this Act the person at whose instance such work has been executed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council may make bye-laws for the guidance of licensed plumbers and a copy of all such`
  line `bye-laws shall be attached to every licence granted to a plumber by the Council.`
  line
  line `(5) The Council may, from time to time, prescribe the charges to be paid to licensed plumbers for any`
  line `work done by them under or for any of the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(6) No licensed plumber shall, for any work referred to in sub-section (5), demand or receive more`
  line `than the charges prescribed therefor, under that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(7) The Council shall make bye-laws providing for--`
  line
  line `(a) the exercise of adequate control on all licensed plumbers;`
  line
  line `(b) the inspection of all works carried out by them; and`
  line
  line `(c) the hearing and disposal of complaints made by the owners or occupiers of premises with`
  line `regard to the quality of work done, material used, delay in execution of work, and the charges made,`
  line `by a licensed plumber.`
  line
  line `(8) No licensed plumber shall contravene any of the bye-laws made under this section or execute`
  line `carelessly or negligently any work under this Act or make use of bad materials appliances or fittings.`
  line
  line `(9) If any licensed plumber contravenes sub-section (8), his licence may be suspended or cancelled`
  line `whether he is prosecuted under this Act or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (48589)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 194
  title `Prohibition of certain acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48589&sectionno=194&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall--`
  line
  line `(a) wilfully obstruct any person acting under the authority of the Council, or the Chairperson, in`
  line `setting out the lines of any works or pull up or remove any pillar, post or stake fixed in the ground for`
  line `the purpose of setting out lines of such work, or deface or destroy any works made for the same`
  line `purpose; or`
  line
  line `(b) wilfully or negligently break, injure, turn on, open, close, shut off or otherwise interfere with`
  line `any lock, cock, valve, pipe, meter or other work or apparatus belonging to the Council; or`
  line
  line `(c) unlawfully obstruct the flow of or flush, draw off, or divert, or take water from any water`
  line `work belonging to the Council; or`
  line
  line `(d) unlawfully obstruct the flow of, or flush, draw off, divert or take sewage from any sewage`
  line `work belonging to the Council or break or damage any electrical transmission line maintained by the`
  line `Council; or`
  line
  line `(e) obstruct any officer or other employee of the Council in the discharge of his duties under this`
  line `Chapter or refuse or wilfully neglect to furnish him with the means necessary for the making of any`
  line `entry, inspection, examination or inquiry thereunder in relation to any water or sewage work; or`
  line
  line `(f) bathe in, at or upon any water work or wash or throw or cause to enter therein any animal, or`
  line `throw any rubbish, dirt or filth into any water work or wash or clean therein any cloth, wool or leather`
  line `or the skin of any animal, or cause the water of any sink, or drain or any steam-engine or boiler or any`
  line `polluted water to turn or be brought into any water work, or do any other act whereby the water in any`
  line `water work is fouled or likely to be fouled.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall apply to a consumer closing the stopcock fixed on`
  line `the service pipe supplying water to his premises so long as he has obtained the consent of any other`
  line `consumer whose supply will be affected thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (48590)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 195
  title `Functions in relation to electricity supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48590&sectionno=195&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Council to develop`
  line `and maintain an efficient, co-ordinated and economical system of electricity supply for New Delhi area`
  line `under its jurisdiction and for that purpose to take steps from time to time--`
  line
  line `(a) acquiring supplies of electricity and its distribution to consumers;`
  line
  line `(b) for preparing and carrying out in accordance with rules made in this behalf schemes for`
  line `distribution of electricity.`
  line
  line `(2) In the discharge of its functions in relation to electricity supply, the Council shall, as far as`
  line practicable--
  line
  line `(a) promote the use of all economical methods of transmitting and distributing electricity;`
  line
  line `(b) secure the development of supplies of electricity;`
  line
  line `(c) secure the extension of supplies of electricity to areas without such supplies;`
  line
  line `(d) promote the standardisation of systems of supply and types of electrical fittings;`
  line
  line `(e) promote the simplification and standardisation of methods of charge for supplies of electricity.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (48591)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 196
  title `Additional functions in relation to electricity supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48591&sectionno=196&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may take steps to`
  line `manufacture, purchase, sell or let on hire on the execution of a hire purchase agreement or otherwise, any`
  line `electrical machinery, control gear, fittings, wires or apparatus for lighting, heating, cooling or motive`
  line `power or for any other purpose for which electricity can or may be used, or any industrial or agricultural`
  line `machinery operated by electricity, and to install, connect, repair, maintain or remove such machinery,`
  line `control gear, fitting, wires or apparatus and in respect thereof demand and take such remuneration or rents`
  line `and charges and make such terms and conditions as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may also maintain shops and show rooms for the display, sale or hire of machinery,`
  line `control gear, fittings, wires or apparatus as aforesaid, conduct displays, exhibitions and demonstrations thereof and generally do all things, including advertising incidental to the sale or hire of such machinery,`
  line `control gear, fittings, wires and apparatus and to the promotion and encouragement of the use of`
  line electricity.
  line
  line `(3) Moneys received and expended in connection with additional functions specified in`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be shown separately in the accounts.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (48592)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 197
  title `Council to have powers and obligations of licensee under Act 9 of 1910.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48592&sectionno=197&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `provision of this Act the Council shall in respect of the New Delhi areas under its jurisdiction have all the`
  line `powers and obligations of a licensee under the Electricity Act, 1910, and this Chapter shall be deemed to`
  line `be the licence of the Council for the purposes of that Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in sections 3 to 12 of, or in clauses I to IX of the Schedule to, that Act relating`
  line `to the duties and obligations of a licensee shall apply to the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (48593)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 198
  title `Restriction on building and other acts interfering with the works of electric supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48593&sectionno=198&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `(1) No building, wall or other structure shall be newly erected and no street or railway shall be`
  line `constructed over, or in such a manner as to interfere with, any work constructed or maintained for the`
  line `purposes of the electric supply except with the written permission of the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may cause any building, wall or other structure erected, or any street or railway`
  line `constructed in contravention of sub-section (1), to be removed or otherwise dealt with as he deems fit, and`
  line `the expenses incurred therefor shall be paid by the person or authority responsible and shall be`
  line `recoverable from such person or authority as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (48594)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 199
  title `Power of Council to make arrangements with licensees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48594&sectionno=199&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may enter into an`
  line `agreement with any licensee within or outside New Delhi in regard to the purchase of electricity and price`
  line `thereof and within New Delhi in regard to sale and price thereof or in regard to operation or control of any`
  line `generating station or main transmission line and notwithstanding anything contained in any law or in any`
  line `licence, memorandum of association or other instrument regulating the constitution and powers of the`
  line `licensee, it shall be lawful for the licensee to enter into and carry out any agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) In entering into an agreement under this section the Council shall not show any undue preference`
  line `to any licensee.`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (48595)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 200
  title `Charges for supply of electricity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48595&sectionno=200&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of any law for the time being in`
  line `force, charges shall be leviable for the supply of electricity by the Council at such rates as may, from time`
  line `to time, be fixed by the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (48596)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 201
  title `Bulk receipt of electricity by the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48596&sectionno=201&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall receive bulk supply of`
  line `electricity from the authority which may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall be entitled to receive bulk supply of electricity from that authority prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government subject to such terms and conditions as may be determined by means of a`
  line `contract entered into between that other authority and the Council. The contract mentioned in this`
  line `sub-section shall provide also for a stipulation therein that disputes between that other authority and the`
  line `Council in regard to any matter relating to the bulk supply of electricity to the Council shall be referred to`
  line `the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final and binding on both parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (48597)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 202
  title `Vesting of public streets in the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48597&sectionno=202&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `(1) All streets within New Delhi which are or at any`
  line `time become public streets and the pavements, stones and other materials thereof shall vest in the`
  line `Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that no public street which immediately before the commencement of this Act vested in the`
  line `Union shall, unless the Central Government with the consent of the Council so directs, vest in the Council`
  line `by virtue of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) All public streets vesting in the Council shall be under the control of the Chairperson and shall be`
  line `maintained, controlled and regulated by him in accordance with the bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (48598)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 203
  title `Functions of Chairperson in respect of public streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48598&sectionno=203&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall, from time`
  line `to time, cause all public streets vested in the Council to be levelled, metalled or paved, channelled, altered`
  line `or repaired, and may widen, extend or otherwise improve any such street or cause the soil thereof to be`
  line `raised, lowered or altered or may place and keep in repair fences and posts for the safety of foot`
  line `passengers:`
  line
  line `Provided that no widening, extension or other improvement of a public street, the aggregate cost of`
  line `which will exceed one lakh rupees, shall be undertaken by the Chairperson except with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) With the previous sanction of the Council, the Chairperson may permanently close the whole or`
  line `any part of a public street:`
  line
  line `Provided that before according such sanction the Council shall by notice, published in the manner`
  line `specified by bye-laws give reasonable opportunity to the residents likely to be affected by such closure to`
  line `make suggestions or objections with respect to such closure and shall consider all such suggestions or`
  line `objections which may be made within one month from the date of publication of the said notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (48599)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 204
  title `Disposal of land forming site of public streets permanently closed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48599&sectionno=204&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any public`
  line `street or a part thereof is permanently closed under sub-section (2) of section 203 the site of such street or`
  line `of the portion thereof may be disposed of as land vesting in the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (48600)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 205
  title `Power to make new public streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48600&sectionno=205&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may at any time with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Council,--`
  line
  line `(a) lay out and make new public streets;`
  line
  line `(b) construct bridges and sub-ways;`
  line
  line `(c) turn or divert any existing public street; and`
  line
  line `(d) lay down and determine the position and direction of a street or streets in any part of New`
  line `Delhi notwithstanding that no proposal for the erection of any building in the vicinity has been`
  line received.
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (48601)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 206
  title `Minimum width of new public streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48601&sectionno=206&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall, from time to time, with the`
  line `sanction of council, specify the minimum width of different classes of new public streets according to the`
  line `nature of the traffic likely to be carried thereon, and the streets with which they join at one or both ends,`
  line `the localities in which they are situated, the heights up to which buildings abutting thereon may be erected`
  line `and other similar considerations.`
obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (48602)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 207
  title `Power to prohibit or regulate use of public streets for certain kind of traffic.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48602&sectionno=207&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Chairperson may--`
  line
  line `(a) prohibit or regulate vehicular traffic in any public street or any portion thereof so as to prevent`
  line `danger, obstruction or inconvenience to the public or to ensure decongestion or smooth flow or`
  line `quietness in any locality;`
  line
  line `(b) prohibit or regulate in respect of all public streets, or any particular public street, the transit of`
  line `any vehicle of such form, construction weight or size or laden with such heavy or unwieldly objects`
  line `as may be likely to cause injury to the road-ways or any construction thereon, except under such`
  line `conditions as to time, mode of traction or locomotion, use of appliances for the protection of`
  line `roadways, number of lights and assistants and other general precautions and upon the payment of`
  line `such charges as may be specified by the Chairperson generally or specially in each case; and`
  line
  line `(c) prohibit or regulate access to premises from any particular public street carrying high speed`
  line `vehicular traffic:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson shall not take action without sanction of the Council in cases under`
  line `clauses (a) and (c).`
  line
  line `(2) Notices of such prohibition as are imposed under sub-section (1) shall be posted in conspicuous`
  line `places at or near both ends of public streets or portions thereof to which they relate, unless such`
  line `prohibition applies generally to all public streets.`
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (48603)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 208
  title `Power to acquire lands and buildings for public streets and for public parking places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48603&sectionno=208&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions contained in Chapter X, the Chairperson may--`
  line
  line `(a) acquire any land required for the purpose of opening, widening, extending or otherwise`
  line `improving any public street or of making any new public street, and any building standing upon such`
  line land;
  line
  line `(b) acquire in relation to any such land or building, all such land with buildings, if any, thereon as`
  line `the Council may think expedient to acquire outside of the regular line, or of the intended regular line,`
  line `of such street;`
  line
  line `(c) acquire any land for the purpose of laying out or making a public parking place.`
obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (48604)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 209
  title `Defining the regular line of streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48604&sectionno=209&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may define a line on one or both`
  line `sides of any public street in accordance with the bye-laws made in this behalf and may, with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Council, redefine at any time any such regular line:`
  line
  line `Provided that, before according sanction the Council shall by public notice afford reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the residents or premises abutting on such public street to make suggestions or objections`
  line `with respect to the proposed redefined line of the street and shall consider all such suggestions or`
  line `objections which may be made within one month from the date of the publication of the said notice:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the regular line of any public street operative under any law in force in any part`
  line `of New Delhi immediately before the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to be a line defined by`
  line `the Chairperson under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The line for the time being defined or redefined shall be called the regular line of street.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall construct or reconstruct any building or a portion thereof or any boundary wall or`
  line `other structure whatsoever within the regular line of a street except with the written permission of the`
  line `Chairperson:`
  line
  line `Provided that if within sixty days after the receipt of application from any person for permission to`
  line `construct or reconstruct a boundary wall or portion thereof, the Chairperson fails to take steps to acquire`
  line `the land within the regular line of the street in the accordance with section 212, then that person may,`
  line `subject to any other provisions of this Act and the bye-laws made thereunder, proceed with the work of`
  line `construction or reconstruction of such boundary wall or portion thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) When the Chairperson grants permission for the construction or reconstruction of any building or`
  line `any boundary wall or other structure within the regular line of a street, he may require the owner of the`
  line `building to execute an agreement binding himself and his successors-in-interest not to claim`
  line `compensation in the event of the Chairperson at any time thereafter calling upon him or any of his`
  line `successors by written notice to remove any work carried out in pursuance of such permission and to pay`
  line `the expenses of such removal if, in default, such removal is carried out by the Chairperson and may for`
  line `that purpose require such owner to deposit in the New Delhi Municipal Fund such sum as may be`
  line `determined by him.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson shall maintain--`
  line
  line `(a) a register containing such particulars as may be specified by him in this behalf with plans`
  line `attached thereto showing all public streets in respect of which the regular line of the street has been`
  line `defined or redefined and containing any other particulars which the Chairperson may deem necessary;`
  line
  line `(b) a register of all agreements executed under sub-section (4) and of all deposits made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(6) All such registers shall be open to inspection by any person on payment of such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Chairperson with the sanction of Council.`
  line
  line `(7) Any agreement entered into in pursuance of sub-section (4) shall be in writing, shall be registered`
  line `under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), and shall be deemed to be an agreement in respect of the land to which it relates and any condition contained in such agreement shall be deemed to be an`
  line `obligation annexed to the ownership of the said land and enforceable against the successors-in-interest of`
  line `the owner of such land`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210:
  sectionId (48605)
  sectionNo (210)
  orderNo 210
  title `Setting back building to regular line of street.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48605&sectionno=210&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any part of a building abutting on a`
  line `public street is within the regular line of that street, the Chairperson may, whenever it is proposed--`
  line
  line `(a) to repair, rebuild or construct such building or to take down such building to an extent`
  line `exceeding one-half thereof above the ground level, such half to be measured in cubic metres; or`
  line
  line `(b) to repair, remove, construct or reconstruct or make any additions to, or structural alterations`
  line `of, any portion of such building which is within the regular line of the street,`
  line
  line `by any order which he issues concerning the addition to, rebuilding construction, repair or alterations of,`
  line `such building, require such building to be set back to the regular line of the street.`
  line
  line `(2) When any building or any part thereof within the regular line of a public street falls down or is`
  line `burnt down or is, whether by the order of the Chairperson or otherwise, taken down, the Chairperson may`
  line `forthwith take possession on behalf of the Council of the portion of the land within the regular line of the`
  line `street therefor occupied by the said building and, if necessary, clear the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Land acquired under this section shall be deemed to be part of the public street and shall vest in`
  line `the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_211:
  sectionId (48606)
  sectionNo (211)
  orderNo 211
  title `Compulsory setting back of building to regular line of street.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48606&sectionno=211&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any building or`
  line `any part thereof is within the regular line of a public street and in the opinion of the Chairperson it is`
  line `necessary to set back the building or part thereof to the regular line of the street he may, by notice served`
  line `on the owner in accordance with the provisions of this Act, require him to show cause within such period`
  line `as may be specified in the notice as to why such building or part thereof which is within the regular line`
  line `of the street should not be pulled down and the land within the regular line acquired by the Chairperson`
  line `on behalf of the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) If such owner fails to show cause as required by sub-section (1) the Chairperson may require the`
  line `owner by another notice to be served on him in accordance with the provisions of this Act, to pull down`
  line `the building or part thereof which is within the regular line of the street within such period as is specified`
  line `in the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) If within such period the owner of the building fails to pull down the building or part thereof as`
  line `required by the Chairperson, the Chairperson may pull down the same and all the expenses incurred in so`
  line `doing shall be paid by the owner and recoverable from him as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson shall at once take possession on behalf of the Council of the portion of the land`
  line `within the regular line of the street occupied by the said building or part thereof and such land shall`
  line `thereupon be deemed to be part of the public street and shall vest in the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_212:
  sectionId (48607)
  sectionNo (212)
  orderNo 212
  title `Acquisition of open land and land occupied by platform, etc., within the regular line of street.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_212_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48607&sectionno=212&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line `If any land, whether open or enclosed, not vesting in the Council and not occupied by any`
  line `building is within the regular line of a public street or if a platform, verandah, step, compound wall, hedge`
  line `or fence or some other structure external to a building abutting on a public street or a portion of such`
  line `platform, verandah, step, compound wall, hedge, fence or other structure is within the regular line of such`
  line `street, the Chairperson may, after giving to the owner of the land or building not less than seven clear`
  line `days' notice of his intention so to do, take possession on behalf of the Council of the said land with its`
  line `enclosing wall, hedge or fence, if any, or of the said platform, verandah, step, compound wall, hedge,`
  line `fence or other structure or of any portion thereof which is within the regular line of the public street and,`
  line `if necessary, clear the same and the land so acquired shall thereupon be deemed to be a part of the public`
  line `street and shall vest in the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the land or building is vested in the Union or a State the Chairperson shall not`
  line `take possession thereof without the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_213:
  sectionId (48822)
  sectionNo (213)
  orderNo 213
  title `Acquisition of the remaining part of a building and land after their portions within a regular line of street have been acquired.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_213_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48822&sectionno=213&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_213_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a land or building is partly within the regular line`
  line `of a public street and the Chairperson is satisfied that the land remaining after the excision of the portion`
  line `within the said line will not be suitable or fit for any beneficial use, he may, at the request of the owner,`
  line `acquire such land in addition to the land within the said line and such surplus land shall be deemed to be a`
  line `part of the public street and shall vest in the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) Such surplus land may thereafter, be utilised for the purpose of setting forward a building under`
  line `section 214.`
obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_214:
  sectionId (48609)
  sectionNo (214)
  orderNo 214
  title `Setting forward of buildings to the regular line of street.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_214_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48609&sectionno=214&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may, upon such`
  line `terms as he thinks fit, allow any building to be set forward for the purpose of improving the regular line of`
  line `a public street and may, with the approval of the Council, by notice require any building to be set forward`
  line `in the case of reconstruction thereof or of a new construction.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section a wall separating any premises from a public street`
  line `shall be deemed to be a building, and it shall be deemed a sufficient compliance with permission or`
  line `requisition to set forward a building to the regular line of a street if a wall of such material and`
  line `dimensions as are approved by the Chairperson is erected along the said line`
obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_215:
  sectionId (48610)
  sectionNo (215)
  orderNo 215
  title `Compensation to be paid in certain cases of setting back or setting forward of buildings, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48610&sectionno=215&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_215_content:
  string
  line `(1) Compensation shall be paid by the Chairperson to the owner of any building or land acquired`
  line `for a public street under the provisions of sections 210, 211 and 212 for any loss which such owner may`
  line `sustain in consequence of his building or land being so acquired and for any expense incurred by such`
  line `owner in consequence of any order made by the Chairperson:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) any increase or decrease in the value of the remainder of the property of which the building or`
  line `land so acquired formed part, likely to accrue from the setting back to the regular line of the street`
  line `shall be taken into consideration and allowed for in determining the amount of such compensation;`
  line
  line `(b) if any such increase in the value exceeds the amount of loss sustained or expenses incurred by`
  line `the owner, the Chairperson may recover from him half the amount of such excess as a betterment`
  line charge.
  line
  line `(2) If in consequence of any order to set forward a building made by the Chairperson the owner of`
  line `such building sustains any loss or damage, compensation shall be paid to him by the Chairperson for such`
  line `loss or damage after taking into account any increase in value likely to accrue from the setting forward.`
  line
  line `(3) If the additional land which will be included in the premises of any person required or permitted`
  line `under sub-section (2) to set forward a building belongs to the Council, the order or permission of the`
  line `Chairperson to set forward the building shall be a sufficient conveyance to the said owner of the said land;`
  line `and the price to be paid to the Council by the owner for such additional land and the other terms and`
  line `conditions of the conveyance shall be set forth in the order or permission.`
  line
  line `(4) If, when the Chairperson requires any building to be set forward, the owner of the building is`
  line `dissatisfied with the price fixed to be paid to the Council or with any of the terms or conditions of`
  line `conveyance, the Chairperson shall, upon the application of the owner at any time within fifteen days after`
  line `the said terms and conditions are communicated to him, refer the case for the determination of the court`
  line `of the district judge of Delhi whose decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_216:
  sectionId (48611)
  sectionNo (216)
  orderNo 216
  title `Owner's obligation when dealing with land as building sites.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_216_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48611&sectionno=216&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_216_content:
  string
  line `If the owner of any land`
  line `utilises, sells, leases out or otherwise disposes of such land for the construction of buildings thereon he`
  line `shall lay down and make a street or streets giving access to the plots into which the land may be divided`
  line `and connecting with an existing public or private street.`
obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_217:
  sectionId (48612)
  sectionNo (217)
  orderNo 217
  title `Lay-out plans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_217_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48612&sectionno=217&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before utilising, selling or otherwise dealing with any land under`
  line `section 216, the owner thereof shall send to the Chairperson a written application with a layout plan of the`
  line `land showing the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the plots into which the land is proposed to be divided for the erection of buildings thereon`
  line `and the purpose or purposes for which such buildings are to be used;`
  line
  line `(b) the reservation or allotment of any site for any street, open space, park, recreation ground,`
  line `school, market or any other public purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) the intended level, direction and width of street or streets;`
  line
  line `(d) the regular line of street or streets;`
  line
  line `(e) the arrangement to be made for levelling, paving, metalling, flagging, channelling, sewering,`
  line `draining, conserving and lighting street or streets.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Act and the bye-laws made thereunder as to width of the public streets and`
  line `the height of buildings abutting thereon, shall apply in the case of streets referred to in sub-section (1) and`
  line `all the particulars referred to in that sub-section shall be subject to the sanction of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) Within sixty days after the receipt of any application under sub-section (1) the Council shall either`
  line `accord sanction to the layout plan on such conditions as it may think fit or disallow it or ask for further`
  line `information with respect to it.`
  line
  line `(4) Such sanction shall be refused--`
  line
  line `(a) if the particulars shown in the lay-out plan would conflict with any arrangements which have`
  line `been made or which are in the opinion of the Council likely to be made for carrying out any general`
  line `scheme of development of New Delhi whether contained in the master plan or a zonal development`
  line `plan prepared for New Delhi or not; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the said lay-out plan does not conform to the provisions of this Act and bye-laws made`
  line `thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(c) if any street proposed in the plan is not designed so as to connect at one end with a street`
  line `which is already open.`
  line
  line `(5) No person shall utilise, sell or otherwise deal with any land or lay-out or make any new street`
  line `without or otherwise than in conformity with the orders of the Council and if further information is asked`
  line `for, no step shall be taken to utilise, sell or otherwise deal with the land or to lay-out or make the street`
  line `until orders have been passed upon receipt of such information:`
  line
  line `Provided that the passing of such orders shall not be in any case delayed for more than sixty days`
  line `after the Council has received the information which it considers necessary to enable it to deal with the`
  line `said application.`
  line
  line `(6) The lay-out plan referred to earlier in this section, shall be prepared by an architect.`
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_218:
  sectionId (48613)
  sectionNo (218)
  orderNo 218
  title `Alteration or demolition of street made in breach of section 217.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_218_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48613&sectionno=218&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_218_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person lays-out`
  line `or makes any street referred to in section 217 without or otherwise than in conformity with the orders of`
  line `the Council, the Chairperson may, whether or not the offender be prosecuted under this Act, by notice--`
  line
  line `(a) require the offender to show cause by a written statement signed by him and sent to the`
  line `Chairperson on or before such date as may be specified in the notice, why such street should not be`
  line `altered to the satisfaction of the Chairperson or if such alteration be impracticable, why such street`
  line `should not be demolished; or`
  line
  line `(b) require the offender to appear before the Chairperson either personally or by a duly authorised`
  line `agent on such day and at such time and place as may be specified in the notice and show cause as`
  line aforesaid.
  line
  line `(2) If any person on whom such notice is served fails to show cause to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Chairperson why such street should not be so altered or demolished, the Chairperson may pass an order`
  line `directing the alternation or demolition of such street.`
obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_219:
  sectionId (48614)
  sectionNo (219)
  orderNo 219
  title `Power of Chairperson to order work to be carried out or to carry it out himself in default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_219_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48614&sectionno=219&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_219_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any private street or part thereof is not levelled, paved, metalled, flagged, chanelled,`
  line `sewered, drained, conserved or lighted to the satisfaction of Chairperson, he may by notice require the`
  line `owners of such street or part and the owners of the lands and buildings fronting or abutting on such street`
  line `or part to carry out any work which in his opinion may be necessary, and within such time as may be`
  line `specified in such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If such work is not carried out within the time specified in the notice, the Chairperson, may, if he`
  line `thinks fit, execute it and the expenses incurred shall be paid by the owners referred to in sub-section (1) in`
  line `such proportion as may be determined by the Chairperson and shall be recoverable from them as an arrear`
  line `of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_220:
  sectionId (48615)
  sectionNo (220)
  orderNo 220
  title `Right of owner to require streets to be declared public.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_220_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48615&sectionno=220&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_220_content:
  string
  line `If any street has been levelled,`
  line `paved, metalled, flagged, channelled, sewered, drained, conserved and lighted under the provisions of`
  line `section 219, the Chairperson may, and on the requisition of a majority of the owners referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of that section shall, declare such a street to be a public street and thereupon the street`
  line `shall vest in the Council`
obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_221:
  sectionId (48616)
  sectionNo (221)
  orderNo 221
  title `Prohibition of projections upon streets, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_221_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48616&sectionno=221&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_221_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as provided in section 222, no person`
  line `shall erect, set up, add to, or place against or in front of any premises any structure or fixture which will--`
  line
  line `(a) overhang, jut or project into, or in any way encroach upon, and obstruct in any way the safe or`
  line `convenient passage of the public along any street, or`
  line
  line `(b) jut or project into or encroach upon any drain or open channel in any street so as in any way to`
  line `interfere with the use or proper working of such drain or channel or to impede the inspection or`
  line `cleansing thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may by notice require the owner or occupier of any premises to remove, or to`
  line `take such other action as he may direct in relation to, any structure or fixture which has been erected,`
  line `set up, added to or placed against, or in front of, the said premises in contravention of this section.`
  line
  line `(3) If the occupier of the said premises removes or alters any structure or fixture in accordance with`
  line `such notice, he shall be entitled, unless the structure or fixture was erected, set up or placed by himself, to`
  line `credit into account with the owner of the premises for all reasonable expenses incurred by him in`
  line `complying with the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_222:
  sectionId (48617)
  sectionNo (222)
  orderNo 222
  title `Projections over streets may be permitted in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_222_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48617&sectionno=222&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_222_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may give a`
  line `written permission, on such terms and on payment of such fee as he in each case thinks fit, to the owner`
  line `or occupier of the building abutting on any street--`
  line
  line `(i) to erect an arcade over such street or any portion thereof; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to put up a verandah, balcony, arch, connecting passage, sun-shade, weather frame, canopy,`
  line `owning or other such structure or thing projecting from any storey over or across any street or portion`
  line `thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that no permission shall be given by the Chairperson for the erection of an arcade in any`
  line `public street in which construction of an arcade has not been generally sanctioned by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may at any time by notice require the owner or occupier of any building to`
  line `remove a verandah, balcony, sun-shade, weather frame or the like put up in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of any law and such owner or occupier shall be bound to take action accordingly but shall be`
  line `entitled to compensation for the loss caused to him by such removal and the cost incurred thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_223:
  sectionId (48618)
  sectionNo (223)
  orderNo 223
  title `Ground floor doors, etc., not to open outwards on streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_223_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48618&sectionno=223&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_223_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may at any time`
  line `by notice require the owner of any premises on the ground floor of which any door, gate, bar, or window`
  line `opens outwards upon a street or upon any land required for the improvement of a street in such manner, as`
  line `in the opinion of the Chairperson, to obstruct the safe or convenient passage of the public along such`
  line `street, to have the said door, gate, bar or window altered so as not to open outwards.`
obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_224:
  sectionId (48619)
  sectionNo (224)
  orderNo 224
  title `Prohibition of structures or fixtures which cause obstruction in street.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_224_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48619&sectionno=224&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_224_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall,`
  line `except with the permission of the Chairperson granted in this behalf, erect or set up any wall, fence, rail,`
  line `post, step, booth or other structure whether fixed or movable or whether of a permanent or temporary`
  line `nature, or any fixture in or upon any street or upon or over any open channel, drain, well or tank in any`
  line `street so as to form an obstruction to, or an encroachment upon, or a projection over, or to occupy any`
  line `portion of such street, channel, drain, well or tank.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall apply to any erection or thing to which clause (c) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 229 applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_225:
  sectionId (48620)
  sectionNo (225)
  orderNo 225
  title `Prohibition of deposit, etc., of things in streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_225_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48620&sectionno=225&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_225_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, except with the`
  line `permission of the Chairperson and on payment of such fee as he in each case thinks fit, place or deposit`
  line `upon any street, or upon any open channel, drain or well in any street or upon any public place any stall,`
  line `chair, bench, box, ladder, bale, or other thing whatsoever so as to form an obstruction thereto or`
  line `encroachment thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) applies to building material`
obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_226:
  sectionId (48621)
  sectionNo (226)
  orderNo 226
  title `Power to remove anything deposited or exposed for sale in contravention of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_226_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48621&sectionno=226&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_226_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Chairperson may, without notice, cause to be removed--`
  line
  line `(a) any stall, chair, bench, box, ladder, bale, or other thing whatsoever, placed, deposited,`
  line `projected, attached or suspended in, upon, from or to any place in contravention of this Act.`
  line
  line `(b) any article whatsoever hawked or exposed for sale on any public street or in other public place`
  line `in contravention of this Act and any vehicle, package, box or any other thing in or on which such`
  line `article is placed.`
obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_227:
  sectionId (48622)
  sectionNo (227)
  orderNo 227
  title `Prohibition of the tethering of animals and milking of cattle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_227_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48622&sectionno=227&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_227_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall tether any`
  line `animal or cause or permit the same to be tethered in any public street or public place.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall milk or cause or permit to be milked any cow or buffalo in any street or public`
  line place.
  line
  line `(3) Any animal tethered or any cow or buffalo found being milked as aforesaid in any street may be`
  line `removed by the Chairperson or any municipal officer or employee and be impounded and dealt with`
  line `under the provisions of the Cattle-trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871).`
obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_228:
  sectionId (48623)
  sectionNo (228)
  orderNo 228
  title `Precautions during repair of streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_228_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48623&sectionno=228&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_228_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall, so far as is practicable,`
  line `during the construction or repair of any public street, or any municipal drain or any premises vested in the`
  line Council--
  line
  line `(a) cause the same to be fenced and guarded,`
  line
  line `(b) take proper precautions against accident by shoring up and protecting the adjoining buildings,`
  line
  line `(c) cause such bars, chains or posts to be fixed across or in any street in which any such work of`
  line `construction or repair is under execution as are necessary in order to prevent the passage of vehicles`
  line `or animals and avert danger.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall cause such street, drain or premises to be sufficiently lighted or guarded`
  line `during night while under construction or repair.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall, with all reasonable speed, cause the said work to be completed, the ground`
  line `to be filled in, the street, drain or premises to be repaired and the rubbish occasioned thereby to be`
  line removed.
  line
  line `(4) No person shall, without the permission of the Chairperson or other lawful authority, remove any`
  line `bar, chain, post or shorting, timber, or remove or extinguish any light set up under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_229:
  sectionId (48824)
  sectionNo (229)
  orderNo 229
  title `Streets not to be opened or broken up and building materials not to be deposited thereon without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_229_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48824&sectionno=229&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_229_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person other than the Chairperson or a municipal officer or other municipal`
  line `employee shall, without the written permission of the Chairperson--`
  line
  line `(a) open, break up, displace, take up or make any alteration in, or cause any injury to the soil or`
  line `pavement or any wall, fence, post, chain or other materials or thing forming part of any street; or`
  line
  line `(b) deposit any building materials in any street; or`
  line
  line `(c) set up in any street any scaffold or any temporary erection for the purpose of any work`
  line `whatever, or any posts, bars, rails, boards or other things by way of an enclosure, for the purpose of`
  line `making mortar or depositing bricks, lime, rubbish or other materials.`
  line
  line `(2) Any permission granted under clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be terminable at the`
  line `discretion of the Chairperson on his giving not less than twenty-four hours' notice of such termination to`
  line `the person to whom such permission was granted.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson may, without notice, cause to be removed any of the things referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) which has been deposited or set up in any street without the permission`
  line `specified in that sub-section or which having been deposited or set up with such permission has not been`
  line `removed within the period specified in the notice issued under sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to cases under clause (b) or clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) in which an application for permission has been made with such fee as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Chairperson in this behalf but no reply has been sent to the applicant within seven days from the`
  line `date of the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_230:
  sectionId (48625)
  sectionNo (230)
  orderNo 230
  title `Disposal of things removed under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_230_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48625&sectionno=230&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_230_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any of the things caused to be removed`
  line `by the Chairperson under this Chapter shall, unless the owner thereof turns up to take back such thing and`
  line `pays to the Chairperson the charges for the removal and storage of such thing, be disposed of by the`
  line `Chairperson by public auction or in such other manner and within such time as the Chairperson thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The charges for removal and storage and sale of the thing sold under sub-section (1) shall be paid`
  line `out of the proceeds of the sale thereof and the balance, if any, shall be paid to the owner of the thing sold`
  line `on a claim being made therefor within a period of one year from the date of sale, and if no such claim is`
  line `made within the said period, shall be credited to the New Delhi Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_231:
  sectionId (48626)
  sectionNo (231)
  orderNo 231
  title `Naming and numbering of streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_231_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48626&sectionno=231&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_231_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may--`
  line
  line `(a) with the sanction of the Council determine the name or number by which any street or public`
  line `place vested in the Council shall be known;`
  line
  line `(b) cause to be put up or painted at a conspicuous part of any building, wall or place at or near`
  line `each end, corner or entrance of such street or on some convenient part of such street, the name or`
  line `number by which it is to be known;`
  line
  line `(c) cause to be put up or painted on boards of suitable size the name of any public place vested in`
  line `the Council;`
  line
  line `(d) determine the number or sub-number by which any premises or part of such premises shall be`
  line `known and cause such number or sub-number to be fixed to the side or outer door of such premises or`
  line `to some place at the entrance of the enclosure thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall destroy, remove, deface or in any way injure or alter any such name or number or`
  line `sub-number or put up or paint any name or number or sub-number different from that put up or painted by`
  line `order of the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_232:
  sectionId (48627)
  sectionNo (232)
  orderNo 232
  title `Chairperson to take steps for repairing or enclosing dangerous places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_232_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48627&sectionno=232&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_232_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any place is,`
  line `in the opinion of the Chairperson, for want of sufficient repair or protection or enclosure, or owing to`
  line `some work being carried on thereupon, dangerous or causing inconvenience to passengers along a street`
  line `or to other persons including the owner or occupier of the said place, who have legal access thereto or to`
  line `the neighbourhood thereof, the Chairperson may by notice in writing require the owner or occupier of`
  line `such place to repair, protect or enclose the same or take such other step as shall appear to the Chairperson`
  line `necessary in order to prevent the danger or inconvenience arising therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may before giving any such notice or before the period of any such notice has`
  line `expired, take such temporary measures as he thinks fit to prevent the danger or inconvenience arising therefrom; and any expense incurred by the Chairperson in taking such temporary measures shall be`
  line `recoverable from the owner or occupier of the place as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_233:
  sectionId (48628)
  sectionNo (233)
  orderNo 233
  title `Measures for lighting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_233_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48628&sectionno=233&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_233_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall--`
  line
  line `(a) take measures for lighting in a suitable manner all such public streets and public places as`
  line `may be specified by him;`
  line
  line `(b) procure, erect and maintain such number of lamps, lamp posts and other appurtenances as`
  line `may be necessary for the said purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) cause such lamps to be lighted by means of oil, electricity or such other light as he may`
  line determine.
obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_234:
  sectionId (48629)
  sectionNo (234)
  orderNo 234
  title `Prohibition of removal, etc., of lamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_234_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48629&sectionno=234&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_234_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, without lawful authority, take`
  line `away or wilfully or negligently break or throw down or damage--`
  line
  line `(a) any lamp or any appurtenance of any lamp or lamp post or lamp iron set up; in any public`
  line `street or any public place;`
  line
  line `(b) any electric wire for lighting such lamp;`
  line
  line `(c) any post, pole, standard, stay, strut, bracket or other contrivance for carrying, suspending or`
  line `supporting any electric wire or lamp.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall wilfully or negligently extinguish the light of any lamp set up in any public street`
  line `or any public place.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person wilfully or through negligence or accident breaks, or causes any damage to any of`
  line `the things described in sub-section (1) he shall in addition to any penalty to which he may be subjected`
  line `under this Act, pay the expenses of repairing the damage so done by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_235:
  sectionId (48630)
  sectionNo (235)
  orderNo 235
  title `General superintendence, etc., of the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_235_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48630&sectionno=235&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_235_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provision of this Act, the Chairperson shall exercise his powers and discharge his`
  line `functions under this Chapter, under the general superintendence, direction and control of the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_236:
  sectionId (48631)
  sectionNo (236)
  orderNo 236
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_236_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48631&sectionno=236&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_236_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, the expression "to erect a`
  line `building" means--`
  line
  line `(a) to erect a new building on any site whether previously built upon or not;`
  line
  line `(b) to re-erect--`
  line
  line `(i) any building of which more than one-half of the cubical contents above the level of the`
  line `plinth have been pulled down, burnt or destroyed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any building of which more than one-half of the superficial area of the external walls`
  line `above the level of the plinth has been pulled down; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any frame building of which more than-half of the number of the columns or beams in`
  line `the external walls have been pulled down;`
  line
  line `(c) to convert into a dwelling house any building or any part of a building not originally`
  line `constructed for human habitation or, if originally so constructed, subsequently appropriated for any`
  line `other purpose;`
  line
  line `(d) to convert into more than one dwelling house a building originally constructed as one`
  line `dwelling house only;`
  line
  line `(e) to convert into a place of religious worship or into a sacred building any place or building not`
  line `originally constructed for such purpose;`
  line
  line `(f) to roof or cover an open space between walls or buildings to the extent of the structure which`
  line `is formed by the roofing or covering of such space;`
  line
  line `(g) to convert two or more tenements in a building into a greater or lesser number;`
  line
  line `(h) to convert into a stall, shop, warehouse or godown, stable, factory or garage any building not`
  line `originally constructed for use as such or which was not so used before the change;`
  line
  line `(i) to convert a building which when originally constructed was legally exempt from the`
  line `operations of any building regulations contained in this Act or in any bye-laws made thereunder or in`
  line `any other law, into a building which had it been originally erected in its converted form, would have`
  line `been subject to such building regulations;`
  line
  line `(j) to convert into or use as a dwelling house any building which has been discontinued as or`
  line `appropriated for any purpose other than, a dwelling house.`
obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_237:
  sectionId (48632)
  sectionNo (237)
  orderNo 237
  title `Prohibition of building without sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_237_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48632&sectionno=237&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_237_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall erect or commence to erect any`
  line `building or execute any of the works specified in section 239 except with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Chairperson not otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and of the bye-laws`
  line `made under this Act in relation to the erection of buildings or execution of works.`
  line
  line `(2) In such areas as may be specified by bye-laws made in this behalf, no roof, verandah, pandal or`
  line `wall of a building or no shed or fence shall be constructed or reconstructed of cloth, grass leaves, mats or`
  line `other inflammable materials except with the written permission of the Chairperson, nor shall any such`
  line `roof, verandah, pandal, wall, shed or fence constructed or reconstructed in any year be retained in a`
  line `subsequent year except with fresh permission obtained in this behalf`
obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_238:
  sectionId (48633)
  sectionNo (238)
  orderNo 238
  title `Erection of building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_238_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48633&sectionno=238&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_238_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who intends to erect a building shall apply for sanction`
  line `by giving notice in writing of his intention to the Chairperson in such form and containing such`
  line `information as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such notice shall be accompanied by such documents and plans as may be so prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_239:
  sectionId (48634)
  sectionNo (239)
  orderNo 239
  title `Applications for additions to, or repairs of, buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_239_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48634&sectionno=239&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_239_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who intends to`
  line `execute any of the following works, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) to make any addition to a building;`
  line
  line `(b) to make any alteration or repairs to a building involving the removal or re-erection of any`
  line `external or partly wall thereof or of any wall which supports the roof thereof to an extent exceeding`
  line `one-half of such wall above the plinth level, such half to be measured in superficial metres;`
  line
  line `(c) to make any alteration or repairs to a frame building involving the removal or re-erection of`
  line `more than one-half of the columns or posts in any such wall thereof as aforesaid; or involving the`
  line `removal or re-erection of any such wall thereof as aforesaid to an extent exceeding one-half of such`
  line `wall above plinth level, such half to be measured in superficial metres;`
  line
  line `(d) to make any alteration in a building involving--`
  line
  line `(i) the sub-division of any room in such building so as to convert the same into two or more`
  line `separate rooms; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the conversion of any passage or space in such building into a room or rooms;`
  line
  line `(e) to repair, remove, construct, reconstruct or make any addition to or structural alteration in any`
  line `portion of a building abutting on a street which stands within the regular line of such street;`
  line
  line `(f) to close permanently any door or window in an external wall;`
  line
  line `(g) to remove or reconstruct the principal staircase or to alter its position;`
  line
  line `shall apply for sanction by giving notice in writing of his intention to the Chairperson in such form and`
  line `containing such information as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such notice shall be accompanied by such documents and plans as may be so prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_240:
  sectionId (48635)
  sectionNo (240)
  orderNo 240
  title `Conditions of valid notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_240_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48635&sectionno=240&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_240_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person giving the notice required by section 238 shall`
  line `specify the purpose for which it is intended to use the building to which such notice relates; and a person`
  line `giving the notice required by section 239, shall specify whether the purpose for which the building is`
  line `being used is proposed or likely to be changed by the execution of the proposed work.`
  line
  line `(2) No notice shall be valid until the information required under sub-section (1) and any further`
  line `information and plans which may be required by bye-laws made in this behalf have been furnished to the`
  line `satisfaction of the Chairperson alongwith the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_241:
  sectionId (48636)
  sectionNo (241)
  orderNo 241
  title `Sanction or refusal of building or work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_241_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48636&sectionno=241&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_241_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall sanction the erection of a`
  line `building or the execution of a work unless such building or work would contravene any of the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (2) of this section or the provisions of section 245.`
  line
  line `(2) The grounds on which the sanction of a building or work may be refused shall be the following,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the building or work or the use of the site for the building or work or any of the`
  line `particulars comprised in the site plan, ground plan, elevation, section or specification would`
  line `contravene the provisions of any bye-law made in this behalf or of any other law or rule, bye-law or`
  line `order made under such other law;`
  line
  line `(b) that the notice for sanction does not contain the particulars or is not prepared in the manner`
  line `required under the bye-laws made in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) that any information or documents required by the Chairperson under this Act or any bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder has or have not been duly furnished;`
  line
  line `(d) that in cases falling under section 216, lay-out plans have not been sanctioned in accordance`
  line `with section 217;`
  line
  line `(e) that the building or work would be an encroachment on Central Government or Government`
  line `land or land vested in the Council;`
  line
  line `(f) that the site of the building or work does not abut on a street or projected street and that there`
  line `is no access to such building or work from any such street by a passage or pathway appertaining to`
  line `such site;`
  line
  line `(g) that the land on which it is proposed to erect or re-erect such building is vested in the Central`
  line `Government or Government or in the Council, and the consent of the Government concerned or, as`
  line `the case may be, of the Council has not been obtained, or if the title of the land is in dispute between`
  line `such person and the Council or any Government, or for any other reason, to be communicated in`
  line `writing to the person, which is deemed to be just and sufficient as effecting such building.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall communicate the sanction to the person who has given the notice; and`
  line `where he refuses sanction on any of the grounds specified in sub-section (2) or under section 245 he shall`
  line `record a brief statement of his reasons for such refusal and the Chairperson shall communicate the refusal`
  line `alongwith the reasons therefor to the person who has given the notice.`
  line
  line `(4) The sanction or refusal as aforesaid shall be communicated in such manner as may be specified in`
  line `the bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_242:
  sectionId (48637)
  sectionNo (242)
  orderNo 242
  title `When building or work may be proceeded with.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_242_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48637&sectionno=242&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_242_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where within a period of sixty days or`
  line `in cases falling under clause (b) of section 236 within a period of thirty days, after the receipt of any`
  line `notice under section 238 or section 239 or of the further information, if any, required under section 240,`
  line `the Chairperson does not refuse to sanction the building or work or upon refusal, does not communicate`
  line `the refusal to the person who has given the notice, the Chairperson shall be deemed to have accorded`
  line `sanction to the building or work and the person by whom the notice has been given shall be free to`
  line `commence and proceed with the building or work in accordance with his intention as expressed in the`
  line `notice and the documents and plans accompanying the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that if it appears to the Chairperson that the site of the proposed building or work is likely to`
  line `be affected by any scheme of acquisition of land for any public purpose or by any proposed regular line of`
  line `a public street or extension, improvement, widening or alteration of any street, the Chairperson may`
  line `withhold sanction of the building or work for such period not exceeding three months as he deems fit and the period of sixty days or as the case may be, the period of thirty days specified in this sub-section shall`
  line `be deemed to commence from the date of the expiry of the period for which the sanction has been`
  line withheld.
  line
  line `(2) Where a building or work is sanctioned or is deemed to have been sanctioned by the Chairperson`
  line `under sub-section (1), the person who has given the notice shall be bound to erect the building or execute`
  line `the work in accordance with such sanction but not so as to contravene any of the provisions of this Act or`
  line `any other law or of bye-law made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) If the person or anyone lawfully claiming under him does not commence the erection of the`
  line `building or the execution of the work within one year of the date on which the building or work is`
  line `sanctioned or is deemed to have been sanctioned, he shall have to give notice under section 238 or, as the`
  line `case may be, under section 239 for fresh sanction of the building or the work and the provisions of this`
  line `section shall apply in relation to such notice as they apply in relation to the original notice.`
  line
  line `(4) Before commencing the erection of a building or execution of a work within the period specified`
  line `in sub-section (3), the person concerned shall give notice to the Chairperson of the proposed date of the`
  line `commencement of the erection of the building or the execution of the work:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the commencement does not take place within seven days of the date so notified, the`
  line `notice shall be deemed not to have been given and a fresh notice shall be necessary in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_243:
  sectionId (48638)
  sectionNo (243)
  orderNo 243
  title `Sanction accorded under misrepresentation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_243_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48638&sectionno=243&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_243_content:
  string
  line `If at any time after the sanction of any building`
  line `or work has been accorded, the Chairperson is satisfied that such sanction was accorded in consequence`
  line `of any material misrepresentation or fraudulent statement contained in the notice given or information`
  line `furnished under sections 238, 239 and 240, he may by order in writing cancel for reasons to be recorded`
  line `such sanction and any building or work commenced, erected or done shall be deemed to have been`
  line `commenced, erected or done without such sanction:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any such order the Chairperson shall give reasonable opportunity to the`
  line `person affected as to why such order should not be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_244:
  sectionId (48639)
  sectionNo (244)
  orderNo 244
  title `Buildings at corners of streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_244_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48639&sectionno=244&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_244_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may require any building intended to be`
  line `erected at the corner of two streets to be rounded off or splayed or cut off to such height and to such`
  line `extent as he may determine, and may acquire such portion of the site at the corner as he may consider`
  line `necessary for public convenience or amenity.`
obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_245:
  sectionId (48640)
  sectionNo (245)
  orderNo 245
  title `Provisions as to buildings and works on either side of new streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_245_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48640&sectionno=245&orderno=245&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_245_content:
  string
  line `(1) The erection of any`
  line `building on either side of a new street may be refused by the Chairperson unless and until such new street`
  line `has been levelled, and wherever in the opinion of the Chairperson practicable, metalled or paved, drained,`
  line `lighted and laid with a water main to its satisfaction.`
  line
  line `(2) The erection of any such building or the execution of any such work may be refused by the`
  line `Chairperson if such building or any portion thereof or such work comes within the regular line of any`
  line `street, the position and direction of which has been laid down by the Chairperson but which has not been`
  line `actually constructed or if such building or any portion thereof or such work is in contravention of any`
  line `building or any other scheme or plan prepared under this Act or any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_246:
  sectionId (48641)
  sectionNo (246)
  orderNo 246
  title `Period for completion of building or work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_246_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48641&sectionno=246&orderno=246&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_246_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, when sanctioning the erection`
  line `of a building or execution of a work, shall specify a reasonable period after the commencement of the`
  line `building or work within which the building or work is to be completed and if the building or work is not`
  line `completed within the period so specified, it shall not be continued thereafter without fresh sanction`
  line `obtained in the manner hereinbefore provided, unless the Chairperson on application made therefor has`
  line `allowed an extension of that period.`
obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_247:
  sectionId (48642)
  sectionNo (247)
  orderNo 247
  title `Order of demolition and stoppage of buildings or works in certain cases and appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_247_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48642&sectionno=247&orderno=247&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_247_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the erection of any building or execution of any work has been commenced, or is being carried`
  line `on, or has been completed without or contrary to the sanction referred to in section 241 or in`
  line `contravention of any condition subject to which such sanction has been accorded or in contravention of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act or bye-laws made thereunder, the Chairperson may, in addition to any`
  line `other action that may be taken under this Act, make an order directing that such erection or work shall be`
  line `demolished by the person at whose instance the erection or work has been commenced or is being carried on or has been completed, within such period (not being less than five days and more than fifteen days`
  line `from the date on which a copy of the order of demolition with a brief statement of the reasons therefor has`
  line `been delivered to that person), as may be, specified in the order of demolition:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of demolition shall be made unless the person has been given by means of a`
  line `notice served in such manner as the Chairperson may think fit, a reasonable opportunity of showing cause`
  line `why such order shall not be made:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the erection or work has not been completed, the Chairperson may by the`
  line `same order or by a separate order, whether made at the time of the issue of the notice under the first`
  line `proviso or at any other time, direct the person to stop the erection or work until the expiry of the period`
  line `within which an appeal against the order of demolition, if made, may be preferred under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Chairperson made under sub-section (1) may prefer an`
  line `appeal against the order to the Appellate Tribunal within the period specified in the order for the`
  line `demolition of the erection or work to which it relates.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an appeal is preferred under sub-section (2) against an order of demolition the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 255 stay the enforcement of that`
  line `order on such terms, if any, and for such period, as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the erection of any building or execution of any work has not been completed at`
  line `the time of the making of the order of demolition, no order staying the enforcement of the order of`
  line `demolition shall be made by the Appellate Tribunal unless security, sufficient in the opinion of the said`
  line `Tribunal has been given by the appellant for not proceeding, with such erection or work pending the`
  line `disposal of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) No court shall entertain any suit, application or order proceeding for injunction or other relief`
  line `against the Chairperson to restrain him from taking any action or making any order in pursuance of the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to an order made by the Administrator on appeal under section 256, every order made by`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal on appeal under this section, and subject to the orders of the Administrator and the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal on appeal, the order of demolition made by the Chairperson shall be final and`
  line conclusive.
  line
  line `(6) Where no appeal has been preferred against an order of demolition made by the Chairperson`
  line `under sub-section (1) or where an order of demolition made by the Chairperson under that sub-section has`
  line `been confirmed on appeal, whether with or without variation, by the Appellate Tribunal and by the`
  line `Administrator in a case where an appeal has been preferred against the order of the Appellate Tribunal,`
  line `the person against whom the order has been made shall comply with the order within the period specified`
  line `therein, or as the case may be, within the period, if any fixed by the Appellate Tribunal or the`
  line `Administrator on appeal and on the failure of the person to comply with the order within such period, the`
  line `Chairperson may himself cause the erection or the work to which the order relates to be demolished and`
  line `the expenses of such demolition shall be recoverable from such person as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_248:
  sectionId (48643)
  sectionNo (248)
  orderNo 248
  title `Order of stoppage of buildings or works in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_248_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48643&sectionno=248&orderno=248&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_248_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the erection of any`
  line `building or execution of any work has been commenced or is being carried on (but has not been`
  line `completed) without or contrary to the sanction referred to in section 241, or in contravention of any`
  line `condition subject to which such sanction has been accorded or in contravention of any provisions of this`
  line `Act or bye-laws made thereunder, the Chairperson may in addition to any other action that may be taken`
  line `under this Act, by order require the person at whose instance the building or the work has been`
  line `commenced or is being carried on to stop the same forthwith.`
  line
  line `(2) If an order made by the Chairperson under section 247 or under sub-section (1) of this section`
  line `directing any person to stop the erection of any building or execution of any work is not complied with,`
  line `the Chairperson may require any police officer to remove such person and all his assistants and workmen`
  line `from the premises or to seize any construction material, tool, machinery, scaffolding or other things used`
  line `in the erection of any building or execution of any work within such time as may be specified in the`
  line `requisition and such police officer shall comply with the requisition accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Any of the things caused to be seized by the Chairperson under sub-section (2) shall be disposed`
  line `of by him in the manner specified in section 230.`
  line
  line `(4) After the requisition under sub-section (2) has been complied with, the Chairperson may, if he`
  line `thinks fit, depute by a written order a police officer or a municipal officer or other municipal employee of`
  line `the Council to watch the premises in order to ensure that the erection of the building or the execution of`
  line `the work is not continued.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a police officer or a municipal officer or other municipal employee has been deputed under`
  line `sub-section (4) to watch the premises, the cost of such deputation shall be paid by the person at whose`
  line `instance such erection or execution is being continued or to whom notice under sub-section (1) was given`
  line `and shall be recoverable from such person as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_249:
  sectionId (48644)
  sectionNo (249)
  orderNo 249
  title `Power of Chairperson to require alteration of work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_249_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_249_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48644&sectionno=249&orderno=249&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_249_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may at any time`
  line `during the erection of any building or execution of any work or at any time after the completion thereof`
  line `by a written notice of not less than seven days specify any matter in respect of which such erection or`
  line `execution is without or contrary to the sanction referred to in section 241 or is in contravention of any`
  line `condition of such sanction or any of the provisions of this Act or any bye-laws made thereunder and`
  line `require the person who gave the notice under section 238 or section 239 or the owner of such building or`
  line `work either--`
  line
  line `(a) to make such alterations as may be specified in the said notice with the object of bringing the`
  line `building or work in conformity with the said sanction, condition or provisions, or`
  line
  line `(b) to show cause why such alterations should not be made, within a period stated in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If the person or the owner does not show cause as aforesaid, he shall be bound to make the`
  line `alterations specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) If the person or the owner shows cause as aforesaid, the Chairperson shall by an order either`
  line `cancel the notice issued under sub-section (1) or confirm the same subject to such modifications as he`
  line `thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_249_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_250:
  sectionId (48645)
  sectionNo (250)
  orderNo 250
  title `Power to seal unauthorised constructions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_250_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48645&sectionno=250&orderno=250&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_250_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for the Chairperson, at any`
  line `time, before or after making an order of demolition under section 247 or of the stoppage of the erection of`
  line `any building or execution of any work under section 247 or under section 248, to make an order directing`
  line `the sealing of such erection or work or of the premises in which such erection or work is being carried on`
  line `or has been completed in the manner prescribed by rules, for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of`
  line `this Act, or for preventing any dispute as to the nature and extent of such erection or work.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any erection or work or any premises in which any erection or work is being carried on,`
  line `has or have been sealed, the Chairperson may, for the purpose of demolishing such erection or work in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, order such seal to be removed.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall remove such seal except--`
  line
  line `(a) under an order made by the Chairperson under sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(b) under an order of an Appellate Tribunal or the Administrator, made in an appeal under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_251:
  sectionId (48646)
  sectionNo (251)
  orderNo 251
  title `Completion certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_251_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48646&sectionno=251&orderno=251&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_251_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who employs an architect registered with the`
  line `Council or an architects or an engineer or a person approved by the Chairperson to design or erect a`
  line `building or execute any work shall, within one month after the completion of the erection of the building`
  line `or execution of the work, deliver or send or cause to be delivered or sent to the Chairperson a notice in`
  line `writing of such completion accompanied by a certificate in the form prescribed by bye-laws made in this`
  line `behalf and shall give to the Chairperson all necessary facilities for the inspection of such building or`
  line work.
  line
  line `(2) No person shall occupy or permit to be occupied any such building or use or permit to be used any`
  line `building or a part thereof effected by any such work until permission has been granted by the Chairperson`
  line `in this behalf in accordance with bye-laws made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Chairperson fails within a period of thirty days after the receipt of the notice of`
  line `completion to communicate its refusal to grant such permission, such permission shall be deemed to have`
  line `been granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_252:
  sectionId (48647)
  sectionNo (252)
  orderNo 252
  title `Restrictions on uses of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_252_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48647&sectionno=252&orderno=252&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_252_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without the written permission of the`
  line `Chairperson, or otherwise than in conformity with the conditions, if any, of such permission--`
  line
  line `(a) use or permit to be used for human habitation any part of a building not originally erected or`
  line `authorised to be used for that purpose or not used for that purpose before any alteration has been`
  line `made therein by any work executed in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) change or allow the change of the use of any land or building;`
  line
  line `(c) convert or allow the conversion of one kind of tenement into another kind.`
obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_253:
  sectionId (48648)
  sectionNo (253)
  orderNo 253
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_253_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_253_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48648&sectionno=253&orderno=253&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_253_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `constitute one or more Appellate Tribunals with headquarters at Delhi or New Delhi, for deciding appeals`
  line `preferred under section 247 or section 254.`
  line
  line `(2) An Appellate Tribunal shall consist of one person to be appointed by the Central Government on`
  line `such terms and conditions of service as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the presiding officer of an Appellate tribunal`
  line `unless he is, or has been, a district judge or an additional district judge or has, for at least ten years, held a`
  line `judicial office in India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, if it so thinks fit, appoint one or more persons having special`
  line `knowledge of, or experience in, matters involved in such appeals, to act as assessors to advise the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal in the proceedings before it, but no advice of the assessors shall be binding on the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, define the territorial limits`
  line `within which an Appellate Tribunal shall exercise its jurisdiction, and where different Appellate Tribunals`
  line `have jurisdiction over the same territorial limits, the Central Government shall also provide for the`
  line `distribution and allocation of work to be performed by such Tribunals.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purpose of enabling it to discharge its functions under this Act, every Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall have a Registrar and such other staff on such terms and conditions of service as may be prescribed`
  line `by rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar and staff may be employed jointly for all or any number of such Tribunals`
  line `in accordance with the rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_253_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_254:
  sectionId (48649)
  sectionNo (254)
  orderNo 254
  title `Appeals against certain orders or notices issued under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_254_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_254_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48649&sectionno=254&orderno=254&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_254_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved`
  line `by any of the following orders made or notices issued under this Act, may prefer an appeal against such`
  line `order or notice to the Appellate Tribunal, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) an order according or disallowing sanction to a lay-out plan under section 217;`
  line
  line `(b) an order directing the alteration or demolition of any street under section 218;`
  line
  line `(c) a notice under sub-section (1) of section 219;`
  line
  line `(d) a notice under sub-section (2) of section 221;`
  line
  line `(e) an order directing the disposal of things removed under Chapter XIII or seized under section`
  line `248, or an order rejecting the claim of any person for the balance of the proceeds of sale of things so`
  line `disposed of;`
  line
  line `(f) an order sanctioning or refusing to sanction the erection of any building or the execution of`
  line `any work under section 241;`
  line
  line `(g) an order withholding sanction under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 242;`
  line
  line `(h) an order cancelling a sanction under section 243;`
  line
  line `(i) an order requiring the rounding off, splaying or cutting off the height of a building intended to`
  line `be erected, or for the acquisition of any portion of a site, under section 244;`
  line
  line `(j) an order disallowing the erection of any building or the execution of any work under`
  line `section 245;`
  line
  line `(k) an order requiring the stoppage of any erection or work under section 248;`
  line
  line `(l) an order requiring the alteration of any building or work under section 249;`
  line
  line `(m) an order directing the sealing of unauthorised constructions under section 250;`
  line
  line `(n) an order refusing to grant permission under sub-section (2) of section 251;`
  line
  line `(o) an order granting or refusing permission under section 252;`
  line
  line `(p) any such other order or notice relating to or arising out of planned development under the`
  line `provisions of this Act as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal under this section shall be filed within thirty days from the date of the order or notice`
  line `appealed against:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be made in such form and shall be accompanied by a`
  line `copy of the order or notice appealed against and by such fees as may be prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_254_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_255:
  sectionId (48650)
  sectionNo (255)
  orderNo 255
  title `Procedure of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_255_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_255_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48650&sectionno=255&orderno=255&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_255_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the`
  line `parties to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming,`
  line `modifying or annulling the order or notice appealed against or may refer the case back to the authority or`
  line `officer against whose order or notice the appeal is filed, for a fresh order or notice, after taking additional`
  line `evidence, if necessary, or such other action as the Appellate Tribunal may specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order passed by it to the parties to the appeal.`
  line
  line `(3) No Appellate Tribunal shall, in any appeal pending before it in respect of any order or notice`
  line `under this Act, make an interim order (whether by way of injunction or stay) against the Council or`
  line `against any officer or servant of the Council acting or purporting to act in his official capacity, unless an`
  line `opportunity is given to the Council or its officer or servant to be heard in the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may without giving an opportunity as aforesaid make an interim`
  line `order as an exceptional measure if it is satisfied for reasons to be recorded by it in writing that it is`
  line `necessary so to do for preventing any loss being caused to the person filing the appeal which cannot be`
  line `adequately compensated in money:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every such interim order shall, if it is not vacated earlier, cease to have effect on`
  line `the expiry of a period of fourteen days from the date on which it is made unless before the expiry of that`
  line `period, the Appellate Tribunal confirms or modifies that order after giving to the Council or its officer or`
  line `servant an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to rules that may be made by the Central Government in this behalf, the awarding of`
  line `damages in and the costs of, and incidental to, any appeal before an Appellate Tribunal, shall be in its`
  line `discretion and it shall have full power to determine by and to whom and to what extent and subject to`
  line `what conditions, if any, such damages or costs are to be paid and to give, in its order disposing of an`
  line `appeal, necessary directions for the purposes aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(5) An order of the Appellate Tribunal made under this section may be executed or caused to be`
  line `executed by it on the application of the person in whose favour the order has been made.`
  line
  line `(6) In hearing and deciding an appeal or in the execution of an order, an Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `follow such procedure as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(7) Every Appellate Tribunal, shall in addition to the powers conferred on it under this Act, have the`
  line `same power as are vested in a Civil Court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908) in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and inspection of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `and every proceeding of an Appellate Tribunal in hearing or deciding an appeal or in connection with the`
  line `execution of its order, shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and`
  line `228 and for the purpose of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and every Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall be deemed to be a Civil Court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_255_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_256:
  sectionId (48651)
  sectionNo (256)
  orderNo 256
  title `Appeal against orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_256_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_256_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48651&sectionno=256&orderno=256&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_256_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal shall lie to the Administrator,`
  line `against an order of the Appellate Tribunal made in an appeal under section 247 or section 254,`
  line `confirming, modifying or annulling an order made or notice issued under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 254 and section 255 and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, shall, so far as may be, apply to the filing and disposal of an appeal under this section as they`
  line `apply to the filing and disposal of an appeal under those sections.`
  line
  line `(3) An order of the Administrator on an appeal under this section, and subject only to such order, an`
  line `order of the Appellate Tribunal under section 254, and subject to such orders of the Administrator or an`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, an order or notice referred to in sub-section (1) of that section, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_256_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_257:
  sectionId (48652)
  sectionNo (257)
  orderNo 257
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_257_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_257_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48652&sectionno=257&orderno=257&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_257_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the commencement of this Act, no court shall entertain`
  line `any suit, application or other proceedings in respect of any order or notice appealable under section 247 or`
  line `section 254 and no such order or notice shall be called in question otherwise than by preferring an appeal`
  line `under those sections.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), every suit, application or other proceeding`
  line `pending in any court immediately before the commencement of this Act, in respect of any order or notice`
  line `appealable under section 247 or section 254, shall continue to be dealt with and disposed of by that court`
  line `as if the said section had not been brought into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_257_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_258:
  sectionId (48653)
  sectionNo (258)
  orderNo 258
  title `Removal of dangerous buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_258_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_258_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48653&sectionno=258&orderno=258&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_258_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the Chairperson at any time that any`
  line `building is in a ruinous condition, or likely to fall, or in any way dangerous to any person occupying,`
  line `resorting to or passing by such building or any other building or place in the neighbourhood of such`
  line `building, the Chairperson may, by order in writing, require the owner or occupier of such building to`
  line `demolish, secure or repair such building or do one or more of such things within such period as may be`
  line `specified in the order, so as to prevent all cause of danger therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may also, if he thinks fit, require such owner or occupier by the said order either`
  line `forthwith or before proceeding to demolish, secure or repair the building, to set up a proper and sufficient`
  line `hoard or fence for the protection of passers-by and other persons, with a convenient platform and`
  line `hand-rail wherever practicable to serve as a foot-way for passengers outside of such hoard or fence.`
  line
  line `(3) If it appears to the Chairperson that danger from a building which is in a ruinous condition or`
  line `likely to fall is imminent, he may, before making the order aforesaid, fence off, demolish, secure or repair`
  line `the said building or take such steps as may be necessary to prevent the danger.`
  line
  line `(4) If the owner or occupier of the building does not comply with the order within the period specified`
  line `therein, the Chairperson shall take such steps in relation to the building as to prevent all cause of danger`
  line therefrom.
  line
  line `(5) All expenses incurred by the Chairperson in relation to any building under this section shall be`
  line `recoverable from the owner or occupier thereof as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_258_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_259:
  sectionId (48654)
  sectionNo (259)
  orderNo 259
  title `Power to order building to be vacated in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_259_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48654&sectionno=259&orderno=259&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_259_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may`
  line `by order in writing direct that any building which in his opinion is in a dangerous condition or is not`
  line `provided with sufficient means of egress in case of fire or is occupied in contravention of section 251 be`
  line `vacated forthwith or within such period as may be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that at the time of making such order the Chairperson shall record a brief statement of the`
  line `reasons therefor.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person fails to vacate the building in pursuance of such order the Chairperson may direct`
  line `any police officer to remove such person from the building and the police officer shall comply with such`
  line `direction accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall, on the application of any person who has vacated, or been removed from`
  line `any building in pursuance of an order made by him, re-instate such person in the building on the expiry of`
  line `the period for which the order has been in force according as the circumstances prevailing at that time`
  line permit.
obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_260:
  sectionId (48655)
  sectionNo (260)
  orderNo 260
  title `Power of the Central Government to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_260_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_260_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48655&sectionno=260&orderno=260&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_260_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make bye-laws for carrying out the provisions of this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that all bye-laws made by the New Delhi Municipal Committee under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 189 of the Punjab Municipal Act, 1911 (Punjab Act 3 of 1911) and in force immediately before`
  line `such commencement, shall be deemed to have been made under the provision of this section and shall`
  line `continue to have the same force and effect after such commencement until it is amended, varied,`
  line `rescinded or superseded under the provision of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such bye-laws may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the regulation or restriction of the use of sites for buildings for different areas;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation or restriction of buildings in different areas;`
  line
  line `(c) the form of notice of erection of any building or execution of any work and the fee in respect`
  line `of the same;`
  line
  line `(d) the plans and documents to be submitted together with such notice and the information and`
  line `further information to be furnished;`
  line
  line `(e) the level and width of foundation, level of lowest floor and stability of structure;`
  line
  line `(f) the construction of buildings and the materials to be used in the construction of buildings;`
  line
  line `(g) the height of buildings whether absolute or relative to the width of streets or to different areas;`
  line
  line `(h) the number and height of storeys composing a building and the height of rooms and the`
  line `dimensions of rooms intended for human habitation;`
  line
  line `(i) the provision of open spaces external and internal, and adequate means of light and ventilation;`
  line
  line `(j) the provision of means of egress in case of fire, fire-escapes and water lifting devices;`
  line
  line `(k) the provision of secondary means of access for the removal of house refuse;`
  line
  line `(l) the materials and methods of construction of external and party walls, roofs and floors;`
  line
  line `(m) the position, materials and methods of construction of hearths, smoke-escapes, chimneys,`
  line `stair-cases, latrines, drains and cesspools;`
  line
  line `(n) the provision of lifts;`
  line
  line `(o) the paving of yards;`
  line
  line `(p) the restrictions on the use of inflammable materials in buildings;`
  line
  line `(q) the restriction on construction of foundation on certain sites;`
  line
  line `(r) the measures to be taken to protect building from dump arising from sub-soil;`
  line
  line `(s) the wells, tanks and cisterns and pumps for the supply of water for human consumption in`
  line `connection with buildings;`
  line
  line `(t) in the case of wells, the dimensions of the well, the manner of enclosing it and; if the well is`
  line `intended for drinking purposes, the means which shall be used to prevent pollution of the water;`
  line
  line `(u) the supervision of buildings;`
  line
  line `(v) the setting back of garages and shops from the regular line of a street;`
  line
  line `(w) the construction of partable structures and permission for such construction.`
  line
  line `(3) The draft of the bye-laws referred to in sub-section (1) shall be forwarded to the Chairperson, who`
  line `shall cause the same to be published in the Official Gazette for inviting objections and suggestions from`
  line `the public within thirty days from the date of such publication.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson shall forward the draft bye-laws to the Central Government along with his`
  line `recommendations and the objections and suggestions received from the public, within three months of`
  line `their publication in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may issue such directions to the Chairperson as it thinks fit, for ensuring`
  line `proper implementation of the bye-laws made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_260_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_261:
  sectionId (48656)
  sectionNo (261)
  orderNo 261
  title `Provision for daily cleansing of streets and removal of rubbish and filth.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_261_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_261_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48656&sectionno=261&orderno=261&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_261_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the`
  line `purpose of securing the efficient scavenging and cleansing of all streets and premises, the Chairperson`
  line `shall provide--`
  line
  line `(a) for the daily surface-cleansing of all streets and the removal of the sweepings therefrom, and`
  line
  line `(b) for the removal of the contents of all receptacles and depots and of the accumulations at all`
  line `places provided or appointed by him under the provisions of this Act for the temporary deposit of`
  line `rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may, by public notice, issue directions as to the time at which, the manner in`
  line `which, and the conditions subject to which, any matter referred to in sub-section (1) may be removed`
  line `along a street or may be deposited or otherwise disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_261_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_262:
  sectionId (48657)
  sectionNo (262)
  orderNo 262
  title `Rubbish, etc., to be the property of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_262_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_262_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48657&sectionno=262&orderno=262&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_262_content:
  string
  line `All matters deposited in public receptacles,`
  line `depots and places provided or appointed under section 263 and all matters collected by municipal`
  line `employees or contractors in pursuance of section 261 and section 265 shall be the property of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_262_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_263:
  sectionId (48658)
  sectionNo (263)
  orderNo 263
  title `Provision or appointment of receptacles, depots and places for rubbish, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_263_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_263_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48658&sectionno=263&orderno=263&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_263_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Chairperson shall--`
  line
  line `(a) provide or appoint in proper and convenient situations public receptacles, depots or places for`
  line `the temporary deposit of rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter and for the final`
  line `disposal of rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter;`
  line
  line `(b) provide dustbins for the temporary deposit of rubbish;`
  line
  line `(c) provide vehicles or other suitable means for the removal of rubbish and offensive matter; and`
  line
  line `(d) provide covered vehicles or vessels for the removal of filth and other polluted and obnoxious`
  line matter.
  line
  line `(2) Different receptacles, depots or places may be provided or appointed for the temporary deposit or`
  line
  line `final disposal of any of the matters specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall make adequate provision for preventing receptacles, depots, places,`
  line `dustbins, vehicles and vessels referred to in sub-section (1) from becoming sources of nuisance`
obj_root_law_sections_263_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_264:
  sectionId (48659)
  sectionNo (264)
  orderNo 264
  title `Duty of owners and occupiers to collect and deposit rubbish, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_264_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48659&sectionno=264&orderno=264&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_264_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the`
  line `owners and occupiers of all premises--`
  line
  line `(a) to have the premises swept and cleaned;`
  line
  line `(b) to cause all filth, rubbish and other polluted and obnoxious matter to be collected from their`
  line `respective premises and to be deposited at such times as the Chairperson, by public notice prescribes,`
  line `in public receptacles, depots or places provided or appointed under section 263 for the temporary`
  line `deposit or final disposal thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) to provide receptacles of the type and in the manner prescribed by the Chairperson for the`
  line `collection therein of all filth, rubbish and other polluted and obnoxious matter from such premises`
  line `and to keep such receptacles in good condition and repair.`
obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_265:
  sectionId (48660)
  sectionNo (265)
  orderNo 265
  title `Collection and removal of filth and polluted matter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_265_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48660&sectionno=265&orderno=265&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_265_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the owner`
  line `and occupier of every premises situate in any portion of New Delhi in which there is not a latrine, or`
  line `urinal connected by a drain with a municipal drain, to cause all filth and polluted and obnoxious matter`
  line `accumulating upon such premises to be collected and removed to the nearest receptacle or depot provided`
  line `for this purpose under section 263 at such times, in such vehicle or vessel by such route and with such`
  line `precautions as the Chairperson may by public notice prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be lawful for the Chairperson to take or cause to be taken measures for the daily collection,`
  line `removal and disposal of all filth and polluted and obnoxious matters from latrines, urinals and cesspools`
  line `not connected by a drain with a municipal drain from all premises situate in any portion of New Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) In such portion of New Delhi and in any premises where situate in which there is a latrine or`
  line `urinal connected with a municipal drain, it shall not be lawful, except with the written permission of the`
  line `Chairperson, for any person who is not employed by or on behalf of the Chairperson to discharge any of`
  line `the duties of scavengers.`
obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_266:
  sectionId (48661)
  sectionNo (266)
  orderNo 266
  title `Removal of rubbish, etc., accumulated on premises used as factories, workshop, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_266_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48661&sectionno=266&orderno=266&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_266_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Chairperson may, if he thinks fit,--`
  line
  line `(a) by written notice require the owner or occupier of any premises used for carrying on any`
  line `manufacture, trade or business or used as a factory, workshop, trade premises or market or in any way`
  line `so that rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter are accumulated in large quantities, to`
  line `collect all such rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter accumulating thereon and to`
  line `remove the same at such times and in such carts or receptacles and by such routes as may be specified`
  line `in the notice to a depot or place provided or appointed under section 263, or`
  line
  line `(b) after giving such owner or occupier notice of his intention, cause all rubbish, filth and other`
  line `polluted and obnoxious matter accumulated in such premises to be removed, and charge the said`
  line `owner or occupier for such removal such fee as may, with the sanction of the Council be specified in`
  line `the notice issued under clause (a).`
obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_267:
  sectionId (48662)
  sectionNo (267)
  orderNo 267
  title `Prohibition against accumulation of rubbish, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_267_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48662&sectionno=267&orderno=267&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_267_content:
  string
  line `(1) No owner or occupier of any premises`
  line `shall keep or allow to be kept for more than twenty-four hours or otherwise than in a receptacle approved`
  line `by the Chairperson, any rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter on such premises or any`
  line `place belonging thereto or neglect to employ proper means to remove such rubbish, filth and other`
  line `polluted and obnoxious matter from, or to cleanse, such receptacle and to dispose of such rubbish, filth`
  line `and other polluted and obnoxious matter in the manner directed by the Chairperson, or fail to comply with`
  line `any requisition of the Chairperson as to the construction, repair, pavement or cleansing of any latrine, or`
  line `urinal on or belonging to the premises.`
  line
  line `(2) No owner or occupier shall allow the water of any sink, drain, latrine or urinal or any rubbish, filth`
  line `and other polluted and obnoxious matter to run down on or to, or be thrown or put upon, any street or into`
  line `any drain in or along the side of any street except in such manner as shall prevent any avoidable nuisance`
  line `from any such water, rubbish, filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall, after due provision has been made in this respect under the foregoing provisions`
  line `of this Chapter for the deposit and removal of the same--`
  line
  line `(a) deposit any rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter in any street or on the`
  line `verandah of any building or on any unoccupied ground alongside any street or on the bank of a water`
  line `course; or`
  line
  line `(b) deposit any filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter in any dustbin or in any vehicle not`
  line `intended for the removal of the same; or`
  line
  line `(c) deposit rubbish in any vehicle or vessel intended for the removal of filth and other polluted`
  line `and obnoxious matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_268:
  sectionId (48663)
  sectionNo (268)
  orderNo 268
  title `Prohibition in respect of air pollutant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_268_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48663&sectionno=268&orderno=268&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_268_content:
  string
  line `No owner or occupier of any premises shall allow or`
  line `cause to be allowed any air pollutant above the standards, laid down under clause (g) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 17 of the Air (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1981 (14 of 1981).`
obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_269:
  sectionId (48664)
  sectionNo (269)
  orderNo 269
  title `Chairperson's power to get premises scavenged and cleansed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_269_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48664&sectionno=269&orderno=269&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_269_content:
  string
  line `If any premises are not`
  line `properly and regularly scavenged or cleansed or are in a filthy and unwholesome condition, the`
  line `Chairperson may cause them to be scavenged and cleansed and recover the expenses from the owner or,`
  line `as the case may be, occupier as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_270:
  sectionId (48665)
  sectionNo (270)
  orderNo 270
  title `Public latrines, urinals, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_270_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48665&sectionno=270&orderno=270&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_270_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall provide and maintain in proper and`
  line `convenient places a sufficient number of public latrines and urinals.`
  line
  line `(2) Such public latrines and urinals shall be so constructed as to provide separate compartments for`
  line `each sex and not to be a nuisance, and shall be provided with all necessary conservancy establishments,`
  line `and shall regularly be cleansed and kept in proper order.`
obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_271:
  sectionId (48666)
  sectionNo (271)
  orderNo 271
  title `Construction of latrines and urinals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_271_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48666&sectionno=271&orderno=271&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_271_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall not be lawful to construct any latrine or`
  line `urinal for any premises except with the written permission of the Chairperson and in accordance with`
  line `such terms not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or any bye-laws made thereunder as he may`
  line prescribe.
  line
  line `(2) In prescribing any such terms the Chairperson may determine in such case--`
  line
  line `(a) whether the premises shall be served by the service system or by the flush system or partly by`
  line `the one and partly by the other; and`
  line
  line `(b) what shall be the site or position of each latrine or urinal.`
  line
  line `(3) If any latrine or urinal is constructed on any premises in contravention of the foregoing provisions,`
  line `the Chairperson may, after giving not less than ten days' notice to the owner or occupier of such premises,`
  line `alter, reconstruct, close or demolish such latrine or urinal and the expenditure incurred by the Chairperson`
  line `in so doing shall be recoverable from the owner or occupier as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_272:
  sectionId (48667)
  sectionNo (272)
  orderNo 272
  title `Latrines and urinals, etc., in new buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_272_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48667&sectionno=272&orderno=272&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_272_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall not be lawful to erect any building or`
  line `execute any work on or in relation to such building without providing such latrine accommodation and`
  line `urinal accommodation and accommodation for bathing or for washing clothes and utensils on each floor`
  line `of such building as the Chairperson may prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) In prescribing any such accommodation, the Chairperson may determine in each case--`
  line
  line `(a) that such building shall be served by the flush system only;`
  line
  line `(b) what shall be the site or position of each latrine, urinal, bathing or washing place or site and`
  line `their number on each floor and their clear internal dimensions.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall not be lawful to erect a residential building composed of separate tenements on the flat`
  line `system without providing at least one latrine and one bathing or washing place for servants on the ground`
  line `floor of such building or at any other suitable place in the same premises.`
  line
  line `(4) In this section, the expression "to erect a building" has the same meaning as in section 236.`
obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_273:
  sectionId (48668)
  sectionNo (273)
  orderNo 273
  title `Latrines and urinals for labourers, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_273_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48668&sectionno=273&orderno=273&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_273_content:
  string
  line `Every person employing workmen, labourers or`
  line `other persons exceeding twenty in number shall provide and maintain for the separate use of persons of`
  line `each sex so employed, latrines and urinals of such description and number as the Chairperson may by`
  line `notice require and within such time as may be fixed in the notice and shall keep the same in clean and`
  line `proper order`
obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_274:
  sectionId (48669)
  sectionNo (274)
  orderNo 274
  title `Provision of latrines and urinals for markets, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_274_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48669&sectionno=274&orderno=274&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_274_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may by notice require`
  line `any owner or manager of a market, cart stand, cattle shed, theatre, railway station and other places of`
  line `public resort within such time as may be specified in such notice to provide and maintain for the separate`
  line `use of persons of each sex, latrines and urinals of such description and number and in such position as`
  line `may be specified and to keep the same in clean and proper order.`
obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_275:
  sectionId (48670)
  sectionNo (275)
  orderNo 275
  title `Other provisions as to private latrines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_275_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48670&sectionno=275&orderno=275&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_275_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may, by written notice--`
  line
  line `(a) require the owner or other person having the control of any private latrine or urinal not to put`
  line `the same to public use; or`
  line
  line `(b) require the owner or other person having the control of such private latrine or urinal which in`
  line `the opinion of the Chairperson constitutes a nuisance, to remove the latrine or the urinal; or`
  line
  line `(c) require any person having the control whether as owner, lessee or occupier of any land or`
  line building--
  line
  line `(i) to have any latrine provided for the same shut out by a sufficient roof, wall or fence from`
  line `the view of persons passing by or dwelling in the neighbourhood; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to clean in such manner as the Chairperson may prescribe in the notice any latrine or`
  line `urinal belonging to the land or building; or`
  line
  line `(d) where any premises intended or used for human habitation are without any latrine or urinal`
  line `accommodation or are provided with insufficient latrine or urinal accommodation, require the owner,`
  line `lessee or occupier of such premises to provide such or such additional latrine or urinal`
  line `accommodation as he may prescribe, if necessary by causing any part of such premises to be vacated`
  line `and demolished in accordance with bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_276:
  sectionId (48671)
  sectionNo (276)
  orderNo 276
  title `Removal of congested buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_276_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48671&sectionno=276&orderno=276&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_276_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the Chairperson that any block of`
  line `buildings is in an unhealthy condition by reasons of the manner in which the buildings are crowded`
  line `together, or of the narrowness, closeness, or faulty arrangement of streets, or of the want of proper`
  line `drainage and ventilation, or of the impracticability of cleansing the buildings or other similar cause, he`
  line `shall cause the block to be inspected to by the officer authorised by him and such officer shall make a`
  line `report in writing the Chairperson regarding the sanitary condition of the block.`
  line
  line `(2) If upon receipt of such report the Chairperson considers that the sanitary condition of the block is`
  line `likely to cause risk of disease to the inhabitants of the buildings or of the neighbourhood or otherwise to`
  line `endanger the public health, he shall with the approval of the Council select the buildings which in his`
  line `opinion should wholly or in part be removed in order to abate the unhealthy condition of the block and`
  line `may thereupon by notice in writing require the owners of such building remove them within such period`
  line `as may be specified in the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing the notice reasonable opportunity shall be afforded to the owners to show`
  line `cause why the buildings should not be removed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Chairperson shall make compensation to the owners for any buildings so`
  line `removed which may have been erected under proper authority.`
  line
  line `(3) If a notice under sub-section (2) requiring any owner of a building to remove it is not complied`
  line `with, then, after the expiration of the time specified in the notice the Chairperson may himself remove or`
  line `cause to be removed the building required to be removed by the notice and recover from owner of the`
  line `building the expenses of such removal as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_277:
  sectionId (48672)
  sectionNo (277)
  orderNo 277
  title `Power of Chairperson to require improvement of building unfit for human habitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_277_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48672&sectionno=277&orderno=277&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_277_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Chairperson upon information in his possession is satisfied that any building is in any`
  line `respect unfit for human habitation, he may, unless in his opinion the building is not capable at a`
  line `reasonable expense of being rendered fit, serve upon the owner of the building a notice requiring him`
  line `within such time not being less than thirty days as may be specified in the notice to execute the works of`
  line `improvement specified therein and stating that in his opinion those works will render the building fit for`
  line `human habitation.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to serving a notice under this section on the owner the Chairperson may serve a copy`
  line `of the notice on any other person having an interest in the building whether as a lessee, mortgagee or`
  line otherwise.
  line
  line `(3) In determining whether a building can be rendered fit for human habitation at a reasonable`
  line `expense regard shall be had to the estimated cost of the work necessary to render it so fit and the value`
  line `which it is estimated that the building will have when the works are completed.`
obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_278:
  sectionId (48673)
  sectionNo (278)
  orderNo 278
  title `Enforcement of notice requiring execution of works of improvement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_278_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48673&sectionno=278&orderno=278&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_278_content:
  string
  line `If a notice under`
  line `section 277 requiring the owner of the building to execute works of improvement is not complied with,`
  line `then after the expiration of the time specified in the notice the Chairperson may himself do or cause to be`
  line `done the works required to be done by the notice and recover the expenses incurred in connection`
  line `therewith as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_279:
  sectionId (48674)
  sectionNo (279)
  orderNo 279
  title `Power of Chairperson to order demolition of buildings unfit for human habitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_279_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48674&sectionno=279&orderno=279&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_279_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Chairperson upon any information in his possession is satisfied that any building is unfit`
  line `for human habitation and is not capable at a reasonable expense of being rendered so fit he shall serve`
  line `upon the owner of the building and upon any other person having an interest in the building, whether as a`
  line `lessee, mortgagee or otherwise a notice to show cause within such time as may be specified in the notice`
  line `as to why an order of demolition of the building should not be made.`
  line
  line `(2) If any of the person upon whom a notice has been served under sub-section (1) appears in`
  line `pursuance thereof before the Chairperson and gives an undertaking to him that such person shall, within a`
  line `period specified by the Chairperson, execute such works of improvement in relation to the building as`
  line `will, in the opinion of the Chairperson, render the building fit for human habitation or an undertaking that`
  line `the building shall not be used for human habitation until the Chairperson on being satisfied that it has`
  line `been rendered fit for that purpose, cancels the undertaking, the Chairperson shall not make an order of`
  line `demolition of the building.`
  line
  line `(3) If no such undertaking as is mentioned in sub-section (2) is given or if in a case where any such`
  line `undertaking has been given, any work of improvement to which the undertaking relates is not carried out`
  line `within the specified period, or the building is at any time used in contravention of the terms of the`
  line `undertaking, the Chairperson shall, forthwith make an order of demolition of the building requiring that`
  line `the building shall be vacated within a period to be specified in the order not being less than thirty days`
  line `from the date of the order, and that it shall be demolished within six weeks after the expiration of that`
  line period.
  line
  line `(4) Where an order of demolition of building under this section has been made, the owner of the`
  line `building or any other person having an interest therein, shall demolish that building within the time`
  line `specified in that behalf by the order, and if the building is not demolished within that time, the`
  line `Chairperson shall demolish or cause to be demolished the building and sell the materials thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) Any expenses incurred by the Chairperson under sub-section (4) if not satisfied out of the`
  line `proceeds of the sale of materials of the building shall be recovered from the owner of the building or any`
  line `other person having an interest therein as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) In determining for the purposes of section 277 and this section whether a building is unfit for`
  line `human habitation, regard shall be had to its condition in respect of the following matters, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) repair;`
  line
  line `(b) stability;`
  line
  line `(c) freedom from damp;`
  line
  line `(d) natural light and air;`
  line
  line `(e) water supply;`
  line
  line `(f) drainage and sanitary conveniences;`
  line
  line `(g) facilities for storage, preparation and cooking of food and for the disposal of rubbish, filth and`
  line `other polluted matter,`
  line
  line `and the building shall be deemed to be unfit as aforesaid if it is so far defective, in one or more of the said`
  line `matters that it is not reasonably suitable for occupation in that condition.`
  line
  line `(7) For the purpose of section 277, section 278 and this section, "work of improvement" in relation to`
  line `a building includes any one or more of the following works, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) necessary repairs;`
  line
  line `(b) structural alterations;`
  line
  line `(c) provision of light points and water taps;`
  line
  line `(d) construction of drains, open or covered;`
  line
  line `(e) provision of latrines and urinals;`
  line
  line `(f) provision of additional or improved fixtures and fittings;`
  line
  line `(g) opening up or paving of courtyard;`
  line
  line `(h) removal of rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter;`
  line
  line `(i) any other work including the demolition of any building or any part thereof which, in the`
  line `opinion of the Chairperson, is necessary for executing any of the works specified above.`
  line
  line `(8) The provisions of section 276, section 277, section 278 and this section shall not apply in relation`
  line `to any building in any area which has been declared to be a slum area under the Slum Areas`
  line `(Improvement and Clearance) Act, 1956 (96 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_280:
  sectionId (48675)
  sectionNo (280)
  orderNo 280
  title `Insanitary huts and sheds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_280_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48675&sectionno=280&orderno=280&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_280_content:
  string
  line `Where the Chairperson upon any information in his possession is`
  line `satisfied that any hut or shed used as a dwelling house or as a stable or for any other purpose, is likely, by`
  line `reason of its being constructed without a plinth or upon a plinth of insufficient height or without proper`
  line `means of drainage or on account of the impracticability of scavenging and cleansing it or owing to the`
  line `manner in which it and other huts or sheds are crowded together, to cause risk of disease to the inmates`
  line `thereof or to the inhabitants of the neighbourhood, or is for any reason likely to endanger public health or`
  line `safety, he may by notice in writing require the owner or occupier of the hut or shed or the owner or`
  line `occupier of the land on which the hut or shed stands to remove or alter the hut or shed or carry out such`
  line `improvement thereof as the Chairperson may deem necessary within such time as may be specified in the`
  line notice.
obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_281:
  sectionId (48676)
  sectionNo (281)
  orderNo 281
  title `Prohibition against washing by washerman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_281_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48676&sectionno=281&orderno=281&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_281_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may by public notice`
  line `prohibit the washing of clothes by washermen in the exercise of their callings except at such places as he`
  line `may appoint for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) When any such prohibition has been made, no person who is by calling a washerman shall in`
  line `contravention of such prohibition wash clothes except for himself or for personal and family service or for`
  line `hire on or within the premises of the hirer, at any place other than a place appointed under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_282:
  sectionId (48677)
  sectionNo (282)
  orderNo 282
  title `Obligation to give information of dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_282_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48677&sectionno=282&orderno=282&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_282_content:
  string
  line `Any person being in charge of, or in`
  line `attendance, whether as a medical practitioner or otherwise, upon any person whom he knows or has`
  line `reason to believe to be suffering from a dangerous disease, or being the owner, lessee, or occupier of any`
  line `building in which he knows that any such person is so suffering shall forthwith give information`
  line `respecting the existence of such disease to the officer specified by the Chairperson for the said purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_283:
  sectionId (48678)
  sectionNo (283)
  orderNo 283
  title `Removal to hospital of patients, suffering from dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_283_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48678&sectionno=283&orderno=283&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_283_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person`
  line `suffering from any dangerous disease is found to be--`
  line
  line `(a) without proper lodging or accommodation; or`
  line
  line `(b) living in a room or house which he neither owns or pays rent for nor occupies as the guest or`
  line `relative of any person who owns, or pays rent for it; or`
  line
  line `(c) living in a sarai, dharamshala, hotel, boarding house, hostel, guest house, lodging house, club;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) lodged in premises occupied by members of two or more families,`
  line
  line `the Chairperson or any person authorised by him in this behalf, may on the advice of any medical officer`
  line `of the rank not inferior to that of a general duty medical officer remove the patient to any hospital or place`
  line `at which persons suffering from such diseases are received for medical treatment and may do anything`
  line `necessary for such removal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall if required by the Central Government erect an infectious disease hospital of`
  line `such type and dimension as that Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_284:
  sectionId (48679)
  sectionNo (284)
  orderNo 284
  title `Disinfection of buildings and articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_284_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48679&sectionno=284&orderno=284&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_284_content:
  string
  line `Where the Chairperson is of opinion that the cleansing`
  line `and disinfection of any building or part of a building or of any articles in such building or part which are`
  line `likely to retain infection, or the renewal of flooring of any building or part of such building, and the`
  line `renewal of plastering of the walls thereof, would tend to prevent or check the spread of any dangerous`
  line `disease; he may, by notice in writing, require the owner or occupier to cleanse and disinfect the said`
  line `building, part or articles, as the case may be, or to renew the said flooring and if necessary, the said`
  line `plastering also within such time as may be specified in the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that where in the opinion of the Chairperson the owner or occupier is from poverty or any`
  line `other cause unable effectually to carry out any such requisition, the Chairperson may at the expense of the`
  line `New Delhi Municipal Fund cleanse and disinfect the building, part or articles, or, as the case may be,`
  line `renew the flooring and if necessary, the plastering also.`
obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_285:
  sectionId (48680)
  sectionNo (285)
  orderNo 285
  title `Destruction of infectious huts or sheds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_285_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48680&sectionno=285&orderno=285&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_285_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the destruction of any hut or shed is in the`
  line `opinion of the Chairperson necessary to prevent the spread of any dangerous disease, the Chairperson`
  line `may by notice in writing require the owner to destroy the hut or shed and the materials thereof within`
  line `such time as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Chairperson is satisfied that the destruction of any hut or shed is immediately necessary`
  line `for the purpose of preventing the spread of any dangerous disease, he may order the owner or occupier of`
  line `the hut or shed to destroy the same forthwith or may himself cause it to be destroyed after giving not less`
  line `than six hours' notice to the owner or occupier.`
  line
  line `(3) Compensation may be paid by the Chairperson, in any case which he thinks fit, to any person who`
  line `sustains substantial loss by the destruction of any such hut or shed, but, except as so allowed by the`
  line `Chairperson, no claim for compensation shall lie for any loss or damage caused by any exercise of the`
  line `power conferred by this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_286:
  sectionId (48681)
  sectionNo (286)
  orderNo 286
  title `Means of disinfection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_286_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48681&sectionno=286&orderno=286&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_286_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall--`
  line
  line `(a) provide proper places with necessary attendants and apparatus for the disinfection of`
  line `conveyances, clothing, bedding and other articles which have been exposed to infection;`
  line
  line `(b) cause conveyances, clothing and other articles brought for disinfection to be disinfected either`
  line `free of charge or on payment of such charges as he may fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may notify places at which articles of clothing, bedding and the conveyances or`
  line `other articles which have been exposed to infection shall be washed and if he does so, no person shall`
  line `wash any such thing at any place not so notified without having previously disinfected such thing.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson may direct the destruction of any clothing, bedding or other article likely to`
  line `retain infection and may give such compensation as he thinks fit for any article so destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_287:
  sectionId (48682)
  sectionNo (287)
  orderNo 287
  title `Special measures in case of outbreak of dangerous or epidemic diseases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_287_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48682&sectionno=287&orderno=287&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_287_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event`
  line `of New Delhi or any part thereof being visited or threatened by an outbreak of any dangerous disease`
  line `among the inhabitants thereof or any epidemic disease among any animals therein, the Chairperson, if he`
  line `thinks that the other provisions of this Act and the provisions of any other law for the time being in force`
  line `are insufficient for the purpose, may, with the previous sanction of the Council--`
  line
  line `(a) take such special measures; and`
  line
  line `(b) by public notice, give such directions to be observed by the public or by any class or section`
  line `of the public,`
  line
  line `as he thinks necessary to prevent the outbreak or spread of the disease:`
  line
  line `Provided that where in the opinion of the Chairperson immediate measures are necessary, he may`
  line `take action, without such sanction as aforesaid and if he does so, shall forthwith report such action to the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) No person shall commit a breach of any direction given under sub-section (1) and if he does so he`
  line `shall be deemed to have committed an offence under section 188 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_288:
  sectionId (48683)
  sectionNo (288)
  orderNo 288
  title `Infected clothes not to be sent to washerman or to laundry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_288_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48683&sectionno=288&orderno=288&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_288_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not send or`
  line `take to any washerman or to any laundry or place set apart for the exercise by washerman of their calling,`
  line `for the purpose of being washed or to any place for the purpose of being cleansed, any cloth or other`
  line `article which he knows to have been exposed to infection from a dangerous disease unless that cloth or`
  line `article has been disinfected by or to the satisfaction of the officer authorised in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The occupier of any building in which a person is suffering from a dangerous disease shall, if`
  line `required by the officer authorised by the Chairperson, furnish to him the address of any washerman to`
  line `whom or any laundry or other place to which clothes and other articles from the building have been, or`
  line `will be, sent during the continuance of the disease, for the purpose of being washed or cleaned.`
obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_289:
  sectionId (48684)
  sectionNo (289)
  orderNo 289
  title `Contamination and disinfection of public conveyance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_289_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48684&sectionno=289&orderno=289&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_289_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) uses a public conveyance while suffering from a dangerous disease; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses a public conveyance for the carriage of a person who is suffering from any dangerous`
  line `disease; or`
  line
  line `(c) uses a public conveyance for the carriage of the corpse of a person who has died from any`
  line `such disease,`
  line
  line `shall be bound to take proper precautions against the communication of the disease to other persons using`
  line `or who may thereafter use the conveyance and to notify such use to the owner, driver, or person in charge`
  line `of the conveyance, and further report without delay to the Chairperson the number of the conveyance and`
  line `the name of the person so notified.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person suffering from, or the corpse of any person who has died from, a dangerous`
  line `disease has been carried in public conveyance which ordinarily plies in New Delhi or any part thereof, the`
  line `driver thereof shall forthwith report the fact to the Chairperson who shall forthwith cause the conveyance`
  line `to be disinfected if that has not already been done.`
  line
  line `(3) No such conveyance shall be again brought into use until the officer authorised by the`
  line `Chairperson has granted a certificate stating that it can be used without causing risk of infection.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever fails to make to the Chairperson any report which he is required to make under this`
  line `section shall be guilty of an offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_290:
  sectionId (48685)
  sectionNo (290)
  orderNo 290
  title `Driver of conveyance not bound to carry persons suffering from dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_290_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48685&sectionno=290&orderno=290&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_290_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force no owner, driver or person in`
  line `charge of a public conveyance shall be bound to convey or to allow to be conveyed in such conveyance in`
  line `or in the vicinity of New Delhi any person suffering from a dangerous disease or the corpse of any person`
  line `who has died from such disease unless and until such person pays or tenders a sum sufficient to cover any`
  line `loss and expense which would ordinarily be incurred in disinfecting the conveyance.`
obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_291:
  sectionId (48686)
  sectionNo (291)
  orderNo 291
  title `Disinfection of buildings before letting the same.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_291_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48686&sectionno=291&orderno=291&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_291_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any building or part of a`
  line `building is intended to be let in which any person has, within six weeks immediately preceding, been`
  line `suffering from a dangerous disease, the person letting the building or part shall, before doing so, disinfect`
  line `the same in such manner as the Chairperson may by general or special notice direct together with all`
  line `articles therein liable to retain infection.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section the keeper of a hostel, lodging house, dharamshala, sarai, boarding`
  line `house, guest house, hotel or club shall be deemed to have let to any person who is admitted as a guest`
  line `therein that part of the building in which such person is permitted to reside.`
obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_292:
  sectionId (48687)
  sectionNo (292)
  orderNo 292
  title `Disposal of infected articles without disinfection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_292_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48687&sectionno=292&orderno=292&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_292_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without previous`
  line `disinfection of the same, give, lend, sell, transmit or otherwise dispose of to another person any article or`
  line `thing which he knows or has reason to believe has been exposed to contamination by any dangerous`
  line `disease and is likely to be used in or taken into New Delhi or any part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_293:
  sectionId (48688)
  sectionNo (293)
  orderNo 293
  title `Prohibition of making or selling of food, etc., or washing of clothes by infected persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_293_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48688&sectionno=293&orderno=293&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_293_content:
  string
  line `No person while suffering from, or in circumstances in which he is likely to spread, any dangerous`
  line `disease, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) make, carry or offer for sale or take any part in the business of making, carrying or offering`
  line `for sale, any article of food or drink or any medicine or drug for human consumption, or any article of`
  line `clothing or bedding for personal use or wear; or`
  line
  line `(b) take any part in the business of the washing or carrying of clothes.`
obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_294:
  sectionId (48689)
  sectionNo (294)
  orderNo 294
  title `Power to restrict or prohibit sale of food or drink.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_294_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48689&sectionno=294&orderno=294&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_294_content:
  string
  line `When New Delhi or any part thereof is`
  line `visited or threatened by an outbreak of any dangerous disease the Chairperson may, by public notice,`
  line `restrict in such manner or prohibit for such period as may be specified in the notice, the sale or`
  line `preparation of any article of food or drink for human consumption specified in the notice or the sale of`
  line `any flesh of any description of animal so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_295:
  sectionId (48690)
  sectionNo (295)
  orderNo 295
  title `Control over wells and tanks, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_295_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48690&sectionno=295&orderno=295&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_295_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Chairperson is of opinion that the water in any`
  line `well, tank or other place, is likely, if used for drinking, to endanger, or cause the spread of, any disease,`
  line `he may--`
  line
  line `(a) by public notice, prohibit the removal or use of such water for drinking; or`
  line
  line `(b) by notice in writing require the owner or person having control of such well, tank or place to`
  line `take such steps as may be directed by the notice to prevent the public from having access to or using`
  line `such water; or`
  line
  line `(c) take such other steps as he may consider expedient to prevent the outbreak or spread of any`
  line `such disease.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of New Delhi or any part thereof being visited or threatened by an outbreak or a`
  line `dangerous disease the officer authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf may, without notice and at any`
  line `time, inspect and disinfect any well, tank or other place from which water is, or is likely to be, taken for`
  line `the purposes of drinking and may further take such steps as he may think fit to ensure the purity of the`
  line `water or to prevent the use of the same for drinking purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_296:
  sectionId (48691)
  sectionNo (296)
  orderNo 296
  title `Duty of persons suffering from dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_296_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48691&sectionno=296&orderno=296&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_296_content:
  string
  line `No person shall--`
  line
  line `(a) knowing that he is suffering from a dangerous disease expose other persons to the risk of`
  line `infection by his presence or conduct in any public street or public place;`
  line
  line `(b) having the care of a person whom he knows to be suffering from a dangerous disease, cause`
  line `or permit that person to expose other persons to the risk of infection by his presence or conduct in any`
  line `such street or place as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(c) place or cause to be placed in a dustbin or other receptacle for the deposit of rubbish, any`
  line `matter which he knows to have been exposed to infection from a dangerous disease and which has not`
  line `been disinfected properly;`
  line
  line `(d) throw or cause to be thrown into any latrine or urinal any matter which he knows to have been`
  line `exposed to infection from a dangerous disease and which has not been disinfected properly.`
obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_297:
  sectionId (48692)
  sectionNo (297)
  orderNo 297
  title `Disposal of infectious corpses where any person has died from any dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_297_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48692&sectionno=297&orderno=297&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_297_content:
  string
  line `Where any person has died from any dangerous disease the Chairperson may, by notice in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) require any person having charge of the corpse to convey the same to mortuary thereafter to`
  line `be disposed of in accordance with law, or`
  line
  line `(b) prohibit the removal of corpses from the place where death occurred except for the purpose of`
  line `being burnt, buried or for being conveyed to a mortuary.`
obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_298:
  sectionId (48828)
  sectionNo (298)
  orderNo 298
  title `Conditions of service of sweepers and certain other class of persons employed in municipal service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_298_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48828&sectionno=298&orderno=298&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_298_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person being a sweeper employed by the Council shall in the absence of any contract`
  line `authorising him so to do and without reasonable cause, resign his employment or absent himself from his`
  line `duty without having given one month's notice to the Chairperson or shall neglect or without reasonable`
  line `cause refuse to perform his duties.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may by resolution direct that on or from such date as may be specified in the`
  line `resolution, the provisions of this section shall apply in the case of any specified class of persons employed`
  line `by the Council whose functions are intimately concerned with public health or safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_299:
  sectionId (48694)
  sectionNo (299)
  orderNo 299
  title `Conditions of service of sweepers employed for doing house scavenging.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_299_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48694&sectionno=299&orderno=299&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_299_content:
  string
  line `No sweeper,`
  line `being employed for doing house scavenging of any building shall discontinue to do such house`
  line `scavenging without reasonable cause or without having fourteen days notice to his employer.`
obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_300:
  sectionId (48695)
  sectionNo (300)
  orderNo 300
  title `Power to call for information regarding burning and burial grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_300_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48695&sectionno=300&orderno=300&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_300_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson`
  line `may, by notice in writing, require the owner or person in charge of any burning or burial ground to supply`
  line `such information as may be specified in the notice concerning the condition, management or position of`
  line `such ground.`
obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_301:
  sectionId (48696)
  sectionNo (301)
  orderNo 301
  title `Permission for use of new burning or burial ground.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_301_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48696&sectionno=301&orderno=301&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_301_content:
  string
  line `(1) No place which has not been used`
  line `as a burning or burial ground before the commencement of this Act shall be so used without the`
  line `permission in writing of the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) Such permission may be granted subject to any conditions which the Chairperson may think fit to`
  line `impose for the purpose of preventing any annoyance to, or danger to the health of, any person residing in`
  line `the neighbourhood`
obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_302:
  sectionId (48697)
  sectionNo (302)
  orderNo 302
  title `Power to require closing of burning and burial grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_302_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48697&sectionno=302&orderno=302&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_302_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Chairperson, after`
  line `making or causing to be made local inquiry is of opinion that any burning or burial ground has become`
  line `offensive to, or dangerous to the health of, persons residing in the neighbourhood, he may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Council, by notice in writing, require the owner or person in charge of such`
  line `ground to close the same from such date as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) No corpse shall be burnt or buried at the burning or burial ground in respect of which a notice has`
  line `been issued under this section`
obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_303:
  sectionId (48698)
  sectionNo (303)
  orderNo 303
  title `Removal of corpses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_303_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48698&sectionno=303&orderno=303&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_303_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may by public notice prescribe routes by which alone`
  line `corpses may be removed to burning or burial ground.`
obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_304:
  sectionId (48699)
  sectionNo (304)
  orderNo 304
  title `Disposal of dead animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_304_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48699&sectionno=304&orderno=304&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_304_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any animal in the charge of any person dies, the person`
  line `in charge thereof shall within twenty-four hours either--`
  line
  line `(a) convey the carcass to a place provided or appointed under section 263 for the final disposal of`
  line `the carcasses of dead animals, or`
  line
  line `(b) give notice of the death to the Chairperson whereupon he shall cause the carcass to be`
  line `disposed of on such fee as may be prescribed by the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_305:
  sectionId (48700)
  sectionNo (305)
  orderNo 305
  title `Appointment of Chief Registrar, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_305_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48700&sectionno=305&orderno=305&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_305_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Registration of Births and Deaths Act, 1969 (18 of 1969), but subject to the provisions to this Act and to`
  line `any directions that the Central Government may give in this behalf, the officer specified in the Official`
  line `Gazette by the Chairperson, shall be the Chief Registrar of Births and Deaths for New Delhi and shall`
  line `keep in such form as may be prescribed by bye-laws a register of all births and deaths occurring in New`
  line Delhi.
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall for the purposes of this Chapter appoint an additional chief registrar and`
  line `such number of persons to be registrars of births and deaths for New Delhi as he deems necessary and`
  line `define the respective areas which shall be under the charge of such registrars.`
obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_306:
  sectionId (48701)
  sectionNo (306)
  orderNo 306
  title `Duties of registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_306_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48701&sectionno=306&orderno=306&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_306_content:
  string
  line `The registrar shall keep himself informed of every birth or death`
  line `occurring within the area under his charge and shall ascertain and register as soon as conveniently may be`
  line `after the event, and without fee or reward such particulars in respect of every birth or death as may be`
  line `prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_307:
  sectionId (48702)
  sectionNo (307)
  orderNo 307
  title `Information of births and deaths.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_307_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48702&sectionno=307&orderno=307&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_307_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the father or mother of every`
  line `child born in New Delhi and in default of the father or mother, of any relation of the child living in the`
  line `same premises, and in default of such relation, of the person having charge of the child, to give to the best`
  line `of his knowledge and belief to the registrar of the area concerned within eight days after such birth,`
  line `information containing such particulars as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the nearest relation present at the time of the death or in attendance during`
  line `the last illness of any person dying in New Delhi and in default of such relation, of any person present or`
  line `in attendance at the time of the death and of the occupier of the premises in which to his knowledge the`
  line `death took place and in default of the person hereinbefore mentioned, of each inmate of such premises`
  line `and of the undertaker or other person causing the corpse of the deceased person to be disposed of, to give`
  line `to the best of his knowledge and belief to the registrar of the area within which the death place`
  line `information containing such particulars as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) If a birth or death occurs in the hospital, none of the persons mentioned in sub-section (1) or, as`
  line `the case may be, in sub-section (2) shall be bound to give information required by that sub-section, but it`
  line `shall be the duty of the medical officer in charge of the hospital within twenty-four hours after the birth or`
  line `death, to send to the officer authorised by the Chairperson, a notice containing such particulars as may be`
  line `prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_308:
  sectionId (48703)
  sectionNo (308)
  orderNo 308
  title `Prohibition of nuisances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_308_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48703&sectionno=308&orderno=308&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_308_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall--`
  line
  line `(a) in any public street or public place--`
  line
  line `(i) ease himself; or`
  line
  line `(ii) carry meat exposed to public view; or`
  line
  line `(iii) picket animals or collect carts; or`
  line
  line `(iv) being engaged in the removal of rubbish, filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter`
  line `wilfully or negligently permit any portion thereof to spill or fall, or neglect to sweep away or`
  line `otherwise effectually to remove any portion thereof which may spill or fall in such street or place;`
  line or
  line
  line `(v) without proper authority affix, upon any building, monument, post, wall, fence, tree or`
  line `other thing, any bill, notice or other document; or`
  line
  line `(vi) without proper authority deface or write upon or otherwise mark any building,`
  line `monument, post, wall, fence, tree or other thing; or`
  line
  line `(vii) without proper authority remove, destroy, deface or otherwise obliterate any notice or`
  line `other document put up or exhibited under this Act or the rules or bye-laws made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(viii) without proper authority displace, damage, make any alteration in, or otherwise interfere`
  line `with, the pavement, gutter, storm, water-drain, flags or other materials of any such street, or any`
  line `lamp bracket, direction-post, hydrant or water-pipe maintained by the Council in any such street`
  line `or place or extinguish a public light; or`
  line
  line `(ix) carry rubbish, filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter at any hour prohibited by the`
  line `Chairperson by public notice, or in any pattern of cart or receptacle which has not been approved`
  line `for the purpose by the Chairperson, or fail to close such cart or receptacle when in use; or`
  line
  line `(b) carry rubbish, filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter along any route in contravention of`
  line `any prohibition made in this behalf by the Chairperson by public notice; or`
  line
  line `(c) deposit or cause or permit to be deposited, earth or materials of any description or any rubbish`
  line `or polluted and obnoxious matter in any place not intended for the purpose in any public street or`
  line `public place or waste or unoccupied land under the control and management of the Council; or`
  line
  line `(d) make any grave or burn or bury any corpse at any place not set apart for such purpose; or`
  line
  line `(e) at any time or place at which the same has been prohibited by the Chairperson by public or`
  line `special notice, beat a drum or tom-tom, or blow a horn or trumpet, or beat any utensil, or sound any`
  line `brass or other instrument, or play any music; or`
  line
  line `(f) disturb the public peace or order by singing, screaming or shouting, or by using any apparatus`
  line `for amplifying or reproducing the human voice, such as a megaphone or a loudspeaker; or`
  line
  line `(g) let loose any animal so as to cause, or negligently allow any animal to cause injury, danger,`
  line `alarm or annoyance to any person; or`
  line
  line `(h) save with the written permission of the Chairperson and in such manner as he may authorise,`
  line `store or use night-soil, cowdung, manure, rubbish or any other substance emitting an offensive smell;`
  line or
  line
  line `(i) use or permit to be used as a latrine or urinal any place not intended for that purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person shall take all reasonable means to prevent every child under the age of twelve years`
  line `being in his charge from easing himself in any public street or public place.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner or keeper of any animal shall not allow it straying in a public street or public place`
  line `without a keeper.`
  line
  line `(4) Any animal found straying as aforesaid may be removed by an officer or employee of the Council`
  line `or by any police officer to a pound.`
  line
  line `(5) Swine found straying in a public street or public place shall be liable to be destroyed by any`
  line `officer or other employee of the Council appointed in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_309:
  sectionId (48704)
  sectionNo (309)
  orderNo 309
  title `Power of Chairperson to require removal or abatement of nuisance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_309_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48704&sectionno=309&orderno=309&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_309_content:
  string
  line `Where the`
  line `Chairperson is of opinion that there is a nuisance on any land or building, he may, by notice in writing,`
  line `require the person by whose act, default or sufferance the nuisance arises or continues or the power,`
  line `lessee or occupier of the land or building, or any or more or these persons, to remove or abate the`
  line `nuisance by taking such measures in such manner and within such period as may be specified in the`
  line notice.
obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_310:
  sectionId (48705)
  sectionNo (310)
  orderNo 310
  title `Registration and control of dogs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_310_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48705&sectionno=310&orderno=310&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_310_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, by bye-laws made in this behalf,--`
  line
  line `(a) require the registration, by the registration authority appointed by the Chairperson in this`
  line `behalf of all dogs kept within New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b) require that every registered dog shall wear a collar to which shall be attached a metal token to`
  line `be issued by the registration authority, and fix and fee payable for the issue thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) require that any dog which has not been registered or which is not wearing such token shall, if`
  line `found in any public place, be detained at a place set apart for the purpose; and`
  line
  line `(d) fix the fee which shall be charged for such detention and provide that any such dog shall be`
  line `liable to be destroyed or otherwise disposed of unless it is claimed and the fee in respect thereof is`
  line `paid within one week.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may--`
  line
  line `(a) cause to be destroyed, or to be confined for such period as he may direct, any dog or other`
  line `animal which is, or is reasonably suspected to be, suffering from rabies, or which has been bitten by`
  line `any dog or other animal suffering or suspected to be suffering from rabies;`
  line
  line `(b) by public notice direct that, after such date as may be specified in the notice, dogs which are`
  line `without collars or without marks distinguishing them as private property and are found straying on the streets or beyond the enclosures of the houses of their owners, if any, may be destroyed and cause`
  line `them to be destroyed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) No damages shall be payable in respect of any dog or other animal destroyed or otherwise`
  line `disposed of under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) No one, being the owner or person in charge of any dog, shall allow it to be at large in any public`
  line `street or public place without being muzzled and without being secured by a chain lead in any case in`
  line which--
  line
  line `(a) he knows that the dog is likely to annoy or intimidate any person, or`
  line
  line `(b) the Chairperson has, by public notice during the prevalence of rabies, directed that dogs shall`
  line `not be at large without muzzles and chain leads.`
  line
  line `(5) No one shall--`
  line
  line `(a) allow any ferocious dog which belongs to him or is in his charge to be at large without being`
  line `muzzled; or`
  line
  line `(b) set on or urge any dog or other animal to attack, worry or intimidate any person;`
  line
  line or
  line
  line `(c) knowing or having reason to believe that any dog or animal belonging to him or in his charge`
  line `has been bitten by an animal suffering or reasonably suspected to be suffering from rabies, fail or`
  line `neglect to give immediate information of the fact to the Chairperson or give information which is`
  line false.
obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_311:
  sectionId (48706)
  sectionNo (311)
  orderNo 311
  title `Stacking or collecting inflammable materials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_311_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48706&sectionno=311&orderno=311&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_311_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may, by public notice,`
  line `prohibit in any case where such prohibition appears to him to be necessary for the prevention of danger to`
  line `life or property, the stacking or collecting of wood, dry grass, straw or other inflammable materials, or the`
  line `placing of mats or thatched huts or the lighting of fires in any place which may be specified in the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_312:
  sectionId (48707)
  sectionNo (312)
  orderNo 312
  title `Care of naked lights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_312_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48707&sectionno=312&orderno=312&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_312_content:
  string
  line `No person shall set a naked light on or near any building in any public`
  line `street or other public place in such manner as to cause danger of fire:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prohibit the use of lights for the purposes of`
  line `illumination on the occasion of a festival or public or private entertainment.`
obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_313:
  sectionId (48708)
  sectionNo (313)
  orderNo 313
  title `Discharging fire works, fire-arms, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_313_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48708&sectionno=313&orderno=313&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_313_content:
  string
  line `No one shall discharge any fire-arm or let off`
  line `fire-works or fire-baloons, or engage in any game in such manner as to cause or to be likely to cause`
  line `danger to persons passing by or dwelling or working in the neighbourhood or risk of injury to property.`
obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_314:
  sectionId (48709)
  sectionNo (314)
  orderNo 314
  title `Power to require buildings, wells, etc., to be rendered safe.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_314_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48709&sectionno=314&orderno=314&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_314_content:
  string
  line `Where any building, or wall, or`
  line `anything affixed thereto, or any well, tank, reservoir, pool, depression, or excavation, or any bank or tree,`
  line `is in the opinion of the Chairperson, in a ruinous state, for want of sufficient repairs, protection or`
  line `enclosure, a nuisance or dangerous to persons passing by or dwelling or working in the neighbourhood,`
  line `the Chairperson may by notice in writing require the owner or part-owner or person claiming to be the`
  line `owner or part-owner thereof or failing any of them the occupier thereof to remove the same or may`
  line `require him to repair, protect or enclose the same in such manner as he thinks necessary; and if the danger`
  line `is, in the opinion of the Chairperson, imminent, he shall forthwith take such steps as he thinks necessary`
  line `to avert the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_315:
  sectionId (48710)
  sectionNo (315)
  orderNo 315
  title `Enclosure of waste land used for improper purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_315_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48710&sectionno=315&orderno=315&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_315_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may, by notice in`
  line `writing, require the owner or part-owner, or person claiming to be the owner or part-owner of any land or`
  line `building, or the lessee, or the person claiming to be the lessee of any such land which, by reason of disuse`
  line `or disputed ownership or other cause, has remained unoccupied and has become the resort of idle and`
  line `disorderly persons or of persons who have no ostensible means of subsistence or cannot give a`
  line `satisfactory account of themselves or is used for gaming or immoral purposes or otherwise occasions or is`
  line `likely to occasion a nuisance, to secure and enclose the same within such time as may be specified in the`
  line notice.
obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_316:
  sectionId (48711)
  sectionNo (316)
  orderNo 316
  title `Provision of municipal market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_316_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48711&sectionno=316&orderno=316&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_316_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson, when authorised by the Council in this`
  line `behalf, may provide and maintain municipal markets and slaughter houses in such number as he thinks fit`
  line `together with stalls, shops, sheds, pens, and other buildings and conveniences for the use of persons`
  line `carrying on trade or business in, or frequenting such markets or slaughter house, and may provide and`
  line `maintain in any such markets buildings and places, machines, weights, scales and measures for the`
  line `weighment or measurement of goods sold therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Municipal markets and slaughter houses shall be under the control of the Chairperson who may, at`
  line `any time, by public notice, close any municipal market, slaughter house or any part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_317:
  sectionId (48712)
  sectionNo (317)
  orderNo 317
  title `Use of municipal markets and slaughter house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_317_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48712&sectionno=317&orderno=317&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_317_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, without the general or`
  line `special permission in writing of the Chairperson, sell or expose for sale any animal or article in any`
  line `municipal market.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person contravening the provisions of sub-section (1), and any animal or article exposed for`
  line `sale by such person, may be summarily removed from the market by or under the orders of the`
  line `Chairperson or any officer or employee of the Council authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_318:
  sectionId (48713)
  sectionNo (318)
  orderNo 318
  title `Private markets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_318_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48713&sectionno=318&orderno=318&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_318_content:
  string
  line `(1) No place other than a municipal market shall be used as a market unless`
  line `such place has been licensed as a market by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) No place other than a municipal slaughter house shall be used as a slaughter house:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed--`
  line
  line `(i) to restrict the slaughter of any animal in any place on the occasion of any religious festival or`
  line `ceremony, subject to such conditions (non-compliance with which shall be punishable under this Act)`
  line `as the Chairperson may, by public or special notice, impose in this behalf, or`
  line
  line `(ii) to prevent the Chairperson, with the sanction of the Council, from setting apart place for the`
  line `slaughter of animal in accordance with religious custom.`
obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_319:
  sectionId (48714)
  sectionNo (319)
  orderNo 319
  title `Conditions of grant of licence for private market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_319_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48714&sectionno=319&orderno=319&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_319_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may charge such`
  line `fees as the Council may prescribe in this behalf for the grant of a licence to any person to open a private`
  line `market and may grant such licence subject to such conditions, consistent with this Act and any bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Council refuses to grant any licence, it shall record a brief statement of the reasons for`
  line `such refusal.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson may, for reasons to be recorded, suspend a licence in respect of a private market`
  line `for such period as he thinks fit, or cancel his licence.`
  line
  line `(4) A private market of which the licence has been suspended or cancelled as aforesaid shall be closed`
  line `with effect from such date as may be specified in the order of suspension or cancellation.`
obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_320:
  sectionId (48715)
  sectionNo (320)
  orderNo 320
  title `Prohibition of keeping market open without licence, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_320_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48715&sectionno=320&orderno=320&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_320_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall keep open for`
  line `public use any market in respect of which a licence is required by or under this Act without obtaining a`
  line `licence therefor, or while the licence therefor is suspended or after the same has been cancelled.`
  line
  line `(2) When a licence to open a private market is granted or refused or is suspended or cancelled the`
  line `Chairperson shall cause a notice of the grant, refusal, suspension or cancellation to be posted in such`
  line `language or languages as he thinks necessary in some conspicuous place by or near the entrance to the`
  line `place to which the notice relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_321:
  sectionId (48716)
  sectionNo (321)
  orderNo 321
  title `Prohibition of use of unlicensed markets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_321_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48716&sectionno=321&orderno=321&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_321_content:
  string
  line `No person knowing that market has been opened`
  line `to the public without a licence having been obtained therefor when such licence is required by or under`
  line `this Act or that the licence granted therefor is for the time being suspended or that it has been cancelled,`
  line `shall sell or expose for sale any animal or article in such market.`
obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_322:
  sectionId (48717)
  sectionNo (322)
  orderNo 322
  title `Prohibition of business and trade near a market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_322_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48717&sectionno=322&orderno=322&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_322_content:
  string
  line `(1) No animal or article shall be sold or`
  line `exposed for sale within a distance of one hundred metres of any municipal market or licensed private`
  line `market without the permission of the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person contravening the provisions of sub-section (1) and any animal or article exposed for`
  line `sale by such person may be summarily removed by or under the orders of the Chairperson or any officer`
  line `or employee of the Council appointed by him in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_323:
  sectionId (48718)
  sectionNo (323)
  orderNo 323
  title `Levy of stallages, rents and fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_323_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48718&sectionno=323&orderno=323&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_323_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Council may--`
  line
  line `(a) charge such stallages, rents and fees as may from time to time be fixed by him in this behalf--`
  line
  line `(i) for the occupation or use of any stall, shop, stand, shed or pen in a municipal market or`
  line `municipal slaughter house;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the right to expose articles for sale in a municipal market;`
  line
  line `(iii) for the use of machines, weights, scales and measures provided for in any municipal`
  line `market; and`
  line
  line `(iv) for the right to slaughter animals in any municipal slaughter house, and for the feed of`
  line `such animals before they are ready for slaughter; or`
  line
  line `(b) farm the stallages, rents and fees chargeable as aforesaid or any portion thereof for such`
  line `period as he thinks fit; or`
  line
  line `(c) put up to public auction or dispose by the private sale the privilege of occupying or using any`
  line `stall, shop, shed or pen in a municipal market or municipal slaughter house for such period and on`
  line `such conditions as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the table of stallages and fees, if any, chargeable in any municipal market in New Delhi`
  line `and of the bye-laws made under this Act for the purpose of regulating the use of such market printed in`
  line `such language or languages as the Chairperson may direct, shall be affixed in some conspicuous place in`
  line `the market.`
obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_324:
  sectionId (48719)
  sectionNo (324)
  orderNo 324
  title `Power to expel disturbers, etc., from markets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_324_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48719&sectionno=324&orderno=324&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_324_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may prevent the entry in any`
  line `market and shall expel therefrom, any person suffering from any dangerous disease, who sells or exposes`
  line `for sale therein any article or who, not having purchased the same handles any article exposed for sale`
  line `therein; and he may expel therefrom any person who is creating a disturbance therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_325:
  sectionId (48720)
  sectionNo (325)
  orderNo 325
  title `Butcher's fish-monger's and poulter's licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_325_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48720&sectionno=325&orderno=325&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_325_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall without or otherwise than`
  line `in conformity with a licence from the Chairperson carry on the trade of a butcher, fish-monger, poulterer`
  line `or importer of flesh intended for human consumption or use any place for the sale of flesh, fish or poultry`
  line `intended for human consumption:`
  line
  line `Provided that no licence shall be required for any place used for the sale or storage for sale of`
  line `preserved flesh or fish contained in air-tight or hermetically sealed receptacles.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may order and subject to such conditions as to supervision and inspection as he`
  line `thinks fit to impose grant a licence or may by order refuse for reasons to be recorded, to grant the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such licence shall expire at the end of the year for which it is granted or at such earlier date`
  line `as the Chairperson may, for special reasons, specify in the licence.`
  line
  line `(4) If any place is used for the sale of flesh, fish or poultry in contravention of the provisions of this`
  line `section, the Chairperson may stop the use thereof by such means as he may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(5) (i) If the Chairperson or any person authorised by him in this behalf has reason to believe that any`
  line `animal intended for human consumption is being slaughtered or that the flesh of any such animals is`
  line `being sold or exposed for sale, in any place or manner not duly authorised under this Act, he may at any`
  line `time by day or night without notice inspect such place for the purpose of satisfying himself as to whether`
  line `any provision of this Act or of any bye-law under this Act at the time in force is being contravened thereat`
  line `and may seize any such animal or the carcass of such animal or such flesh found therein.`
  line
  line `(ii) The Chairperson may remove and sell by auction or otherwise dispose of any animal or carcass of`
  line `any animal or any flesh seized under clause (i) of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(iii) If within one month of such seizure the owner of the animal, carcass or flesh fails to appear and`
  line `prove his claim to the satisfaction of the Chairperson or if the owner is convicted of an offence under this`
  line `Act in respect of such animal, carcass or flesh, the proceeds of any sale under clause (i) of this sub-section`
  line `shall vest in the Council.`
  line
  line `(iv) Any person slaughtering any animal or selling or exposing for sale the flesh of any such animal in`
  line `any place or manner not duly authorised under the provisions of this Act may be arrested by any police`
  line `officer without a warrant.`
  line
  line `(v) No claim shall lie against any person for compensation for any damage necessarily caused by any`
  line `such entry or by the use of any force necessary for affecting such entry.`
obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_326:
  sectionId (48721)
  sectionNo (326)
  orderNo 326
  title `Factory, etc., not to be established without permission of the Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_326_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48721&sectionno=326&orderno=326&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_326_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person`
  line `shall, without the previous permission in writing of the Chairperson, establish in any premises, or`
  line `materially alter, enlarge or extend, any factory, workshop or trade premises in which it is intended to`
  line `employ steam, electricity, water or other mechanical power.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may refuse to give such permission, if he is of the opinion that the establishment,`
  line `alteration, enlargement or extension of such factory, workshop or trade premises, in the proposed position`
  line `would be objectionable by reason of the density of the population in the neighbourhood thereof, or would`
  line `be a nuisance to the inhabitants of the neighbourhood.`
obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_327:
  sectionId (48722)
  sectionNo (327)
  orderNo 327
  title `Premises not to be used for certain purposes without licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_327_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48722&sectionno=327&orderno=327&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_327_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall use or`
  line `permit to be used any premises for any of the following purposes without or otherwise than in conformity`
  line `with the terms of a licence granted by the Chairperson in this behalf, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) any of the purposes specified in Part I of the Ninth Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) any purpose which is, in the opinion of the Chairperson dangerous to life, health or property`
  line `or likely to create a nuisance;`
  line
  line `(c) keeping horses, cattle or other quadruped animals or birds for transportation, sale or hire or for`
  line `sale of the produce thereof; or`
  line
  line `(d) storing any of the articles specified in Part II of the Ninth Schedule except for domestic use of`
  line `any of those articles:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council may declare that premises in which the aggregate quantity of articles stored`
  line `for sale does not exceed such quantity as may be prescribed by bye-laws in respect of any such articles`
  line `shall be exempted from the operation of clause (d).`
  line
  line `(2) In prescribing the terms of a licence granted under this section for the use of premises as mills or`
  line `iron yards or for similar purposes the Chairperson may, when he thinks fit, require the licensee to provide`
  line `a space or passage within the premises for carts for loading and unloading purposes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall fix a scale of fees to be paid in respect of premises licensed under`
  line `sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall exceed five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_328:
  sectionId (48723)
  sectionNo (328)
  orderNo 328
  title `Seizure of certain animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_328_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48723&sectionno=328&orderno=328&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_328_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any horses, cattle or other quardruped animals or birds are`
  line `kept on any premises in contravention of the provisions of section 327, or are found abandoned and`
  line `roaming or tethered on any street or public place or on any land belonging to the Council, the Chairperson`
  line `or any officer empowered by him may seize them and may cause them to be impounded or removed to`
  line `such place as may be appointed by the Government or the Council for this purpose and the cost of seizure`
  line `of these animals or birds and of impounding or removing them and of feeding and watering them shall be`
  line `recoverable by sale by auction of these animals or birds:`
  line
  line `Provided that anyone claiming such animal or bird may, within seven days of the seizure get them`
  line `released on his paying all expenses incurred by the Chairperson in seizing, impounding or removing and in feeding and watering such animal or bird, and on his producing a licence for keeping these animals and`
  line `birds issued under the provisions of section 327.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever the Chairperson is of opinion that the user or any premises for any of the purposes`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) of section 327 is causing a nuisance and such nuisance should be`
  line `immediately stopped, the Chairperson may order the owner or the occupier of the premises to stop such`
  line `nuisance within such time as may be specified in the order and in the event of the failure of the owner or`
  line `occupier to comply with such order, the Chairperson may himself or by an officer subordinate to him`
  line `cause such user to be stopped.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this section any person by whom or at whose`
  line `instance any horses, cattle or other quadruped animals or birds are so kept, abandoned or tethered, shall`
  line `also be punishable under this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_329:
  sectionId (48827)
  sectionNo (329)
  orderNo 329
  title `Power of Chairperson to prevent use of premises in particular areas for purposes referred to in section 327.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_329_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48827&sectionno=329&orderno=329&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_329_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson may give public notice of his intention to declare that in any area`
  line `specified in the notice no person shall use any premises for any of the purposes referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 327, which may be specified in such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) No objections to any such declaration shall be received after a period of one month from the`
  line `publication of the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall consider all objections received within the said period, giving any person`
  line `affected by the notice an opportunity of being heard during such consideration, and may thereupon make`
  line `a declaration in accordance with the notice published under sub-section (1), with such modifications, if`
  line `any, as he may think but not so as to extend its application.`
  line
  line `(4) Every such declaration shall be published in the Official Gazette and in such other manner as the`
  line `Chairperson may determine, and shall take effect from the date of its publication in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) No person shall, in any area specified in any declaration published under sub-section (4) use any`
  line `premises for any of the purposes referred to in section 327 specified in the declaration and the`
  line `Chairperson shall have the power to stop the use of any such premises by such means as he considers`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_330:
  sectionId (48725)
  sectionNo (330)
  orderNo 330
  title `Licences for hawking articles, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_330_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48725&sectionno=330&orderno=330&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_330_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without or otherwise than in conformity`
  line `with the terms of a licence granted by the Chairperson in this behalf,--`
  line
  line `(a) hawk or expose for sale in any place any article whatsoever whether it be for human`
  line `consumption or not;`
  line
  line `(b) use in any place his skill in any handicraft or for rendering services to and for the convenience`
  line `of the public for the purposes of gain or making a living`
obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_331:
  sectionId (48726)
  sectionNo (331)
  orderNo 331
  title `Eating houses, etc., not to be used without licence from the Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_331_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48726&sectionno=331&orderno=331&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_331_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person`
  line `shall, without or otherwise than in conformity with the terms of a licence granted by the Chairperson in`
  line `this behalf, keep any eating house, lodging house, hotel, boarding house, tea shop, coffee house, cafe,`
  line `restaurant, refreshment room or any place where the public are admitted for repose or for the consumption`
  line `of any food or drink or any place, where food is sold or prepared for sale.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson may at any time cancel or suspend any licence granted under sub-section (1) if`
  line `he is of the opinion that the premises covered thereby are not kept in conformity with the conditions of`
  line `such licence or with the provisions of any bye-law made in this behalf, whether the licensee is prosecuted`
  line `under this Act or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_332:
  sectionId (48727)
  sectionNo (332)
  orderNo 332
  title `Licensing and control of theatres, circuses and places of public amusement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_332_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48727&sectionno=332&orderno=332&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_332_content:
  string
  line `No person`
  line `shall, without or otherwise than in conformity with the terms of a licence granted by the Chairperson in`
  line `this behalf, keep open any theatre, circus, cinema house, dancing hall or other similar place of public`
  line `resort, recreation or amusement:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to private performances in any such place.`
obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_333:
  sectionId (48728)
  sectionNo (333)
  orderNo 333
  title `Power of Chairperson to stop use of premises used in contravention of licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_333_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48728&sectionno=333&orderno=333&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_333_content:
  string
  line `If the`
  line `Chairperson is of opinion that any eating house, lodging house, hotel, boarding house, tea shop, coffee house, cafe, restaurant, refreshment room or other place where the public are admitted for repose or for`
  line `consumption of any food or drink or where food is sold or prepared for sale or any theatre, circus, cinema`
  line `house, dancing hall or similar other place of public resort, recreation or amusement is kept open without a`
  line `licence or otherwise than in conformity with the terms of a licence granted in respect thereof, he may stop`
  line `the use of any such premises for any such purpose for a specified period by such means as he may`
  line `consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_334:
  sectionId (48729)
  sectionNo (334)
  orderNo 334
  title `Improvement scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_334_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48729&sectionno=334&orderno=334&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_334_content:
  string
  line `Where the Chairperson upon information in his possession is satisfied`
  line `as respects any area--`
  line
  line `(a) that the buildings in that area are by reason of disrepair or sanitary defects unfit for human`
  line `habitation or are by reason of their bad arrangement, or the narrowness or bad arrangement of the`
  line `streets or the want of light, air, ventilation or proper conveniences, dangerous or injurious to the`
  line `health of the inhabitants of the area; and`
  line
  line `(b) that the most satisfactory method of dealing with the conditions in the area is the`
  line `re-arrangement and reconstruction of the streets and buildings in the area in accordance with an`
  line `improvement scheme,`
  line
  line `he may frame an improvement scheme in respect of the area in accordance with the bye-laws made in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_335:
  sectionId (48730)
  sectionNo (335)
  orderNo 335
  title `Matters to be provided for in an improvement scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_335_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48730&sectionno=335&orderno=335&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_335_content:
  string
  line `(1) An improvement scheme may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the acquisition by agreement or under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), of any`
  line `property necessary for or affected by the execution of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) the relaying out of any land comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) the redistribution of sites belonging to owners of property comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(d) the closure or demolition of buildings or portions of buildings unfit for human habitation;`
  line
  line `(e) the demolition of obstructive buildings or portions thereof;`
  line
  line `(f) the construction and reconstruction of buildings;`
  line
  line `(g) the construction and alteration of streets;`
  line
  line `(h) the water supply, street lighting, electric supply, drainage and other conveniences;`
  line
  line `(i) the provision of open spaces for the benefit of any area comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(j) the sanitary arrangements required for the area comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(k) the provision of accommodation for any class of the inhabitants;`
  line
  line `(l) the provision of facilities for communication;`
  line
  line `(m) the sale, letting or exchange of any property comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter for which, in the opinion of the Chairperson it is expedient to make provision`
  line `with a view to the improvement of the area to which the scheme relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any land is designated in an improvement scheme as subject to acquisition or is required by`
  line `the scheme to be kept as an open space, then, if at the expiration of ten years from the date of sanction of`
  line `the scheme by the Central Government under sub-section (2) of section 336 the land is not acquired by`
  line `the Chairperson, the owner of the land may serve on the Chairperson a notice requiring his interest in the`
  line `land to be so acquired.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Chairperson fails to acquire the land within a period of six months from the receipt of the`
  line `notice, the improvement scheme shall have effect after the expiration of the said six months as if the land`
  line `were not designated as subject to acquisition by the Chairperson or were not required to be kept as an`
  line `open space.`
obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_336:
  sectionId (48823)
  sectionNo (336)
  orderNo 336
  title `Submission of improvement scheme to the Council for approval and to the Central Government for sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_336_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48823&sectionno=336&orderno=336&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_336_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every improvement scheme shall, as soon as may be after it has been`
  line `framed, be submitted by the Chairperson for approval to the Council and the Council may either approve`
  line `the scheme without modifications or with such modifications as it may consider necessary or reject the`
  line `scheme with directions to the Chairperson to have a fresh scheme framed according to such directions.`
  line
  line `(2) No improvement scheme approved by the Council under sub-section (1) shall be valid unless it`
  line `has been sanctioned by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_337:
  sectionId (48732)
  sectionNo (337)
  orderNo 337
  title `Rehousing scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_337_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48732&sectionno=337&orderno=337&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_337_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson while framing an improvement scheme under this`
  line `Chapter for any area may also frame a scheme (hereafter in this Act referred to as the rehousing scheme)`
  line `for the construction, maintenance and management of such area and so many buildings as he may`
  line `consider necessary for providing accommodation for persons who are likely to be displaced by the`
  line `execution of the improvement scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_338:
  sectionId (48826)
  sectionNo (338)
  orderNo 338
  title `Improvement scheme and rehousing scheme to comply with the master plan and zonal development plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_338_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48826&sectionno=338&orderno=338&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_338_content:
  string
  line `No improvement scheme or rehousing scheme framed under this Chapter shall be`
  line `valid unless such scheme is in conformity with the provisions of the master plan for Delhi or a zonal`
  line `development plan for New Delhi or any part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_339:
  sectionId (48734)
  sectionNo (339)
  orderNo 339
  title `Signature, conditions, duration, suspension, revocation, etc., of licences and written permissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_339_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48734&sectionno=339&orderno=339&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_339_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it is provided in this Act or any bye-law made thereunder that a licence or a`
  line `written permission may be granted for any purpose, such licence or written permission shall be signed by`
  line `the Chairperson or by the officer empowered to grant the same under this Act or the bye-laws made`
  line `thereunder or by any officer authorised by the Chairperson or such officer in this behalf and shall specify`
  line `in addition to any other matter required to be specified under any other provision of this Act or any`
  line `provision of any bye-law made thereunder--`
  line
  line `(a) the date of the grant thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) the purpose and the period (if any) for which it is granted;`
  line
  line `(c) restrictions or conditions, if any, subject to which it is granted;`
  line
  line `(d) the name and address of the person to whom it is granted; and`
  line
  line `(e) the fee, if any, paid for the licence or written permission.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise provided in this Act or any bye-law made thereunder, for every such licence`
  line `or written permission a fee may be charged at such rate as may from time to time be fixed by the`
  line `Chairperson with the sanction of the Council and such fee shall be payable by the person to whom the`
  line `licence or written permission is granted.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act or any bye-law made thereunder any licence or written`
  line `permission granted under this Act any bye-law made thereunder may at any time be suspended or revoked`
  line `by the Chairperson or by the officer by whom it was granted, if he is satisfied that it has been secured by`
  line `the grantee through misrepresentation or fraud or if any of its restrictions or conditions have been`
  line `infringed or evaded by the grantee, or if the grantee has been convicted for the contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any bye-law made thereunder relating to any matter for which the licence or`
  line `permission has been granted:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) before making any order of suspension or revocation reasonable opportunity shall be accorded`
  line `to the grantee of the licence or the written permission to show cause why it should not be suspended`
  line `or revoked;`
  line
  line `(b) every such order shall contain a brief statement of the reasons for the suspension or revocation`
  line `of the licence or the written permission.`
  line
  line `(4) When any such licence or written permission is suspended or revoked, or when the period for`
  line `which the same was granted has expired, the grantee shall, for all purposes of this Act or any bye-law`
  line `made thereunder, be deemed to be without a licence or written permission until such time as the order`
  line `suspending or revoking the licence or written permission is rescinded or until the licence or written`
  line `permission is renewed.`
  line
  line `(5) Every grantee of any licence or written permission granted under this Act shall at all reasonable`
  line `times, while such licence or written permission remains in force, if so required by the Chairperson or the`
  line `authority by whom it was granted, produce such licence or written permission.`
obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_340:
  sectionId (48735)
  sectionNo (340)
  orderNo 340
  title `Powers of entry and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_340_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48735&sectionno=340&orderno=340&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_340_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or any officer or other employee authorised`
  line `in this behalf by him or empowered in this behalf by or under any provision of this Act, rules, regulations`
  line `or bye-laws made thereunder, may enter into or upon any land or building with or without assistants and`
  line workmen--
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of ascertaining whether there is or has been on or in connection with the land`
  line `or building any contravention of the provisions of this Act, rules, regulations or any bye-law made`
  line there-under;
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of ascertaining whether or not circumstances exist which would authorise or`
  line `require the Chairperson or any municipal officer or employee authorised or empowered in this behalf`
  line `to take any action or execute any work under this Act, rules, regulations or any bye-law made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(c) for the purpose of taking any action or executing any work authorised or required by this Act,`
  line `rules, regulations or bye-laws made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(d) to make any inquiry, inspection, examination, measurement, valuation or survey authorised or`
  line `required by or under this Act, rules, regulations or bye-laws made thereunder or necessary for the`
  line `proper administration of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) generally for the purpose of efficient discharge of the functions by the Council under this Act,`
  line `rules, regulations or any bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_341:
  sectionId (48736)
  sectionNo (341)
  orderNo 341
  title `Power to enter land adjoining land in relation to any work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_341_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48736&sectionno=341&orderno=341&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_341_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson or any`
  line `person authorised in this behalf by him or empowered in this behalf by or under any provision of this Act,`
  line `rules, regulations or bye-laws made thereunder, may enter on any land within fifty metres of any work`
  line `authorised by or under this Act, rules, regulations or bye-laws made thereunder with or without assistants`
  line `and workmen for the purpose of depositing thereon any soil, gravel, stone or other materials or for`
  line `obtaining access to such work or for any other purposes connected with the execution of the same.`
  line
  line `(2) The person so authorised shall, before entering on any such land, state the purpose thereof, and`
  line `shall, if so required by the owner or occupier thereof, fence off so much of the land as may be required for`
  line `such purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) The person so authorised shall, in exercising any power conferred by this section, do as little`
  line `damage as may be and compensation shall be payable by the Council in accordance with bye-laws made`
  line `in this behalf to the owner or occupier of such land or to both for any such damage, whether permanent or`
  line temporary.
obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_342:
  sectionId (48737)
  sectionNo (342)
  orderNo 342
  title `Breaking into building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_342_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48737&sectionno=342&orderno=342&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_342_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for the Chairperson or any person authorised in`
  line `this behalf by him or empowered in this behalf by or, under any provision of this Act, rules, regulations or`
  line `bye-laws made thereunder to make any entry into any place, and to open or cause to be opened any door,`
  line `gate or other barrier--`
  line
  line `(a) if he considers the opening thereof necessary for the purpose of such entry; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the owner or occupier is absent or being present refuses to open such door, gate or barrier.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making any entry into any such place, or opening or causing to be opened any such door,`
  line `gate or other barrier, the Chairperson or the person authorised or empowered in this behalf, shall call upon two or more respectable inhabitants of the locality in which the place to be entered into is situate, to`
  line `witness the entry or opening and may issue an order in writing to them or any of them so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_343:
  sectionId (48738)
  sectionNo (343)
  orderNo 343
  title `Time of making entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_343_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48738&sectionno=343&orderno=343&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_343_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, rules, regulations or any`
  line `bye-law made thereunder, no entry authorised by or under this Act shall be made except between the`
  line `hours of sunrise and sunset.`
obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_344:
  sectionId (48739)
  sectionNo (344)
  orderNo 344
  title `Consent ordinarily to be obtained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_344_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48739&sectionno=344&orderno=344&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_344_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, rules, regulations`
  line `or any bye-law made thereunder, no land or building shall be entered without the consent of the occupier,`
  line `or if there is no occupier, of the owner thereof and no such entry shall be made without giving the said`
  line `owner or occupier, as the case may be, not less than twenty-four hours written notice of the intention to`
  line `make such entry:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such notice shall be necessary if the place to be inspected is a factory or workshop or`
  line `trade premises or a place used for any of the purposes specified in section 327 or a stable for horses or a`
  line `shed for cattle or a latrine or urinal or a work under construction, or for the purpose of ascertaining`
  line `whether any animal intended for human consumption is slaughtered in that place in contravention of this`
  line `Act or any bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_345:
  sectionId (48740)
  sectionNo (345)
  orderNo 345
  title `Regard to be had to social or religious usages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_345_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48740&sectionno=345&orderno=345&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_345_content:
  string
  line `When any place used as a human dwelling is`
  line `entered under this Act, due regard shall be paid to the social and religious customs and usages of the`
  line `occupants of the place entered, and no apartment in the actual occupancy of a female shall be entered or`
  line `broken open until she has been informed that she is at liberty to withdraw and every reasonable facility`
  line `has been afforded to her withdrawing.`
obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_346:
  sectionId (48741)
  sectionNo (346)
  orderNo 346
  title `Prohibition of obstruction or molestation in execution of work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_346_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48741&sectionno=346&orderno=346&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_346_content:
  string
  line `No person shall obstruct or`
  line `molest any person authorised or empowered by or under this Act or any person with whom the Council`
  line `has lawfully contracted, in the execution of his duty or of anything which he is authorised or empowered`
  line `or required to do by virtue or in consequence of any of the provisions of this Act, rules, regulations or any`
  line `bye-law made thereunder, or in fulfilment of his contract, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_347:
  sectionId (48742)
  sectionNo (347)
  orderNo 347
  title `Public notices how to be made known.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48742&sectionno=347&orderno=347&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_347_content:
  string
  line `Every public notice given under this Act, rules,`
  line `regulations or any bye-law made thereunder shall be in writing under the signature of the Chairperson or`
  line `of any officer authorised in this behalf by him and shall be widely made known in the locality to be`
  line `affected thereby, by affixing copies thereof in conspicuous public places within the said locality or by`
  line `publishing the same by beat of drum or by advertisement in local newspapers or by any two or more of`
  line `these means and by any other means that the Chairperson may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_348:
  sectionId (48743)
  sectionNo (348)
  orderNo 348
  title `Newspapers in which advertisements or notices to be published.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_348_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48743&sectionno=348&orderno=348&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_348_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it is provided`
  line `by this Act or any bye-law made thereunder that notice shall be given by advertisement in local`
  line `newspapers, or that a notification or information shall be published in local newspapers, such notice,`
  line `notification or information shall be inserted, if practicable, in at least three newspapers in such languages`
  line `as the Council may from time to time specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Council publishes a municipal journal, a publication in that journal shall be`
  line `deemed to be a publication in a newspaper of the language in which the said journal may be published.`
obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_349:
  sectionId (48744)
  sectionNo (349)
  orderNo 349
  title `Proof of consent, etc., of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_349_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48744&sectionno=349&orderno=349&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_349_content:
  string
  line `Whenever, under this Act or any rule, regulation or`
  line `bye-law made thereunder, the doing of, or the omission to do, anything or the validity of anything`
  line `depends upon the approval, sanction, consent, concurrence, declaration, opinion or satisfaction of the`
  line `Chairperson or of any municipal officer, a written document signed by the Chairperson or officer`
  line `purporting to convey or set forth such approval, sanction, consent, concurrence, declaration, opinion or`
  line `satisfaction shall be sufficient evidence thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_350:
  sectionId (48745)
  sectionNo (350)
  orderNo 350
  title `Notices, etc., to fix reasonable time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_350_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48745&sectionno=350&orderno=350&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_350_content:
  string
  line `Where any notice, bill, order or requisition issued or`
  line `made under this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder requires anything to be done for`
  line `the doing of which no time is fixed in this Act or the rule, regulation or bye-law, the notice bill, order or`
  line `requisition shall specify a reasonable time for doing the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_351:
  sectionId (48746)
  sectionNo (351)
  orderNo 351
  title `Signature on notices, etc., may be stamped.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_351_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48746&sectionno=351&orderno=351&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_351_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every licence, written permission, notice,`
  line `bill, summons or other document which is required by this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made`
  line `thereunder to bear the signature of the Chairperson or of any officer, shall be deemed to be properly`
  line `signed if it bears a facsimile of the signature of the Chairperson or Officer, as the case may be, stamped`
  line thereupon.
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to apply to a cheque drawn upon the New Delhi`
  line `Municipal Fund under section 46.`
obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_352:
  sectionId (48747)
  sectionNo (352)
  orderNo 352
  title `Notices, etc., by whom to be served or issued.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_352_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48747&sectionno=352&orderno=352&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_352_content:
  string
  line `All notices, bills, summons and other`
  line `documents required by this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder to be served upon, or`
  line `issued to, any person, shall be served or issued by Municipal officers or other Municipal employees or by`
  line `other persons authorised by the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_353:
  sectionId (48748)
  sectionNo (353)
  orderNo 353
  title `Services of notices, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_353_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48748&sectionno=353&orderno=353&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_353_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every notice, bill, summons order, requisition or other document`
  line `required or authorised by this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder to be served or`
  line `issued by or on behalf of the Council, or by the Chairperson or any officer, of any person shall, save as`
  line `otherwise provided in this Act or such rule, regulation or bye-law, be deemed to be duly served--`
  line
  line `(a) where the person to be served is a company, if the document is addressed to the secretary of`
  line `the company at its registered office or at its principal office or place of the business and is either--`
  line
  line `(i) sent by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(ii) delivered at the registered office or at the principal office or place of business of the`
  line company;
  line
  line `(b) where the person to be served is a partnership firm, if the document is addressed to the`
  line `partnership firm at its principal place of business, identifying it by the name or style under which its`
  line `business is carried on, and is either--`
  line
  line `(i) sent by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(ii) delivered at the said place of business;`
  line
  line `(c) where the person to be served is a public body, or a corporation, society or other body, if the`
  line `document is addressed to the secretary, treasurer or other head officer of that body, corporation or`
  line `society as its principal office, and is either--`
  line
  line `(i) sent by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(ii) delivered at that office;`
  line
  line `(d) in any other case, if the document is addressed to the person to be served and--`
  line
  line `(i) is given or tendered to him, or`
  line
  line `(ii) if such person cannot be found, is affixed on some conspicuous part of his last known`
  line `place of residence or business, if within the National Capital Territory of Delhi, or is given or`
  line `tendered to some adult member of his family or is affixed on some conspicuous part of the land or`
  line `building, if any, to which it relates, or`
  line
  line `(iii) is sent by registered post to that person.`
  line
  line `(2) Any document which is required or authorised to be served on the owner or occupier of any land`
  line `or building may be addressed "the owner" or "the occupier", as the case may be, of that land or building`
  line `(naming that land or building) without further name or description, and shall be deemed to be duly`
  line served--
  line
  line `(a) if the document so addressed is sent or delivered in accordance with clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) if the document so addressed or a copy thereof so addressed, is delivered to some person on`
  line `the land or building or, where there is no person on the land or building to whom it can be delivered,`
  line `is affixed to some conspicuous part of the land or building.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a document is served on a partnership firm in accordance with this section, the document`
  line `shall be deemed to be served on each partner.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of enabling any document to be served on the owner of any premises the`
  line `Chairperson may by notice in writing require the occupier of the premises to state the name and address`
  line `of the owner thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the person on whom a document is to be served is a minor, the service upon his guardian or`
  line `any adult member of his family shall be deemed to be service upon the minor.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in sections 351 and 352 and in this section shall apply to any summons issued under this`
  line `Act by a court.`
  line
  line `(7) A servant is not a member of the family within the meaning of this section`
obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_354:
  sectionId (48749)
  sectionNo (354)
  orderNo 354
  title `Service of bills for tax or notice of demand by ordinary post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_354_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48749&sectionno=354&orderno=354&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_354_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sections 352 and 353 a bill for any tax or a notice of demand may be served by sending it by`
  line `ordinary post with a prepaid letter under a certificate of posting addressed to the appropriate person`
  line `specified in section 353 at his last known place of residence or business and in proving the service of`
  line `every bill or notice so sent it shall be sufficient to prove that the letter was properly addressed and posted`
  line `under a certificate of posting.`
obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_355:
  sectionId (48750)
  sectionNo (355)
  orderNo 355
  title `Powers in case of non-compliance with notice, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_355_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48750&sectionno=355&orderno=355&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_355_content:
  string
  line `In the event of non-compliance with the`
  line `terms of any notice, order or requisition issued to any person under this Act or any rule, regulation or`
  line `bye-law made thereunder; requiring such person to execute any work or to do any act it shall be lawful for`
  line `the authority or officer at whose instance the notice, order or requisition has been issued, whether or not`
  line `the person in default is liable to punishment for such default or has been prosecuted or sentenced to any`
  line `punishment therefor, after giving notice in writing to such person, to take such action or such steps as may`
  line `be necessary for the completion of the act or the work required to be done or executed by such person and`
  line `all the expenses incurred on such account shall be payable to the Chairperson on demand and if not paid`
  line `within ten days after such demand, shall be recoverable as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_356:
  sectionId (48751)
  sectionNo (356)
  orderNo 356
  title `Liability of occupier to pay in default of owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_356_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48751&sectionno=356&orderno=356&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_356_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any notice, order or requisition has`
  line `been issued to any person in respect of property of which he is the owner, the authority or the officer at`
  line `whose instance such notice, order or requisition has been issued, may require the occupier of such`
  line `property or of any part thereof to pay to him, instead of to the owner, any rent payable by him in respect`
  line `of such property, as it falls due upto the amount recoverable from the owner under section 355:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the occupier refuses to disclose the correct amount of the rent payable by him or the`
  line `name or address of the person to whom it is payable, the officer may recover from the occupier the whole`
  line `amount recoverable under section 355 as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount recovered from an occupier instead of from an owner under sub-section (1), shall, in`
  line `the absence of any contract between the owner and the occupier to the contrary, be deemed to have been`
  line `paid to the owner.`
obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_357:
  sectionId (48752)
  sectionNo (357)
  orderNo 357
  title `Execution of work by occupier in default of owner and deduction of expenses from rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_357_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48752&sectionno=357&orderno=357&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_357_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the owner of any land or building fails to execute any work which he is required to execute`
  line `under this Act, or any bye-law made thereunder, the occupier, if any, of such land or building may, with`
  line `the approval of the Chairperson, execute the said work and he shall, subject to any contract, between the`
  line `owner and occupier to the contrary, be entitled to recover from the owner the reasonable expenses`
  line `incurred by him in the execution of the work and may deduct the amount thereof from the rent payable by`
  line `him to the owner.`
obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_358:
  sectionId (48753)
  sectionNo (358)
  orderNo 358
  title `Relief to agents and trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_358_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48753&sectionno=358&orderno=358&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_358_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person, by reason of his receiving rent of`
  line `immovable property as a receiver, agent or trustee, or of his being as a receiver, agent or trustee the`
  line
  line `person who would receive the rent if the property were let to a tenant, would under this Act, or any`
  line `bye-law made thereunder, be bound to discharge any obligation imposed on the owner of the property for`
  line `the discharge of which money is required, he shall not be bound to discharge the obligation unless he has,`
  line `or but for his own improper act or default might have had funds in his hands belonging to the owner`
  line `sufficient for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The burden of proving any fact entitling a receiver, agent or trustee to relief under sub-section (1)`
  line `shall lie upon him.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any receiver, agent or trustee has claimed and established his right to relief under this`
  line `section, the Chairperson may, by notice in writing require him, to apply to the discharge of his obligation`
  line `as aforesaid the first moneys which may come to his hands on behalf, or for the use, of the owner and on`
  line `failure to comply with the notice, he shall be deemed to be personally liable to discharge the obligation.`
obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_359:
  sectionId (48754)
  sectionNo (359)
  orderNo 359
  title `General power to compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_359_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48754&sectionno=359&orderno=359&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_359_content:
  string
  line `In any case not otherwise provided for in this Act or in any`
  line `bye-law made thereunder, the Chairperson with the previous approval of the Council, may pay`
  line `compensation to any person who sustains damage by reason of the exercise of any of the powers vested`
  line `by this Act or any bye-law in the Chairperson or in any municipal officer or other municipal employee.`
obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_360:
  sectionId (48755)
  sectionNo (360)
  orderNo 360
  title `Compensation to be paid by offenders for damage caused by them.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_360_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48755&sectionno=360&orderno=360&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_360_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who`
  line `has been convicted of an offence against this Act or any bye-law made thereunder shall, notwithstanding`
  line `any punishment to which he may have been sentenced for the said offence, be liable to pay such`
  line `compensation for any damage to the property of the Council resulting from the said offence as the`
  line `Chairperson may consider reasonable.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of a dispute regarding the amount of compensation payable under sub-section (1)`
  line `such amount shall, on application made to him, be determined by the magistrate before whom the said`
  line `person was convicted of the said offence; and on non-payment of the amount of compensation so`
  line `determined the same shall be recovered under a warrant issued by the said magistrate as if it were a fine`
  line `imposed by him on the person liable therefor`
obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_361:
  sectionId (48756)
  sectionNo (361)
  orderNo 361
  title `Reference to the court of the district judge in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_361_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48756&sectionno=361&orderno=361&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_361_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, when the Chairperson`
  line `demands payment of any expenses referred to in section 355, his right to demand the same or the amount`
  line `of the demand is disputed within ten days after such demand, the Chairperson shall refer the case for`
  line determination--
  line
  line `(a) to the Appellate Tribunal, if such demand relates to the expenses incurred in taking necessary`
  line `action or steps for the completion of any act or work required to be done or executed in the event of`
  line `non-compliance with any notice, order or requisition under sections 221, 229, 247, 248 and 249;`
  line
  line `(b) to the court of the district judge of Delhi, in any other case.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall, pending the decision on any such reference, defer further proceedings for`
  line `the recovery of the sum claimed by him, and shall, after the decision, proceed to recover only such`
  line `amount, if any, as is thereby declared to be due in the manner referred to in section 355.`
obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_362:
  sectionId (48757)
  sectionNo (362)
  orderNo 362
  title `Application to the court of the district judge in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_362_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48757&sectionno=362&orderno=362&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_362_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in any case not`
  line `provided for by section 361, the Council or the Chairperson or any officer or other employee is required`
  line `by this Act or by any bye-law made thereunder to pay any expenses or any compensation, the amount to`
  line `be so paid and if necessary, the apportionment of the same, shall, in case of dispute, be determined by the`
  line `court of the district judge of Delhi on an application having been made to it for this purpose at any time`
  line `within one year from the date when such expenses or compensation first became claimable.`
  line
  line `(2) If the amount of any expenses or compensation ascertained in accordance with sub-section (1) is`
  line `not paid by the person liable therefor on demand, it shall be recoverable as if the same were due under a`
  line `decree passed by the court of the district judge in an original suit tried by it.`
  line
  line `(3) Instead of proceeding in the manner aforesaid for the recovery of any expenses or compensation`
  line `of which the amount due has been ascertained as hereinbefore provided, or after such proceedings have`
  line `been taken unsuccessfully or with only partial success, the sum due or the balance of the sum due, as the`
  line `case may be, may be recovered by a suit brought against the person liable for same in any court of`
  line `competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_363:
  sectionId (48758)
  sectionNo (363)
  orderNo 363
  title `Mode of recovery of certain dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_363_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48758&sectionno=363&orderno=363&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_363_content:
  string
  line `In any case not expressly provided for in this Act or any`
  line `bye-law made thereunder any sum due to the Council on account of any charge, costs, expenses, fees,`
  line `rates or rent or on any other account under this Act or any such bye-law may be recoverable from any`
  line `person from whom such sum is due as an arrear of tax under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no proceedings for the recovery of any sum under this section shall be commenced after`
  line `the expiry of three years from the date on which such sum becomes due.`
obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_364:
  sectionId (48759)
  sectionNo (364)
  orderNo 364
  title `Right of owner to apply to the court of the district judge in case of obstruction by occupier.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_364_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48759&sectionno=364&orderno=364&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_364_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of any land or building may, if he is prevented by the occupier thereof from`
  line `complying with--`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of section 221, section 229, section 247, section 248, section 249, or`
  line `section 252, or any bye-law made thereunder or with any notice or order issued under any such`
  line `provision apply to the Appellate Tribunal; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other provision or any bye-law made thereunder or with any notice, order or requisition`
  line `issued under such provision, apply to the court of the district judge of Delhi and where such`
  line `application is made within any time that may be fixed for the compliance with such provision or`
  line `notice, order or requisition the owner shall not be liable for his failure to comply with the provision,`
  line `or notice, order or requisition within the time so fixed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal or the court, as the case may be, on receipt of such application, may make`
  line `a written order requiring the occupier of the land or building to afford all reasonable facilities to the`
  line `owner for complying with the said provision or notice, order or requisition and may also, if it thinks fit`
  line `direct that the costs of such application and order be paid by the occupier.`
  line
  line `(3) After eight days from the date of the order referred to in sub-section (2), the occupier shall afford`
  line `all such reasonable facilities to the owner for the purpose aforesaid as may be specified in the order; and`
  line `in the event of his continued refusal to do so, the owner shall be discharged during the continuance of`
  line `such refusal, from any liability which may have been otherwise incurred by reason of his failure to`
  line `comply with the said provision or notice, order or requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_365:
  sectionId (48760)
  sectionNo (365)
  orderNo 365
  title `General powers and procedure of the court of the district judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_365_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48760&sectionno=365&orderno=365&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_365_content:
  string
  line `The procedure provided`
  line `in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in regard to suits shall be followed, as far as it can be`
  line `made applicable, in the disposal of applications, appeals or references that may be made to the court of`
  line `the district judge of Delhi under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_366:
  sectionId (48761)
  sectionNo (366)
  orderNo 366
  title `Fees in proceedings before the court of the district judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_366_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48761&sectionno=366&orderno=366&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_366_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, prescribe what fee shall be paid--`
  line
  line `(a) on any application, appeal or reference under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder to the`
  line `court of the district judge of Delhi; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the issue, in connection with any inquiry or proceedings before that court under this Act or`
  line `such bye-law, of any summons or other process:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fee, if any, prescribed under clause (a) shall not, in cases in which the value of the`
  line `claim or subject matter is capable of being estimated in money, exceed the fees leviable for the time being`
  line `under the provisions of the Court-fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870), in cases in which the amount of the claim or`
  line `subject matter is of a like amount.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government may, by like notification, determine the person by whom the fee, if any,`
  line `prescribed under clause (a) of sub-section (1), shall be payable.`
  line
  line `(3) No application, appeal or reference shall be received by the court of the district judge until the fee,`
  line `if any, prescribed therefor under clause (a) of sub-section (1) has been paid:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, in any case in which it thinks fit so to do,--`
  line
  line `(i) receive an application, appeal or reference made by or on behalf of a poor person, and`
  line
  line `(ii) issue process on behalf of any such person,`
  line
  line `without payment or on part payment of the fees prescribed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_367:
  sectionId (48762)
  sectionNo (367)
  orderNo 367
  title `Repayment of half fees on settlement before hearing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_367_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_367_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48762&sectionno=367&orderno=367&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_367_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any application, appeal or`
  line `reference made under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder to the court of the district judge is settled`
  line `by agreement between the parties before the hearing, half the amount of all fees paid up to that time shall`
  line `be repaid by the court to the parties by whom the same have respectively been paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_367_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_368:
  sectionId (48763)
  sectionNo (368)
  orderNo 368
  title `Power of the court of the district judge to delegate certain powers and to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_368_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48763&sectionno=368&orderno=368&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_368_content:
  string
  line The
  line `court of the district judge of Delhi may--`
  line
  line `(a) delegate, either generally or specially, to the court of an additional district judge, power to`
  line `receive applications, appeals and references under this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made`
  line `thereunder, and to hear and determine such applications, appeals and references;`
  line
  line `(b) with the approval of the Government, make rules not inconsistent with this Act or any rule,`
  line `regulation or bye-law made thereunder, providing for any matter connected with the exercise of the`
  line `jurisdiction conferred upon the court by this Act which is not herein specifically provided for.`
obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_369:
  sectionId (48764)
  sectionNo (369)
  orderNo 369
  title `Punishment for certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_369_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48764&sectionno=369&orderno=369&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_369_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) contravenes any provision of any of the sections, sub-sections, clauses, provisos or other`
  line `provisions of this Act mentioned in the first column of the Table in the Tenth Schedule; or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to comply with any order or direction lawfully given to him or any requisition lawfully`
  line `made upon him under any of the said sections, sub-sections, clauses, provisos or other provisions,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable--`
  line
  line `(i) with fine which may extend to the amount or with imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to the period, specified in that behalf in third column of the said Table or with both; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a continuing contravention or failure, with an additional fine which may extend`
  line `to the amount specified in the fourth column of that Table for every day during which such`
  line `contravention or failure continues after conviction for the first such contravention or failure.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), whoever contravenes the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 221, or sub-section (1) of section 224, or sub-section (1) of section 225 or`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 229 or section 244, in relation to any street which is a public street, shall be`
  line `punishable with simple imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend to`
  line `five thousand rupees or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Any member, referred to in clauses (b) and (d) of sub-section (1) of section 4, who knowingly`
  line `acquires, directly or indirectly, any share or interest in any contract made with, or any work done for the`
  line `Council, shall be deemed to have committed offence made punishable under section 168 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_370:
  sectionId (48765)
  sectionNo (370)
  orderNo 370
  title `General penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_370_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_370_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48765&sectionno=370&orderno=370&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_370_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, in any case in which a penalty is not expressly provided by this`
  line `Act, fails to comply with any notice, order or requisition issued under any provision thereof, or otherwise`
  line `contravenes any of the provisions of this Act, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one`
  line `hundred rupees, and in the case of a continuing failure or contravention, with an additional fine which`
  line `may extend to twenty rupees for every day after the first during which he has persisted in the failure or`
  line contravention.
obj_root_law_sections_370_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_371:
  sectionId (48766)
  sectionNo (371)
  orderNo 371
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_371_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48766&sectionno=371&orderno=371&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_371_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence has been committed without his knowledge`
  line `or that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm`
obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_372:
  sectionId (48767)
  sectionNo (372)
  orderNo 372
  title `Certain offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_372_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_372_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48767&sectionno=372&orderno=372&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_372_content:
  string
  line `The Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall`
  line `apply to,--`
  line
  line `(a) an offence under sub-section (5) of section 217 or section 237 or sub-section (1) of section`
  line `238 or sub-section (1) of section 239 or section 247 or section 248 or section 249 or section 252;`
  line
  line `(b) an offence under sub-section (1) of section 221 or sub-section (1) of section 224 or`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 225 or sub-section (1) of section 229 or section 244 in relation to any street`
  line `which is a public street.`
  line
  line `as if it were a cognizable offence--`
  line
  line `(i) for the purposes of investigation of such offence; and`
  line
  line `(ii) for the purposes of all matters other than--`
  line
  line `(1) matters referred to in section 42 of that Code, and`
  line
  line `(2) arrest of a person, except on the complaint of, or upon information received from, such`
  line `officer of the Council, not being below the rank of a Secretary as may be appointed by the`
  line `Chairperson:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offence of the contravention of any condition subject to which sanction was`
  line `accorded for the erection of any building or the execution of any work shall be cognizable, if such`
  line `contravention relates to any deviation from any plan of such erection or execution sanctioned by the`
  line `Chairperson which is compoundable on payment of any amount under the bye-laws relating to buildings`
  line `made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_372_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_373:
  sectionId (48768)
  sectionNo (373)
  orderNo 373
  title Prosecutions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_373_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48768&sectionno=373&orderno=373&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_373_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, no court shall proceed to the trial of any`
  line offence,--
  line
  line `(a) under sub-section (5) of section 217 or section 237 or sub-section (1) of section 238 or`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 239 or section 247 or section 248 or section 249 or section 252 except on`
  line `the complaint of or upon information received from, such officer of the Council, not being below the`
  line `rank of a Secretary as may be appointed by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(b) under sub-section (1) of section 221 or sub-section (1) of section 224 or sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 225 or sub-section (1) of section 229 or section 244, if any such offence was committed in`
  line `relation to any street which is a public street, except on the complaint of, or upon information`
  line `received from, such officer of the Council, not being below the rank of a Secretary as may be`
  line `appointed by the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) other than those specified in clauses (a) and (b) except on the complaint of, or upon`
  line `information received from the Chairperson or a person authorised by him by a general or special`
  line `order in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_374:
  sectionId (48769)
  sectionNo (374)
  orderNo 374
  title `Composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_374_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_374_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48769&sectionno=374&orderno=374&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_374_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson or any person authorised by him by general or`
  line `special order in this behalf may, either before or after the institution of the proceedings, compound any`
  line `offence made punishable by or under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offence shall be compoundable which is committed by failure to comply with a`
  line `notice, order or requisition issued by or on behalf of the Council or of the Chairperson unless and until the`
  line `same has been complied with so far as the compliance is possible.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence has been compounded, the offender, if in custody shall be discharged, and no`
  line `further proceedings shall be taken against him in respect to the offence so compounded.`
obj_root_law_sections_374_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_375:
  sectionId (48770)
  sectionNo (375)
  orderNo 375
  title `Municipal magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_375_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48770&sectionno=375&orderno=375&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_375_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may appoint one or more metropolitan`
  line `magistrates for the trial of offences against this Act and against any rule, regulation or bye-law made`
  line `thereunder and may prescribe the time and place at which such magistrate or magistrates shall sit for the`
  line `despatch of business.`
  line
  line `(2) Such magistrates shall be called municipal magistrates and shall besides the trial of offences as`
  line `aforesaid, exercise all other powers and discharge all other functions of a magistrate as provided in this`
  line `Act or any rule, regulation of bye-law made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) Such magistrates and the members of their staff shall be paid such salary, pension, leave and other`
  line `allowances as may, from to time, be fixed by the Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall, out of the New Delhi Municipal Fund, pay to the Government the amounts of`
  line `the salary, pension, leave and other allowances as fixed under sub-section (3) together with all other`
  line `incidental charges in connection with the establishments of the said magistrates.`
  line
  line `(5) Each such magistrate shall have jurisdiction over the whole of New Delhi.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purpose of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all municipal magistrates`
  line `appointed under this Act shall be deemed to be magistrates appointed under section 16 of the said Code.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to preclude any magistrate appointed hereunder from`
  line `trying any offence under any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_376:
  sectionId (48771)
  sectionNo (376)
  orderNo 376
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_376_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48771&sectionno=376&orderno=376&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_376_content:
  string
  line `All offences against this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made`
  line `thereunder, whether committed within or without the limits of New Delhi, shall be cognizable by a`
  line `municipal magistrate and such magistrate shall not be deemed to be incapable of taking cognizance of any`
  line `such offence or of any offence under any enactment which is repealed by, or which ceases to have effect`
  line `under this Act by reason only of his being liable to pay any municipal tax or rate or benefited out of the`
  line `New Delhi Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_377:
  sectionId (48772)
  sectionNo (377)
  orderNo 377
  title `Limitation of time for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_377_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48772&sectionno=377&orderno=377&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_377_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be liable to punishment for any offence`
  line `against this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder, unless complaint of such offence is`
  line `made before a municipal magistrate within six months next after--`
  line
  line `(a) the date of the commission of the offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) the date on which the commission or existence of such offence was first brought to the notice`
  line `of the complainant.`
obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_378:
  sectionId (48773)
  sectionNo (378)
  orderNo 378
  title `Power of magistrate to hear cases in absence of accused when summoned to appear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48773&sectionno=378&orderno=378&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_378_content:
  string
  line If
  line `any person summoned to appear before a magistrate to answer a charge of an offence against this Act or`
  line `any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder fails to appear at the time and place mentioned in the`
  line `summons, or on any date to which the hearing of the case is adjourned, the magistrate may hear and`
  line `determine the case in his absence, if--`
  line
  line `(a) service of the summons is proved to his satisfaction, and`
  line
  line `(b) no sufficient cause is shown, for the non-appearance of such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_379:
  sectionId (48774)
  sectionNo (379)
  orderNo 379
  title `Complaints concerning nuisances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_379_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48774&sectionno=379&orderno=379&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_379_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson or any municipal officer or other`
  line `municipal employee authorised by him in this behalf or any person who resides or owns property in New`
  line `Delhi, may complain to a municipal magistrate of the existence of any nuisance.`
obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_380:
  sectionId (48775)
  sectionNo (380)
  orderNo 380
  title `Procedure to be followed by magistrate regarding complaints concerning nuisances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_380_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48775&sectionno=380&orderno=380&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_380_content:
  string
  line `(1) Upon the receipt of any complaint under section 379, the magistrate, after making such inquiry as he`
  line `thinks necessary, may by written order direct the person responsible for the nuisance or the owner of the`
  line `land or building on which the nuisance has taken place, to take such measures as to such magistrate may`
  line `seem practicable and reasonable, and within such period as may be specified in the order for abating,`
  line `preventing, removing or remedying such nuisance and may direct the Chairperson to put into force any of`
  line `the provisions of this Act or any bye-law made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The magistrate may further direct the person found responsible for the nuisance to pay to the`
  line `complainant such reasonable costs of and relating to the said complaint as he shall determine, inclusive of`
  line `compensation for the complainants loss of time in prosecuting such complaint.`
  line
  line `(3) Where in the opinion of the magistrate immediate action to prevent the nuisance is necessary he`
  line `may dispense with the inquiry as required by sub-section (1) and make such order as he considers`
  line `necessary forthwith.`
  line
  line `(4) If the person directed to take action by an order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) fails to do`
  line `so within the period specified in the order, the Chairperson may on the expiry of the said period proceed`
  line `to take action as directed in the order or may take such other measures to abate, prevent, remove or`
  line `remedy the nuisance as he considers necessary, and all expenses incurred in that connection shall be`
  line `recoverable from the person against whom the magistrate has made the order as an arrear of tax under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_381:
  sectionId (48776)
  sectionNo (381)
  orderNo 381
  title `Arrest of offenders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_381_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48776&sectionno=381&orderno=381&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_381_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any police officer, may arrest any person who commits in his view`
  line `any offence against this Act or against any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder if--`
  line
  line `(a) the name and address of such person be unknown to him, and`
  line
  line `(b) such person on demand declines to give his name and address or gives a name and address`
  line `which such officer has reason to believe to be false.`
  line
  line `(2) No person so arrested shall be detained in custody after his true name and address are ascertained`
  line `or, without the order of the nearest magistrate for a period longer than twenty-four hours from the time of`
  line `arrest exclusive of the time necessary for the journey from the place of arrest to the court of such`
  line magistrate.
obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_382:
  sectionId (48777)
  sectionNo (382)
  orderNo 382
  title `Duties of police officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_382_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48777&sectionno=382&orderno=382&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_382_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of all police officers, to give immediate`
  line `information to the Chairperson of the commission of, or the attempt to commit any offence against this`
  line `Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder and to assist all municipal officers and other`
  line `municipal employees in the exercise of their lawful authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_383:
  sectionId (48778)
  sectionNo (383)
  orderNo 383
  title `Power to institute, etc., legal proceedings and obtain legal advice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_383_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48778&sectionno=383&orderno=383&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_383_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson`
  line may--
  line
  line `(a) take, or withdraw from, proceedings against any person who is charged with--`
  line
  line `(i) any offence against this Act or any rules, regulation or bye-law made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any offence which affects or is likely to affect any property or interest of the Council or`
  line `the due administration of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) committing any nuisance whatsoever;`
  line
  line `(b) contest or compromise any appeal against rateable value or assessment of any tax or rate;`
  line
  line `(c) take, or withdraw from, compromise proceedings under sections 360, 361 and 362 for`
  line `recovery of expenses or compensation claimed to be due to the Council;`
  line
  line `(d) withdraw or compromise any claim for a sum not exceeding one thousand rupees against any`
  line person;
  line
  line `(e) defend any suit or other legal proceeding brought against the Council or against the`
  line `Chairperson or a municipal officer or municipal employee in respect of anything done or omitted to`
  line `be done by any one of them in his official capacity;`
  line
  line `(f) with the approval of the Council admit or compromise any claim, suit or other legal`
  line `proceeding brought against the Council or against the Chairperson or any officer or other employee in`
  line `respect of anything done or omitted to be done as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(g) withdraw or compromise any claim against any person in respect of a penalty payable under a`
  line `contract entered into with such person by the Chairperson on behalf of the Council;`
  line
  line `(h) institute and prosecute any suit or other legal proceeding, or with the approval of the Council`
  line `withdraw from or compromise any suit or any claim for any sum not exceeding five hundred rupees`
  line `which has been instituted or made in the name of the Council or the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(i) obtain such legal advice and assistance as he from time to time thinks necessary or expedient`
  line `to obtain or as he may be required by the Council to obtain for any of the purposes mentioned in the`
  line `foregoing clauses or for securing lawful exercise or discharge of any power or duty vesting in or`
  line `imposed upon any municipal officer or other municipal employee.`
obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_384:
  sectionId (48779)
  sectionNo (384)
  orderNo 384
  title `Protection of action of the Council, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_384_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_384_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48779&sectionno=384&orderno=384&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_384_content:
  string
  line `No suit or prosecution shall be entertained in any`
  line `court against the Council or against any municipal officer or other municipal employee or against any`
  line `person acting under the order or direction of the Chairperson or any municipal officer or other municipal`
  line `employee, for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done, under this Act or any rule,`
  line `regulation or bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_384_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_385:
  sectionId (48780)
  sectionNo (385)
  orderNo 385
  title `Notice to be given of suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_385_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48780&sectionno=385&orderno=385&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_385_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit shall be instituted against the Council or against the`
  line `Chairperson or against any municipal officer or other municipal employee or against any person acting`
  line `under the order or direction of the Chairperson or any municipal officer or other municipal employee, in`
  line `respect of any act done, or purporting to have been done, in pursuance of this Act or any rule, regulation`
  line `or bye-law made thereunder until the expiration of two months after notice in writing has been delivered`
  line `at the municipal office and, in the case of such officer, employee or person, unless notice in writing has`
  line `also been delivered to him at his office or place of residence, and unless such notice states explicitly the`
  line `cause of action, the nature of the relief sought, the amount of compensation claimed, and the name and`
  line `place of residence of the intending plaintiff, and unless the plaint contains a statement that such notice has`
  line `been so left or delivered.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit, such as is described in sub-section (1), shall unless it is a suit for the recovery of`
  line `immovable property or for a declaration of title thereto, be instituted after the expiry of six months from`
  line `the date on which the cause of action arises.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to apply to a suit in which the only relief claimed is an`
  line `injunction of which the object would be defeated by the giving of the notice or the postponement of the`
  line `institution of the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_386:
  sectionId (48781)
  sectionNo (386)
  orderNo 386
  title `Supplemental provisions respecting rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_386_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48781&sectionno=386&orderno=386&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_386_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any rule which the Central Government is`
  line `empowered to make under this Act may provide that any contravention thereof shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act and bye-laws made by the Central Government under section 260`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for`
  line `a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions,`
  line `and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or bye-laws or both Houses agree`
  line `that the rule or bye-laws, should not be made, the rule or bye-laws, shall thereafter have effect only in`
  line `such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or`
  line bye-laws.
obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_387:
  sectionId (48782)
  sectionNo (387)
  orderNo 387
  title `Supplemental provisions respecting regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_387_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48782&sectionno=387&orderno=387&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_387_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any regulation which may be made by`
  line `the Council under this Act may be made by the Central Government within one year of the establishment`
  line `of the Council; and any regulation so made may be altered or rescinded by the Council in the exercise of`
  line `its powers under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No regulation made by the Council under this Act shall have effect until it has been approved by`
  line `the Central Government and published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_388:
  sectionId (48783)
  sectionNo (388)
  orderNo 388
  title `Power to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_388_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48783&sectionno=388&orderno=388&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_388_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Council may, in`
  line `addition to any bye-laws which it is empowered to make by any other provision of this Act, make`
  line `bye-laws to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `A. Bye-laws relating to taxation`
  line
  line `(1) the maintenance of tax books and registers by the Chairperson and the particulars which such`
  line `books and registers should contain;`
  line
  line `(2) the inspection of and the obtaining of copies and extracts from such books and registers and fees,`
  line `if any, to be charged for the same;`
  line
  line `(3) the publication of rates of taxes as determined by the Council from time to time;`
  line
  line `(4) the requisition by the Chairperson of information and returns from persons liable to pay taxes;`
  line
  line `(5) the notice to be given to the Chairperson by any person who becomes the owner or possessor of a`
  line `vehicle or animal in respect of which any tax is payable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(6) the wearing of badge by the driver of any such vehicle and the display of number plate on such`
  line vehicle;
  line
  line `(7) the submission of returns by persons liable to pay any tax under this Act;`
  line
  line `(8) the collection by the registrar or sub-registrar of Delhi appointed under the Registration Act, 1908`
  line `(16 of 1908) of the additional stamp duty payable to the Council under this Act, the periodical payment of`
  line `such duty to the Council and the maintenance by such registrar or sub-registrar of separate accounts in`
  line `relation thereto;`
  line
  line `(9) any other matter relating to the levy, assessment, collection, refund or remission of taxes under`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `B. Bye-laws relating to water supply, drainage and sewage collection`
  line
  line `(1) the power of the Chairperson to close water works for the supply of water, whether for domestic`
  line `purposes or not, or for gratuitous use and to prohibit the sale and use of water for purpose of business;`
  line
  line `(2) the connection of supply pipes for conveying to any premises a supply of water from a municipal`
  line `water works;`
  line
  line `(3) the making and renewing connections with municipal water works;`
  line
  line `(4) the power of the Chairperson to take charge of private connections;`
  line
  line `(5) the power of the Chairperson to alter the position of connections;`
  line
  line `(6) the equitable distribution of water supplied to occupiers;`
  line
  line `(7) the size, material, quality, description and position of the pipes and fittings to be used for the`
  line `purpose of any connection with or any communication from any municipal water works and the stamping`
  line `of pipes and fittings and fees for such stamping;`
  line
  line `(8) the size, material, quality and description of pipes, cisterns and fittings which are found on an`
  line `examination under the provisions of this Act to be so defective that they cannot be effectively repaired;`
  line
  line `(9) the provision and maintenance of meters when water is supplied by measurement;`
  line
  line `(10) the prohibition of fraudulent and unauthorised use of water and the prohibition of fraud in`
  line `connection with meters;`
  line
  line `(11) the maintenance of pipes; cisterns and other water works;`
  line
  line `(12) the regulation or prohibition of the discharge or deposit of offensive or obstructive matter,`
  line `polluted water or other polluted and obnoxious matter into sewers;`
  line
  line `(13) the regulation in any manner not specifically provided for in this Act of the construction,`
  line `alteration, maintenance, preservation, cleaning and repairs of drains, ventilation shafts, pipes, latrines,`
  line `urinals, cesspools and other drainage works;`
  line
  line `(14) the cleansing of drains;`
  line
  line `(15) the prohibition of erection of buildings over drains without the permission of the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(16) the connection of private drains with municipal drains;`
  line
  line `(17) the location and construction of cesspools;`
  line
  line `(18) the covering and ventilation of cesspools;`
  line
  line `(19) the period or periods of the day during which trade effluent may be discharged from any trade`
  line `premises into municipal drains;`
  line
  line `(20) the exclusion from trade effluent of all condensing water;`
  line
  line `(21) the elimination from trade effluent, before it enters a municipal drain, of any constituent which in`
  line `the opinion of the Council would either alone or in combination with any matter with which it is likely to`
  line `come into contact while passing through municipal drains injure or obstruct those drains or make`
  line `specially difficult or expensive the treatment or disposal of the sewage from those drains;`
  line
  line `(22) the maximum quantity of trade effluent which may without any consent or permission, be`
  line `discharged from any trade premises into municipal drains on any one day and the highest rate at which`
  line `trade effluent may, without such consent or permission, be discharged from any trade premises into`
  line `municipal drains;`
  line
  line `(23) the regulation of the temperature of trade effluent at the time of its discharge into municipal`
  line `drains and the securing of the neutrality of trade effluent (that is to say, that it is neither acid nor alkaline)`
  line `at the time of such discharge;`
  line
  line `(24) the charges to be paid to the Council by occupiers of trade premises for the reception of trade`
  line `effluent into municipal drains and disposal thereof;`
  line
  line `(25) the provision and maintenance of such an inspection chamber or mainhole as will enable a`
  line `person readily to take at any time samples of what is passing into municipal drains from trade premises;`
  line
  line `(26) the provision and maintenance of such meters as may be required to measure the volume of any`
  line `trade effluent being discharged from any trade premises into municipal drains and the testing of such`
  line meters.
  line
  line `C. Bye-laws relating to electric supply`
  line
  line `(1) all matters relating to the conduct and management in respect of electricity supply;`
  line
  line `(2) the provisions for electric sub-stations in New Delhi.`
  line
  line `D. Bye-laws relating to streets`
  line
  line `(1) the closure of streets when any work is in progress and alternative passage during the progress`
  line `of such work;`
  line
  line `(2) the erections of a temporary nature during festivals;`
  line
  line `(3) the setting up of hoards on buildings adjacent to streets during their construction or repair;`
  line
  line `(4) the precautions to be taken when permission is granted to any private individual for opening`
  line `or breaking up any public street and the fees to be paid for the restoration of a street in its original`
  line condition;
  line
  line `(5) the permission, regulation or prohibition or use or occupation of any street or place by it,`
  line `itinerant vendors or hawkers or by any person for the sale of articles or the exercise of any calling or`
  line `the setting up of any booth or stall and the fees chargeable for such occupation;`
  line
  line `(6) any other matter in connection with the construction, repair, maintenance, naming, numbering`
  line `and lighting of streets for which provision is necessary or should be made.`
  line
  line `E. Bye-laws relating to sanitation and public health`
  line
  line `(1) the position of latrines and urinals;`
  line
  line `(2) the provision of air spaces between latrines and buildings or places used for various purposes;`
  line
  line `(3) the white-washing of buildings;`
  line
  line `(4) the regulation or prohibition of the stabling or herding of animals or any class of animals so as`
  line `to prevent danger to public health;`
  line
  line `(5) the seizure of ownerless animals straying within the limits of New Delhi and the regulation`
  line `and control of pounds;`
  line
  line `(6) the fixing and regulation of the use of public bathing and washing places;`
  line
  line `(7) the prevention of the spread of dangerous disease;`
  line
  line `(8) the segregation in or the removal or exclusion from any part of New Delhi or the destruction`
  line `of animals suffering or reasonably suspected to be suffering from any infectious or contagious`
  line disease;
  line
  line `(9) the supervision, regulation, conservation and protection from injury, contamination or`
  line `trespass, of sources and means of public water supply and of appliances for the distribution of water;`
  line
  line `(10) the enforcement of compulsory vaccination and inoculation;`
  line
  line `(11) the proper disposal of corpses, the regulation and management of burning and burial places`
  line `and other places for the disposal of corpses and the fees chargeable for the use of such places where`
  line `the same are provided or maintained at the expense of the New Delhi Municipal Fund;`
  line
  line `(12) the provision of living accommodation for sweepers in buildings newly erected requiring ten`
  line `or more latrines.`
  line
  line `F. Bye-laws relating to vital statistics`
  line
  line `(1) the prescribing of qualifications of persons to be appointed as chief registrar, additional chief`
  line `registrar and registrar under Chapter XVI;`
  line
  line `(2) the registration of births and deaths and marriages and taking of a census.`
  line
  line `G. Bye-laws relating to public safety and suppression of nuisances`
  line
  line `The regulation or prohibition for the purpose of sanitation or the prevention of disease or the`
  line `promotion of public safety or convenience, of any act which occasions or is likely to occasion a`
  line `nuisance and for the regulation or prohibition of which no provision is made elsewhere by this Act.`
  line
  line `H. Bye-laws relating to markets, slaughter houses, trades and occupations`
  line
  line `(1) the days on, and hours during which any market or slaughter house may be kept open for use;`
  line
  line `(2) the regulation of the design, ventilation and drainage of markets and slaughter house the`
  line `materials to be used in the construction thereof;`
  line
  line `(3) the keeping of markets and the slaughter house and the lands and buildings appertaining`
  line `thereto in a clean and sanitary condition, the removal of filth, rubbish and other polluted and`
  line `obnoxious matter therefrom and the supply therein of pure water and of a sufficient number of`
  line `latrines and urinals for the use of persons using or frequenting the same;`
  line
  line `(4) the provision of passages of sufficient width between the stalls in market buildings and market`
  line `places for the convenient use of the public and the prevention of encroachment of such passages;`
  line
  line `(5) the setting apart of separate areas for different classes of article in market buildings and`
  line `market places;`
  line
  line `(6) the proper custody and care of animals for the keeping of which licences are granted under`
  line `section 327;`
  line
  line `(7) the regulation of the import of animals and flesh within New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(8) the rendering necessary of licences for the use of premises within New Delhi as stables or`
  line `cow-houses or as an accommodation for sheep, goat or buffalo and the fees payable, for such`
  line `licences and the conditions subject to which such licences may be granted, refused, suspended or`
  line revoked;
  line
  line `(9) the regulation of sarais, hotels, hostels, guest houses, dak bungalows, lodging houses,`
  line `boarding houses, buildings, let-in-tenements, residential clubs, restaurants, eating houses, cafes,`
  line `refreshment rooms and places of public recreation, entertainment or resort;`
  line
  line `(10) the control and supervision of places where dangerous or offensive trades are carried on so`
  line `as to secure cleanliness therein or to minimise injurious, offensive or dangerous effects arising or`
  line `likely to arise therefrom;`
  line
  line `(11) the regulation of the posting of bills and advertisements and of the position, size, shade or`
  line `style of the name boards, sign boards, hoarding and sign-posts;`
  line
  line `(12) the fixation of a method for the sale of articles whether by measure, weight, piece or any`
  line `other method;`
  line
  line `(13) the procedure regarding the grant of permit to establish a factory, workshop or trade`
  line premises;
  line
  line `(14) the regulation of smoke in factories, workshops and trade premises;`
  line
  line `(15) the regulation of sanitary conditions in factories, workshops, and trade premises;`
  line
  line `(16) the regulation of the use in any factory, workshop or trade premises of whistle, trumpet,`
  line `siren, or horn worked by steam, compressed air, electricity or other mechanical means;`
  line
  line `(17) the prevention of nuisance in any market building, market place, or any factory, workshop or`
  line `trade premises.`
  line
  line `I. Bye-laws relating to improvement`
  line
  line `(1) the form and content of an improvement scheme or a rehousing scheme;`
  line
  line `(2) the procedure to be followed in connection with the framing, submission, approval and`
  line `sanction of such schemes;`
  line
  line `(3) the local enquiries and other hearings that may be held before a scheme is framed, approved`
  line `or sanctioned;`
  line
  line `(4) the alteration of an improvement scheme or a rehousing scheme after approval and sanction.`
  line
  line `J. Bye-laws relating to miscellaneous matters`
  line
  line `(1) the circumstances and the manner in which owners of land or building in New Delhi`
  line `temporarily absent therefrom or not resident therein may be required to appoint as their agents for all`
  line `or any of the purposes of this Act or of any bye-laws made thereunder, persons residing within or near`
  line `New Delhi;`
  line
  line `(2) the maintenance of schools and the furtherance of education generally;`
  line
  line `(3) the regulation and control of municipal dispensaries;`
  line
  line `(4) the rendering necessary of licences--`
  line
  line `(a) for the proprietors or drivers of hackney-carriages; cycle-rickshaws, thelas and rehries`
  line `kept or plying for hire or used for hawking articles;`
  line
  line `(b) for persons working as job-porters for the conveyance of goods;`
  line
  line `(5) the classification of cinema theatres for the purpose of the Third Schedule;`
  line
  line `(6) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed by bye-laws made under this Act or in`
  line `respect of which this Act makes no provisions or makes insufficient provision and provision is, in the`
  line `opinion of the Council necessary for the efficient municipal government of New Delhi.`
  line
  line `(2) Any bye-law which may be made under sub-section (1) may be made by the Central Government`
  line `within one year of the establishment of the Council, and any bye-law so made may be altered or rescinded`
  line `by the Council in exercise of its powers under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_389:
  sectionId (48784)
  sectionNo (389)
  orderNo 389
  title `Regulations and bye-laws to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_389_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48784&sectionno=389&orderno=389&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_389_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall`
  line `cause every regulation made under this Act and every bye-law made under section 388 to be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of`
  line `thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the regulation or bye-law or both Houses agree that the`
  line `regulation or bye-law should not be made, the regulation or bye-law shall thereafter have effect only in`
  line `such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that regulation or`
  line bye-law.
obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_390:
  sectionId (48785)
  sectionNo (390)
  orderNo 390
  title `Penalty for breaches of bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_390_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48785&sectionno=390&orderno=390&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_390_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any bye-law made under this Act may provide that a`
  line `contravention thereof shall be punishable--`
  line
  line `(a) with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees; and`
  line
  line `(b) with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and in the case of a continuing`
  line `contravention, with an additional fine which may extend to twenty rupees for every day during which`
  line `such contravention continues after conviction for the first such contravention;`
  line
  line `(c) with fine which may extend to twenty rupees for every day during which the contravention`
  line `continues, after the receipt of a notice from the Chairperson or any municipal officer duly authorised`
  line `in that behalf, by the person contravening the bye-law requiring such person to discontinue such`
  line `contravention:`
  line
  line `Provided that a contravention of any bye-law relating to the road transport services may be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to`
  line `fifteen hundred rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such bye-law may also provide that a person contravening the same shall be required to`
  line `remedy so far as lies in his power, the mischief, if any, caused by such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_391:
  sectionId (48786)
  sectionNo (391)
  orderNo 391
  title `Supplemental provisions respecting bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_391_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48786&sectionno=391&orderno=391&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_391_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any power to make bye-laws conferred`
  line `by this Act is conferred subject to the condition of the bye-laws being made after previous publication and`
  line `in the case of such bye-laws being made by the Council of their not taking effect until they have been`
  line `approved by the Government and published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government in approving a bye-law may make any change therein which appears to it to be`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(3) The Government may, after previous publication of its intention, cancel any bye-law which it has`
  line `approved, and thereupon the bye-law shall cease to have effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_392:
  sectionId (48787)
  sectionNo (392)
  orderNo 392
  title `Bye-laws to be available for inspection and purchase.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_392_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48787&sectionno=392&orderno=392&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_392_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of all bye-laws made`
  line `under this Act shall be kept at the municipal office and shall, during office hours, be open free of charge`
  line `to inspection by any inhabitant of New Delhi.`
  line
  line `(2) Copies of all such bye-laws shall be kept at the municipal office and shall be sold to the public at`
  line `cost price either singly or in collections at the option of the purchaser.`
obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_393:
  sectionId (48788)
  sectionNo (393)
  orderNo 393
  title `Government to require production of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_393_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48788&sectionno=393&orderno=393&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_393_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may at any time`
  line `require the Chairperson--`
  line
  line `(a) to produce any record, correspondence, plan or other document in his possession or under his`
  line control;
  line
  line `(b) to furnish any return, plan, estimate, statement, account or statistics relating to the`
  line `proceedings, duties or works of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) to furnish or obtain and furnish any report.`
obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_394:
  sectionId (48789)
  sectionNo (394)
  orderNo 394
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_394_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48789&sectionno=394&orderno=394&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_394_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may depute any person in the service of that Government`
  line `to inspect or examine any municipal department or office or any service or work undertaken by the`
  line `Council or any property belonging to the Council and to report thereon and the Council, the Chairperson`
  line `and all municipal officers and other municipal employees shall be bound to afford the person so deputed`
  line `access at all reasonable time to the premises and properties of the Council and to all records, accounts and`
  line `other documents the inspection of which he may consider necessary to enable him to discharge his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_395:
  sectionId (48790)
  sectionNo (395)
  orderNo 395
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_395_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48790&sectionno=395&orderno=395&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_395_content:
  string
  line `If, whether on receipt of a report or on receipt of any`
  line `information or report obtained under section 393 or section 394 or otherwise, the Central Government is`
  line `of opinion,--`
  line
  line `(a) that any duty imposed on the Council by or under this Act has not been performed or has been`
  line `performed in an imperfect, insufficient or unsuitable manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) that adequate financial provision has not been made for the performance of any such duty,`
  line
  line `it may direct the Council within such period as it thinks fit, to make arrangements to its satisfaction for`
  line `the proper performance of the duty, or as the case may be, to make financial provision, to its satisfaction`
  line `for the performance of the duty and the Council shall comply with such direction:`
  line
  line `Provided that unless in the opinion of the Central Government the immediate execution of such order`
  line `is necessary, it shall before making any direction under this section give the Council an opportunity of`
  line `showing cause why such direction should not be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_396:
  sectionId (48791)
  sectionNo (396)
  orderNo 396
  title `Power to provide for enforcement of direction under section 395.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_396_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48791&sectionno=396&orderno=396&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_396_content:
  string
  line `If, within the period fixed`
  line `by a direction made under section 395, any action the taking of which has been directed under that section`
  line `has not been duly taken, the Central Government may make arrangements for the taking of such action`
  line `and may direct that all expenses connected therewith shall be defrayed out of the New Delhi Municipal`
  line Fund.
obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_397:
  sectionId (48792)
  sectionNo (397)
  orderNo 397
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions in relation to primary schools, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_397_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_397_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48792&sectionno=397&orderno=397&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_397_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may give the Council all such directions as it considers necessary in respect`
  line `of subjects, curricula, text books, standards and methods of teaching in primary schools vested in the`
  line `Council or maintained wholly or partly by grants paid out of the New Delhi Municipal Fund and in`
  line `respect of such other matters as that Government considers necessary and the Council shall comply with`
  line `all such directions.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be lawful for any officer appointed by the Central Government in this behalf to inspect any`
  line `such school; and all reasonable facilities shall be given to such officer in connection with the inspection.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government, after considering the report of inspection made by such officer, may`
  line `give the Council such directions as it considers necessary and the Council shall comply with such`
  line directions
obj_root_law_sections_397_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_398:
  sectionId (48793)
  sectionNo (398)
  orderNo 398
  title `Dissolution of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_398_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_398_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48793&sectionno=398&orderno=398&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_398_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the opinion of the Central Government, the Council is`
  line `not competent to perform, or persistently makes default--`
  line
  line `(a) in the performance of, the duties imposed on it by or under this Act or any other law, or`
  line `exceeds or abuses its power; or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to deliver efficient service to the public and generally in regard to the municipal`
  line `administration; or`
  line
  line `(c) to comply with the directions given to the Council by the Central Government in regard to`
  line `matters relating to clauses (a) and (b),`
  line `the Central Government may by an order published, together with a statement of the reasons therefor, in`
  line `the Official Gazette, dissolve the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council shall be given reasonable opportunity of being heard before its dissolution.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Council is dissolved by an order under sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) all members shall, on the date of dissolution, vacate their offices as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) during the period of dissolution of the Council, all powers and duties conferred and imposed`
  line `upon the Council by or under this Act or any other law, shall be exercised and performed by such`
  line `officer or authority as the Central Government may appoint in that behalf; and`
  line
  line `(c) all property vested in the Council shall, until it is reconstituted, vest in the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) An order of dissolution made under this section together with a statement of the reasons therefor`
  line `shall be laid before each House of Parliament and the Legislative Assembly of the National Capital`
  line `Territory of Delhi as soon as may be, after it has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_398_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_399:
  sectionId (48794)
  sectionNo (399)
  orderNo 399
  title `Delegation of power by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_399_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_399_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48794&sectionno=399&orderno=399&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_399_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act shall, subject to`
  line `such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification be exercisable by the Government or any of`
  line `its officers or by the Chairperson or any other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_399_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_400:
  sectionId (48795)
  sectionNo (400)
  orderNo 400
  title `Power to delegate functions of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_400_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48795&sectionno=400&orderno=400&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_400_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act shall, subject to`
  line `such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification be exercisable by the Government or any of`
  line `its officers or by the Chairperson or any other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_401:
  sectionId (48796)
  sectionNo (401)
  orderNo 401
  title `Validity of notices and other documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_401_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_401_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48796&sectionno=401&orderno=401&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_401_content:
  string
  line `No notice, order, requisition, licence, permission in`
  line `writing or any other document issued under this Act shall be invalid merely by reason of defect of form.`
obj_root_law_sections_401_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_402:
  sectionId (48797)
  sectionNo (402)
  orderNo 402
  title `Admissibility of document or entry as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_402_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_402_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48797&sectionno=402&orderno=402&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_402_content:
  string
  line `A copy of any receipt, application, plan,`
  line `notice, order or other document or of any entry in a register in the possession of the Council or the`
  line `Chairperson shall, if duly certified by the legal keeper thereof or other person authorised by the`
  line `Chairperson in this behalf, be admissible in evidence of the existence of the document or entry, and shall`
  line `be admitted as evidence of the matters and transactions therein recorded in every case where, and to the`
  line `same extent to which, the original document or entry would, if produced, have been admissible to prove`
  line `such matters and transactions.`
obj_root_law_sections_402_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_403:
  sectionId (48798)
  sectionNo (403)
  orderNo 403
  title `Evidence of Municipal officer or employee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_403_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48798&sectionno=403&orderno=403&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_403_content:
  string
  line `No municipal officer or other municipal`
  line `employee shall, in any legal proceedings to which the Council is not a party, be required to produce any`
  line `register or document the contents of which can be proved under section 402 by a certified copy, or to`
  line `appear as a witness to prove any matter or transaction recorded therein save by order of the court made`
  line `for special cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_404:
  sectionId (48799)
  sectionNo (404)
  orderNo 404
  title `Prohibition against obstruction of any municipal authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_404_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48799&sectionno=404&orderno=404&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_404_content:
  string
  line `No person shall obstruct or`
  line `molest the Council or the Chairperson or the Vice-Chairperson or any member or any person employed`
  line `by the Council or any person with whom the Chairperson has entered into a contract on behalf of the`
  line `Council in the performance of their duty or of anything which they are empowered or required to do by`
  line `virtue or in consequence of any provision of this Act or of any rule, regulation or bye-law made`
  line thereunder.
obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_405:
  sectionId (48800)
  sectionNo (405)
  orderNo 405
  title `Prohibition against removal of mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_405_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_405_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48800&sectionno=405&orderno=405&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_405_content:
  string
  line `No person shall remove any mark set up for the`
  line `purpose of indicating any level or direction incidental to the execution of any work authorised by this Act`
  line `or of any rule or bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_405_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_406:
  sectionId (48801)
  sectionNo (406)
  orderNo 406
  title `Prohibition against removal or obliteration of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_406_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_406_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48801&sectionno=406&orderno=406&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_406_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without authority in`
  line `that behalf, remove, destroy, deface or otherwise obliterate any notice exhibited by or under orders of the Council or the Chairperson or any municipal officer or other municipal employee specified by the`
  line `Chairperson in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_406_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_407:
  sectionId (48802)
  sectionNo (407)
  orderNo 407
  title `Prohibition against unauthorised dealings with public place or materials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_407_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48802&sectionno=407&orderno=407&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_407_content:
  string
  line `No person shall,`
  line `without authority in that behalf, remove earth, sand or other material or deposit any matter or make any`
  line `encroachment from, in or on any land vested in the Council or in any way obstruct the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_408:
  sectionId (48818)
  sectionNo (408)
  orderNo 408
  title `Liability of Chairperson, etc., for loss, waste or misapplication of New Delhi Municipal Fund or property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_408_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_408_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48818&sectionno=408&orderno=408&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_408_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every member, Chairperson, and every municipal officer and other municipal`
  line `employee shall be liable for the loss, waste, or misapplication of any money or other property owned by`
  line `or vested in the Council, if such loss, waste or misapplication is a direct consequence of his neglect or`
  line `misconduct and a suit for compensation may be instituted against him by the Council with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Central Government or by the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such suit shall be instituted within three years after the date on which the cause of action`
  line arose.
obj_root_law_sections_408_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_409:
  sectionId (48804)
  sectionNo (409)
  orderNo 409
  title `Members and municipal officers and employees to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_409_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48804&sectionno=409&orderno=409&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_409_content:
  string
  line `Every member, the`
  line `Chairperson, and every municipal officer and other municipal employee shall be deemed to be a public`
  line `servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and in the definition of`
  line `"legal remuneration" in section 161 of that Code the word "Government" shall, for the purpose of this`
  line `section, be deemed to include the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_410:
  sectionId (48805)
  sectionNo (410)
  orderNo 410
  title `Annual administration report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_410_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48805&sectionno=410&orderno=410&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_410_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the first day of April in every`
  line `year and not later than such date as may be fixed by the Central Government in this behalf, the Council`
  line `shall submit to that Government a detailed report of the municipal government of New Delhi during the`
  line `preceding year in such form as that Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall prepare such report and the Council shall consider it and forward the same`
  line `to the Central Government with its resolution thereon, if any.`
  line
  line `(3) Copies of the report shall be kept for sale at the municipal office.`
obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_411:
  sectionId (48806)
  sectionNo (411)
  orderNo 411
  title `Other laws not to be disregarded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_411_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_411_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48806&sectionno=411&orderno=411&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_411_content:
  string
  line `Save as provided in this Act nothing contained in this Act`
  line `shall be construed as authorising the disregard by the Council or the Chairperson or any municipal officer`
  line `or other municipal employee of any laws for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_411_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_412:
  sectionId (48807)
  sectionNo (412)
  orderNo 412
  title `Exemption of diplomatic or consular missions from payment of tax, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_412_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_412_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48807&sectionno=412&orderno=412&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_412_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may, by order in the Official Gazette, exempt from the payment of any tax, rate, fee or other`
  line `charge payable under the provisions of this Act, any diplomatic or consular mission of a foreign State or`
  line `the High Commission of a Commonwealth country and any official of such mission or High Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_412_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_413:
  sectionId (48808)
  sectionNo (413)
  orderNo 413
  title `Construction of references.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_413_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_413_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48808&sectionno=413&orderno=413&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_413_content:
  string
  line `After the establishment of the Council any reference in any`
  line `enactment, rule, bye-law, order, scheme, notification or other instrument having the force of law, to New`
  line `Delhi Municipal Committee shall, unless the context or subject otherwise requires, be construed as a`
  line `reference to the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_413_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_414:
  sectionId (48809)
  sectionNo (414)
  orderNo 414
  title `Council to undertake work on agency basis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_414_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_414_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48809&sectionno=414&orderno=414&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_414_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other provision of this Act, the Council may on such terms and conditions as may be determined by`
  line `agreement between the Council and any other authority, body or person, carry out any work which is not`
  line `connected with its functions on agency basis.`
obj_root_law_sections_414_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_415:
  sectionId (48810)
  sectionNo (415)
  orderNo 415
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_415_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_415_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48810&sectionno=415&orderno=415&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_415_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in relation to the transition from the`
  line `provisions of any of the laws repealed by this Act, or in giving effect to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `Central Government may, by order as occasion requires, do anything which appears to it to be necessary`
  line `for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiration of two years from the date of`
  line `establishment of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_415_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_416:
  sectionId (48811)
  sectionNo (416)
  orderNo 416
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_416_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_416_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48811&sectionno=416&orderno=416&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_416_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the date of the establishment of the Council, the Punjab`
  line `Municipal Act, 1911 (Punjab Act 3 of 1911), as applicable to New Delhi, shall cease to have effect within`
  line `New Delhi.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the provisions of sub-section (1) of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) any appointment, notification, order, scheme, rule, form, notice or bye-law made or issued,`
  line `and any licence or permission granted under the Act referred to in sub-section (1) of this section and`
  line `in force immediately before the establishment of the Council, shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent`
  line `with the provisions of this Act continue in force and be deemed to have been made, issued or granted,`
  line `under the provisions of this Act, unless and until it is superseded by any appointment, notification,`
  line `order, scheme, rule, form, notice or bye-law made or issued or any licence or permission granted`
  line `under the said provisions;`
  line
  line `(b) all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all contracts entered into and all matters and`
  line `things engaged to be done by, with or for the New Delhi Municipal Committee before the`
  line `establishment of the Council shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into or engaged to be`
  line `done by, with or for the Council under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all budget estimates, assessments, valuations, measurements or divisions made by the New`
  line `Delhi Municipal Committee shall in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act,`
  line `continue in force and be deemed to have been made under the provisions of this Act unless and until`
  line `they are superseded by any budget estimate, assessment, valuation, measurement or division made by`
  line `the Council under the said provisions;`
  line
  line `(d) all properties, movable and immovable and all interests of whatsoever nature and kind therein,`
  line `vested in the New Delhi Municipal Committee immediately before the establishment of the Council`
  line `shall with all rights of whatsoever description, use, enjoyed or possessed by New Delhi Municipal`
  line `Committee vest in the Council;`
  line
  line `(e) all rates, taxes, fees, rents and other sums of money due to the New Delhi Municipal`
  line `Committee immediately before the establishment of the Council shall be deemed to be due to the`
  line Council;
  line
  line `(f) all rates, taxes, fees, rents, fares and other charges shall, until and unless they are varied by the`
  line `Council continue to be levied at the same rate at which they were being levied by the New Delhi`
  line `Municipal Committee immediately before the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) all suits, prosecutions and other legal proceedings instituted or which might have been`
  line `instituted by or against the New Delhi Municipal Committee may be continued or instituted by or`
  line `against the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_416_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_417:
  sectionId (48825)
  sectionNo (417)
  orderNo 417
  title `Expenditure in connection with the Council from the commencement of this Act to the adoption of the budget by the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_417_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_417_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48825&sectionno=417&orderno=417&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_417_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any expenditure incurred during the period between the`
  line `commencement of this Act and establishment of the Council under any of the provisions of this Act shall`
  line `be borne by the Central Government and the amount of the expenditure so incurred shall on such`
  line `establishment be recoverable by that Government from out of the New Delhi Municipal Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) If in respect of the period between the establishment of the Council and the adoption of the first`
  line `budget by the Council further expenditure from the New Delhi Municipal Fund becomes necessary over`
  line `and above the expenditure thereto authorised for that year by the sanctioned budget estimate, the Council`
  line `shall adopt a supplementary statement showing the estimated amount of that expenditure.`
  line
  line `(3) Every item of expenditure shown in the supplementary statements adopted by the Council shall be`
  line `deemed to be expenditure covered by a current budget-grant within the meaning of section 47.`
  line
  line `(4) The supplementary statement shall be prepared, presented, and adopted in such manner and shall`
  line `provide for such matter as may be determined by the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_417_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_418:
  sectionId (48813)
  sectionNo (418)
  orderNo 418
  title `Transitory provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_418_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_418_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48813&sectionno=418&orderno=418&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_418_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Central`
  line `Government may, if necessary, appoint a person to be called the Special Officer, to exercise the powers`
  line `and discharge the functions of the Council until the day on which the first meeting of the Council is held`
  line `after the commencement of this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_418_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_419:
  sectionId (48814)
  sectionNo (419)
  orderNo 419
  title `Repeal of Ordinance 8 of 1994.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_419_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_419_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932&sectionId=48814&sectionno=419&orderno=419&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00017_199444_1517807323932
obj_root_law_sections_419_content:
  string
  line `(1) The New Delhi Municipal Council Ordinance, 1994`
  line `(Ordinance 8 of 1994), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provision of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_419_footnotes:
  string
  line
